title: pistachio cake
directions: In bowl combine cake, orange juice, eggs, oil and pudding. Mix until blended.
Pour 2/3 of batter into greased Bundt pan. Mix last 1/3 of batter with chocolate syrup.
Pour over top.
Cut through to marbleize.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream the margarine and sugar. Add eggs (beaten).
Stir in bananas.
Sift soda and flour.
Add alternately with milk.
Add pecans and vanilla. Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes in 3 greased and floured loaf pans.

title: molasses milk shake
directions: Blend milk and molasses thoroughly in a shaker, if desired, and serve very cold over cracked ice or with a scoop of ice cream.

title: willie mae's pizza
directions: Sprinkle cutting board	or
flat
surface
to
work on. With rolling pin or glass, roll out each biscuit to its extent (until it flattens).
Put	sauce
meat
and sprinkle with both cheeses. Place on a	cookie	sheet and let bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: venison medallions
directions: Let chops reach room temperature.
Sprinkle with garlic salt and let stand 15 minutes.
Mix milk with Worcestershire, enough to give it a brown color.
Marinate chops in this mix about 10 minutes.
Roll in bread crumbs, season lightly and fry in very hot oil until golden brown.

title: cindy's cream of crab soup
directions: Make sure cartilage is removed from crabmeat.
Melt butter in small soup pot.
Saute onion in butter until translucent.
Blend in flour and stir until smooth.
Slowly stir in chicken broth and pepper and simmer for several minutes.
Add milk and cook slowly, stirring constantly until thickened.
Do not boil.
Soup will be fairly thin.
Add crabmeat to milk mixture and salt to taste. Remove from heat and serve or you may transfer soup to crock-pot and cook on low until ready to eat.

title: oyster crax smack
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour over 12 ounce package of oyster crackers.
Pour on a cookie sheet. Bake in a 300° oven for 30 minutes, stirring every 10 minutes.

title: warm potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes.
Cut peppers into strips and saute in olive oil along with garlic.
Add small amount of black pepper.
Cut warm, cooked potatoes into chunks.
Add pepper mixture to potatoes.
Sprinkle with lemon juice and salt to taste.
Serve warm.

title: cheese fondue
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Add and stir until browned, the bread cubes (approximately 5 slices).
Place cubes in greased 1-quart casserole in alternate layers with shredded cheese.
Mix beaten egg, milk, salt, pepper and dry mustard and pour over bread cubes. Sprinkle with paprika.
Place casserole in pan of water (1-inch deep) and bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Serve hot.
Serves 4.

title: spice cupcakes
directions: Pour boiling water over shortening.
Stir into raisins and soda.
Add sugar, egg and flour sifted with cinnamon and salt.
Add nuts.
Bake 25 minutes in 375° oven.
Ice with brown sugar and milk boiled icing.

title: icing for cake
directions: Mix sugar and flour.
Cut oranges and lemons up in small pieces, not using rinds.
Cook until thick (like honey), then put mixture between layers.
Put 1/2 box of coconut in syrup mixture and put the rest of it on the top and sides of cake.
Decorate with pecan halves.

title: pecan pie squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease jelly roll pan.
Beat the first 4 ingredients in large bowl on medium speed until crumbly.
Press into jelly roll pan and bake 20 minutes until light golden brown. Mix remaining ingredients except pecans until well blended.
Stir in pecans.
Pour over crust.
Bake another 25 minutes and then cut into squares.

title: hot and spicy chicken pie
directions: Combine chicken, corn, broth, celery and onion.
Bring to boiling; reduce heat.
Simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
Add salsa.
Stir 2 tablespoons water into cornstarch.
Add to chicken mixture. Cook and stir until bubbly.
Cook 2 minutes more.
Prepare corn bread according to package directions.
Pour chicken mixture into 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with cheese and chilies. Spoon corn bread atop.
Bake in 425° oven 20 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: disappearing brownies
directions: Melt butterscotch morsels and margarine over low heat and allow to cool.
Mix next 6 ingredients well, adding butterscotch mixture. Fold in marshmallows, chocolate chips and nuts.
Pour into greased 9 x 12 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Center will be "jiggly" but will harden as it cools.

title: banana and peach salad
directions: Slice bananas and sprinkle with lemon juice.
Let set; drain before mixing with other ingredients.
Mix all ingredients with mayonnaise and chill.

title: sour cream raisin pie
directions: Mix and pat into pie pan.
Bake at 350° until brown; let cool.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients until like dough.
Melt chocolate chips and paraffin.
Melt separately, then pour together.
Dip each ball in chocolate one at a time.
Lay on wax paper.

title: apple pie
directions: Combine all ingredients except oleo.
Put into prepared pie shell.
Dot with the 2 tablespoons oleo.
Put on top crust.
Bake at 425° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: buckeyes(peanut butter balls)
directions: Beat butter and peanut butter together till blended. Mix powdered sugar in by hand. Roll into 3/4 to 1 inch balls. Chill or freeze. Makes about 150. Melt 1 pkg chocolate candy coating in microwave bowl. Dip peanut butter balls in chocolate coating; let drip. Dry on waxed paper.

title: bean casserole
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: turkey or chicken casserole
directions: Line bottom of casserole dish with onion.
Mix soup with 2 cans of water.
Alternate layers of soup, rice and meat.
Salt and pepper top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until rice is done.

title: fancy meatloaf
directions: Combine all ingredients except ketchup in a large bowl.
Put mixture evenly into pan.
Drizzle with ketchup.

title: old time molasses cookies
directions: Mix oil, molasses, eggs and sugar in a large mixing bowl.
Sift dry ingredients into the above mixture.
Blend well.
Chill dough for at least one hour.
Roll into balls (one teaspoon).
I use a cookie scoop to make ball.
Roll in granulated sugar and flatten with bottom of glass.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 375 degrees for 10 minutes.
Do not over bake.
Store in airtight tin or container.

title: blueberry dessert
directions: Mix jello, water, pie filling and pineapple with juice.
Leave in refrigerator overnight.
Next day, mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla together.
Put on top of the other ingredients and let refrigerate until ready to use.

title: best yet cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients by hand.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and salt; add evaporated milk, then egg yolks and beat well.
Add fresh milk and cook in a heavy saucepan or double boiler, stirring continually, until thick. Remove from heat.
Add coconut and vanilla.
Pour into a cool pie shell.
Whip egg whites until frothy; add 1/4 cup sugar gradually. Beat until meringue stands in soft peaks.
Add 1/4 teaspoon vanilla.
Spread over cooled pie filling, sealing meringue to edge of crust.
Sprinkle with 1/4 cup coconut and brown in 350° oven.

title: risotto a la pie montese
directions: Combine olive oil and butter in a pan; heat.
Add onions and cook slowly until light brown.
Add ground meat and bay leaves; brown slowly for 10 minutes.
Add the tomato and mushrooms with 1/2 cup water.
Cover and cook for 10 minutes.
Add rice; stir well and brown for 2 minutes.
Add 3 cups of chicken broth and use balance of broth as needed.
Cover and simmer for 17 minutes.
Add salt and pepper as needed.
When cooked, remove from the heat.
Do not overcook.
Sprinkle cheese over top.
Serve immediately.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: peppermint cheesecake
directions: Combine crumbs and margarine.
Press into bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt together chocolate chips, margarine and peanut butter. Put cereal in two large bowls.
Pour melted mixture over cereal. Put mixture into large paper bag with 2 cups powdered sugar (may need more).
Shake vigorously.
Store in airtight containers.

title: chocolate rice krispy cookies
directions: In large mixing bowl, cream Promise and sugar; add egg whites and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add flour, baking powder and salt; mix well.
Stir in cereal and chocolate chips.
Bake in 350° oven for approximately 12 minutes.

title: play dough(for kids)
directions: Mix dry ingredients, add oil, water, coloring and flavoring. Mix well.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until it reaches the consistency of mashed potatoes.
Remove from heat, turn out on board and knead several times.
Store in airtight container.

title: pecan tassies
directions: Cheese Pastry:
Let cream cheese and 1/2 cup butter soften at room temperature, then blend together.
Stir in flour.
Chill 1 hour.
Shape into 2 dozen 1-inch balls.
Place in ungreased 1 3/4-inch muffin tins.
Press dough evenly against all sides.

title: ham and asparagus au gratin
directions: Wrap each ham slice around 4 asparagus spears and place, seam side down, in a greased 11 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish. Beat together eggs and yolks, cream, salt and pepper. Pour over ham rolls. Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes or until top begins to brown and the tip of a knife inserted in the egg mixture comes out clean. Sprinkle with cheese and parsley (optional). Serve immediately. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: beautiful blondies(brownies)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly coat 8-inch square baking pan with vegetable cooking spray.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt in bowl.
Beat margarine, sugar and corn syrup in mixer bowl at medium speed.
Beat in egg whites and vanilla until well blended.
At low speed, gradually add dry ingredients until just combined.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Spread batter in prepared pan and sprinkle top with nuts.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes, until top is golden and toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan on wire rack.
Cut into squares.
Makes 16.

title: hawaiian wedding cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to directions on package.
Spread batter in greased and floured jelly roll pan (15 x 10 x 1-inch). Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Prepare pudding mix using the chilled milk.
Fold in well-drained pineapple.
Spread mixture evenly over cooked cake.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle top with coconut and garnish with nuts and cherries.
Refrigerate.

title: corn and rice casserole
directions: Prepare rice according to package directions; add margarine. Stir until melted.
Add corn and soup.
Combine the cheese with the mixture.
Put in casserole dish and bake 30 minutes at 350°. Remove from oven; sprinkle with some cheese on top and return to oven until melted.
Sprinkle some paprika for color.

title: jack's vegetable soup
directions: In a 2 or 3-quart saucepan, filled with water, add bouillon cubes.
Chop and add onion, celery and carrots.
Add onion powder and garlic powder.
Add whatever leftover meat you want.
Cook 30 minutes.
Add rice and cook 30 minutes (or even a Ziploc bag of leftover rice).
Right before serving, add any leftovers in the icebox.

title: no cook chow chow(delicious)
directions: Grind tomatoes, cabbage, onions, pepper and celery.
Mix with 1/2 cup canning salt.
Cover with cheesecloth and drain for 1 to 2 hours.

title: green bean casserole(makes 6 to 8 servings)
directions: Cook green beans as usual; drain and set aside.
Make a paste of the flour and butter, adding the sugar, salt and onion.
Add sour cream and Swiss cheese.
Gently fold in the green beans and spoon it into a greased casserole, covering with cornflakes.
Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes.

title: potato salad
directions: In 4-quart saucepan, cook potatoes 5 minutes over high heat. Reduce to low.
Simmer 20 to 30 minutes.
Drain.
Cool slightly. Peel potatoes.
Cut in cubes.
In large bowl, combine soups, mayonnaise, vinegar and pepper until well blended.
Add potatoes, celery, peas, radishes and eggs.
Toss gently to coat.
Cover. Refrigerate until serving time, at least 4 hours.
Makes about 7 cups or 8 servings.

title: cherry yum-yum
directions: Combine margarine, crumbs and 1/4 cup sugar in a bowl; set aside.
Combine Dream Whip, milk and vanilla in a large mixing bowl.
Then add sugar and cream cheese into mix and beat smooth.

title: chunky tomato salsa
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Can store up to 5 days in refrigerator.

title: apple crunch
directions: Put apples in bottom of greased pan (9 x 13-inch).
Cut rest of ingredients together until coarse.
Put on top of apples.
Bake at 350° until apples are tender and crust is golden.

title: cheese rice with broccoli: 15 minutes
directions: Bring broccoli, water and milk to boil in saucepan.
Add 5 of the cheese slices; stir until completely melted.
Stir in rice; cover.
Remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Fluff with fork. Garnish with remaining cheese slice.
Makes 6 servings.
Recipe can be doubled.

title: caramel apple dip
directions: Blend all ingredients together and use as a dip.

title: rice pudding
directions: Boil and drain raisins.
Put aside.
Boil 5 cups of water and pinch of salt.
On low heat, put in rice and cook for 15 minutes, stirring frequently.
Do not drain.

title: snowball cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Using electric mixer, cream butter, add sugar gradually, flour, salt and vanilla.
Mix well with your hands until dough holds together.
If necessary, add 1 to 2 teaspoons of cold water.

title: alabama biscuits
directions: Sift the flour, sugar, salt and soda together into a bowl and cut in the shortening.
Dissolve the yeast in the buttermilk, then stir into the flour mixture.
Turn out onto a floured board and knead 30 times.
Roll out 1/4-inch thick and cut with biscuit cutter.
Butter tops and stack 2 biscuits together until all are stacked.
Place on a baking sheet and let rise until doubled in bulk.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: beef-salami
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate.
Each day for 3 days, mix for 5 minutes.
On the fourth day, shape into 3 rolls and place on a jelly roll pan and bake at 150° for 10 hours.
After about 8 hours, turn rolls over so bottoms can brown.
This will keep in the refrigerator for about 6 weeks and also freezes well.

title: pat's pan-fried trout
directions: Dip each fish fillet in bowl of hot sauce.
Then shake in paper bag with fish breading..
Heat olive oil in skillet.
Fry fillets 3 to 4 minutes on each side.
They should brown nicely and fish should flake.

title: spaetzle
directions: In a 6-quart Dutch oven over high heat, heat 4 quarts of water and 1 teaspoon salt to boiling. Meanwhile, in medium bowl with wire whisk or spoon, beat flour, water, eggs and salt until smooth. Reduce heat to medium. Over boiling water with rubber spatula, press butter through colander or spaetzle maker. Stir water gently so spaetzle will not stick together.
Boil 5 minutes or until tender, but firm; drain.

title: diet cheese cake(make in blender)
directions: After blending all ingredients, place in 8 or 9-inch greased Pyrex pie plate.
Place cinnamon on top.
Place in 350° oven for 45 minutes or until finished.

title: lemon-and-lime mist
directions: You will need a tropical flower.

title: crawfish etouffee(may use shrimp instead of crawfish.)
directions: Melt butter in large heavy skillet. Add celery, onions, peppers and garlic. Saut on medium heat until soft. Stir in flour. Add crawfish, water, tomato paste, lemon juice and seasonings. Stir and cook 15 minutes. Cover and simmer another 15 minutes. Stir in parsley and green onions; re-cover. Remove from heat and let set 5 minutes. Serve over rice. Makes 8 servings.

title: creamy pumpkin pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat all ingredients together with rotary or electric beater.
Bake for 50 to 55 minutes until knife inserted in side of filling comes out clean.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mash 3/4 quart berries. Cook over low heat with sugar and cornstarch until slightly thickened. Slice 1/4 quart remaining berries and combine. Cool.
Pour into baked pie shell and chill in refrigerator until set. Top with whipped cream before serving.

title: meat soup
directions: Cook meat in water.
Debone if need to.
Add pepper, peas, potatoes, okra, onion and corn.
Chop vegetables that need to be. Cook until done.
Add tomatoes or tomato juice.
Add rice and egg noodles.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Can add hot pepper if you like.

title: fried chicken
directions: Roll 4 to 6 breasts or legs in flour (self-rising).
Put vegetable oil in frying pan.
Simmer on medium heat for 20 to 30 minutes, covered.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Mix 1 egg and add to milk.
Add to dry ingredients and mix well.
Drop by teaspoon into hot oil. Fry until golden brown.

title: aunt betsy's barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate until ready to use.

title: taco cheese dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and microwave until cheese and margarine are melted. Stir well. Serve with tortilla or other chips.

title: hearty vegetable soup
directions: In a large soup pot, add water, soup starter, lima beans and bouillon cubes.
Simmer for 1 hour.
Cut vegetables and add after first hour.
Simmer on low for 1 hour.
Stewed tomatoes can be added at this time, along with flavor packs from soup mix.
Season to taste with pepper and extra bouillon.
Continue simmering for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: penne rigate with meat sauce peperonata
directions: Cook meat and onion.
Drain fat.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce, red pepper and seasonings.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat.
Simmer 10 minutes, uncovered.
Cook pasta according to package; drain. Toss pasta with meat sauce; sprinkle with cheese.

title: mexican-style ham and cheese in bun
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients in order given; stuff buns with mixture.
Wrap buns in foil.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Sandwiches may be made ahead and frozen.
Bake when ready to serve.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed and drain.
Add the rice, soup and Cheez Whiz.
Mix well and place in a baking dish.
For topping, crumble Ritz crackers; mix with 1 stick melted butter.
Spread on top of casserole.
Bake in 350° preheated oven for about 30 minutes or until it bubbles.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix and bake
in
9 x 13-inch pan.
Place apples in pan and sprinkle
sugar
over
them.
Sift flour and cinnamon over apples. Add eggs,	oil
and
nuts.
Stir
in
pan	until well mixed. Bake 40 to 50 minutes in 350° oven until done.

title: chimichangas
directions: Cook meat, water, garlic and salt 1 1/2 hours until tender. Uncover and boil 12 minutes.
Shred meat and add peppers, vinegar, chili powder, cumin and pepper.
Heat until warm.
Fill warmed tortilla and wrap or roll up envelope fashion.
Cook 3 tortillas in 1 inch of hot oil, about a minute on each side until brown. Drain.
Add garnishes.

title: microwave cheesy ham and vegetable soup
directions: Combine vegetables, water and seasoning in 3-quart casserole. Cook covered on Full power for 7 to 9 minutes or until tender. Stir halfway through cooking time.
Place butter in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Heat Full power for 45 seconds to 1 minute and 15 seconds until melted.
Stir in flour; blend to smooth paste. Gradually blend in milk.
Cook covered on Full power for 8 to 10 minutes until thickened.
Stir 2 to 3 times.
Add sauce to vegetables.
Stir in corn, cheese and ham through.

title: biscuits
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and sugar.
Cut in shortening with pastry blender.
Blend in sour cream.
Turn out on lightly floured board.
Handle gently and make into a ball.
Pat out and cut.
Place in greased baking pan.
Drizzle with squeeze margarine.
Bake in 450° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: baker's 5 minute coconut pie
directions: Beat cream cheese until softened in mixing bowl.
Beat in sugar.
Gradually add milk and beat until smooth.
Fold in coconut, whipped topping and extract.
Spoon into crust.
Freeze until firm, about 4 hours.
Garnish with toasted coconut and maraschino cherries, if desired.
Let stand at room temperature about 15 minutes before cutting.
Store leftovers in freezer.

title: roasted new potatoes
directions: Cook unpeeled potatoes in boiling water about 15 minutes; drain and cool slightly.
Quarter potatoes; spray cut sides with spray.
Combine remaining ingredients; dredge cut sides in mixture.
Place in a single layer on a baking sheet, coated with the cooking spray.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Mix together sugar, flour and eggs in a medium bowl.
Add pineapple with juice.
Pour into a buttered 8 x 8 casserole.
In a bowl, add bread cubes and drizzle with melted butter until bread is coated with butter.
Sprinkle buttered cubes evenly over pineapple mixture and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: waikiki meatballs
directions: Mix 1st six ingredients together into meatballs and brown in pan in 1 tablespoon shortening.
When brown, remove from pan, remove grease and keep warm.
Mix next 5 ingredients.
Stir until smooth and pour into pan and stir until boiling and let boil 1 minute.
Then add meatballs with pineapple chunks and peppers, let cook a few more minutes.

title: tomato and orange salad with orange honey dressing
directions: Tomatoes should be at room temperature.
Core tomatoes.
Cut into wedges (makes about 3 cups).

title: raisin cream pie
directions: Cook raisins in small amount of water until done.
Mix sugar, flour and egg yolks; cream together.
Pour into raisins and cook until thick.
Pour in baked crust.
Cover with beaten egg whites. Return to oven and brown.

title: ground turkey patties
directions: Mix together and form into patties. Cook until no longer pink inside.
(Tastes similar to sausage.)

title: aztec chocolate drink(breakfast drink)
directions: Heat stock and season with cocoa, Tabasco sauce, vanilla and cinnamon.

title: antipasto
directions: Toss together and refrigerate; toss again when ready to serve. (Make all bite size pieces.)

title: macaroni y la tofu
directions: Blend all ingredients, except the parsley, in blender.
Taste (be sure it is seasoned to your taste; add whatever is needed).

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix together the cup of flour, softened butter and confectioners sugar.
Put into 9 x 9-inch pan.
Spread evenly. Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Just before above is ready to come out of oven, mix remaining ingredients.
Pour over crust while still warm.
Put pan back in oven and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix
the
ingredients and pour into pie shell.	Bake at 350° until it is firm and the desired color.

title: panocha(sprouted wheat dessert)
directions: Mix the two kinds of flour thoroughly.
Add one half of the boiling water; stir well.
Set aside and cover.
Let stand for
15 minutes,
then add the rest of the water.
Caramelize the
sugar; add 1 cup boiling water.
When sugar is dissolved, add to flour mixture.
Simmer mixture for 2 hours.
Add butter and place, uncovered,
in 300° hot oven for one hour or until it is quite thick and deep brown.

title: soup with polish sausage
directions: Add water to cover.
Mix all together.
Bring to a boil, then simmer for 1 1/2 hours.
Serve with grated cheese topping.
Salt to taste.

title: wiener mix-up
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place in lightly greased casserole dish (1 1/2-quart).
Put covered casserole in oven heated to 350° for 1 hour.
Cool and serve.

title: peanut butter kisses
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Have cookie sheets ready.
With a wooden spoon, stir sugar, eggs and peanut butter in medium bowl until blended.
Dough will be slightly sticky.
With floured hands, roll level measuring tablespoonfuls into 1 1/4-inch balls.
Bake 12 to 14 minutes, until cookies look dry with tops crackled.

title: christmas eggnog
directions: In a large bowl, beat egg yolks until light.
Gradually beat in 1 cup sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Stir in next 5 ingredients.
Beat egg whites until frothy; gradually add remaining sugar and beat until soft peaks are formed.
Fold in egg whites and whipped cream.
Chill.
Before serving, stir and sprinkle with nutmeg.
Serves 24.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Mix cream cheese, olives, onion and mayonnaise in bowl. Spread small amount of mixture on a tortilla, covering it.
Then place a slice of ham on that.
Roll tortilla up real tight in plastic wrap.
Secure with toothpicks.
Chill in refrigerator until very firm.

title: lemon ecstasy
directions: Press into 13 x 9-inch pan and bake 15 minutes at 375°.
Cool.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix together.
Spread over crust and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool and sprinkle top with powdered sugar.
Cut into squares.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Prepare day before:
Spread 3 slices bread, cubed, in buttered 9 x 11-inch casserole.
Mix the next 6 ingredients and place on cubed bread.
Cube remaining bread and spread over chicken.
Mix eggs with milk.
Stir well and pour over casserole.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown ground beef; add spaghetti sauce.
Beat eggs; add cottage cheese, Parmesan cheese and 1 cup Mozzarella.
Add oregano.

title: marinated salad
directions: Combine oil, vinegar and mayonnaise.
Combine with vegetables and toss together.
Add bacon bits to taste.
Chill.

title: gofor balls
directions: Melt margarine.
Add the remaining ingredients; roll into balls.
Top with chocolate topping, if desired.

title: vegie cheese puffs
directions: Combine broccoli, cauliflower, onions, peppers, cheese, mayo, egg whites, sesame and turmeric. Mix well.

title: pink popcorn surprises
directions: Measure popped corn into large buttered bowl.
In top of double boiler over hot water, heat marshmallows, butter and salt, stirring frequently, until marshmallows melt and mixture is smooth.
Stir in food coloring.
Pour mixture over corn in bowl; toss gently to coat.
With buttered hands, quickly shape mixture around lollipops into 3-inch balls.
Makes 8 to 10 balls.

title: caramel apple dip
directions: Cream the topping, sugar, vanilla and cream cheese until blended and smooth.
Add chopped peanuts.

title: crock-pot chicken and dressing
directions: Saute celery and onion in 1 tablespoon margarine in skillet. In a very large bowl, mix all ingredients.
Stir in chicken.
Pour into the crock-pot.
Cook on high for 45 minutes, then turn on low and cook for 4 hours.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except for tortillas.
Spread mixture over tortilla, then roll it up in jellyroll fashion. Repeat until creamed mixture is gone.
Refrigerate rolls for at least 1 hour.
Slice rolls into bite size pieces.
Serve with toothpicks.
Very good with salsa.

title: pastor's delight
directions: Spread nachos on a large plate.
Layer crab meat and cheese; microwave until cheese melts.
Add peppers and sour cream.
Enjoy.

title: chicken or turkey pot pie
directions: Mix all ingredients (except biscuits) in casserole dish.
Heat until very hot.
Add biscuits on top and cook until done.

title: excellent and easy mix peach cobbler
directions: Grease a 2-quart baking dish or 8-inch square pan.
Mix all ingredients except peaches and 1/4 cup sugar in this dish.
Pour peaches and juice over the somewhat lumpy dough.
Sprinkle with 1/4 cup sugar.
Bake at 350°
for about 45 minutes or until lightly brown.
Serve with whipped topping or is great with a scoop of ice cream.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook sugar, syrup and water until it will spin a thread.
Add peanuts and cook until light brown; add butter and soda.
Spread on greased baking sheet.

title: chicken italian
directions: Dip chicken in melted butter and roll in bread crumbs.
Place in oven baking dish and pour spaghetti sauce on top of chicken; sprinkle with cheese.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cheesy chili dip
directions: Microwave Velveeta and chili in 2-quart microwavable bowl on High 5 minutes or until Velveeta is melted, stirring after 3 minutes. Serve hot with tortilla chips, French bread chunks or corn bread sticks. Makes 3 3/4 cups.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, eggs and juice from pineapple together.
In pan put brown sugar and melted margarine.
Mix well.
Arrange pineapple slices in pan and pour the cake batter over this.
Bake at 350° until cake is done.
Invert on plate.

title: world's best hot fudge sauce
directions: In top of a double boiler, put milk, chocolate and salt.
Cook over rapidly boiling water, stirring often, until thickened. Remove from heat.
Slowly stir in hot water until sauce is of desired thickness.
Stir in vanilla extract.
Makes delicious hot fudge sundaes!
Can be stored in refrigerator and reheated as needed.

title: linda's chicken and rice
directions: Boil chicken in a pot with water, onion, salt and pepper until chicken is tender. Remove chicken and onion from broth, saving broth. Debone chicken. Put chicken meat and 4 cups of the chicken broth in a pot and bring to a boil. Add rice. Stir until it starts to boil. Turn down heat and cover with a tight lid. Keep covered for 20 minutes. Do not lift the lid.

title: green beans with water chestnuts
directions: Cook beans.
Drain and slice water chestnuts.
Add chestnuts to beans and heat.
Can be topped with mushrooms.

title: chocolate sheath cake
directions: Mix sugar and flour and set aside.
Place oleo, water and cocoa in saucepan and bring to boil.
Pour over dry ingredients and stir.
Add eggs, soda and buttermilk.
Bake in sheath pan, 11 x 18-inch for 17 to 20 minutes at 400°.
May use 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch pan.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar for 17 minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Stir in coconut last with a spoon.
Bake in 325° oven for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Start cake in a cool oven.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 2 loaf pans (9 x 5 x 3-inch). Cream shortening and sugar thoroughly.
Add eggs, water and pumpkin.
Blend in dry ingredients.
Stir in nuts and raisins and bake in prepared pans for 60 to 70 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: mounds coconut cream cake
directions: Using an oiled 9 x 13-inch baking pan, mix and bake cake according to package directions.
Remove baked cake from oven; using a fork, poke holes over top of cake.
Mix can of cream of coconut and sweetened condensed milk in a medium bowl and stir with whisk until smooth.
Pour the coconut mixture over the entire cake.
Place in refrigerator overnight.
Spoon whipped topping over the cake and then sprinkle with coconut just prior to serving.
Yield: 12 to 16 servings.

title: pizza in a pocket
directions: Place all ingredients in separate bowls and have the children create their own pizzas.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 400° until cheese is melted.
Great idea for sleepovers and birthday parties.

title: mother's pecan pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix eggs with all ingredients, except pecans.
Mix well; add pecans.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake 45 minutes.
Cool.

title: oh my goodness cookies
directions: Beat softened margarine, sugars and eggs until creamy.
Add vanilla, milk and molasses while continuing to beat (medium speed with electric mixer).
Add flour, baking powder, salt and cinnamon. Mix well.
Stir in oats and wheat germ, mixing well.
Add any optional ingredients you like.
Drop tablespoons of dough on greased cookie sheet with equal spacing.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.
Cool.
Can be frozen.

title: monster cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream in a large bowl peanut butter, granulated sugar, brown sugar, margarine or butter, eggs, baking soda and vanilla.
Stir in M&M's, chocolate chips and Quick oats. Drop by ice cream scoop onto ungreased cookie sheets, 6 to 8 cookies per sheet.
Bake for 8 to 12 minutes.
Leave on cookie sheets until cool.
Makes 50 to 60 cookies.

title: chocolate decadence
directions: Melt chocolate with butter in top of a double boiler. Chocolate chips or chunks of semi-sweet chocolate work equally well.
Don't get any water in chocolate until it is melted. Remove from heat and stir in flour, sugar and hot water.
Separate eggs, slightly beat yolks and stir them into the chocolate mixture.
Beat the whites until stiff, but not dry.
Slowly stir chocolate mixture into the meringue, stirring until well blended. Pour into round 8 to 9-inch cake pan, well buttered.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes only.
It will look undone.
This is best if made in advance and allowed to "age" in refrigerator 2 to 3 days. Can be frozen.
Serve with whipped cream and raspberry puree or fresh raspberries.
This is fantastic!

title: postmaster candy easter eggs
directions: Boil first 3 ingredients for 3 minutes.
Add marshmallows, cracker crumbs and pecans.
(Can omit crumbs and add coconut instead.)
Form eggs and roll in chopped nuts.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix jello, boiling water and cranberry sauce.
Cool and thicken.
Add orange juice, pineapple juice, celery, apples and nuts.
Refrigerate.

title: seafood fettucini
directions: Melt butter; stir in flour.
Gradually add half and half; stir until thickened and add Parmesan.
Cook and stir until thickened. Add crab meat.
Heat 3 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Toss fettucini with sauce; sprinkle in parsley and serve immediately.

title: salad dressing
directions: Cream the mayonnaise and buttermilk together until smooth. Add other ingredients and refrigerate.
Serve on tossed salad.

title: banana cake
directions: Cream butter, oil and sugar. Add eggs.
Sift flour and other dry ingredients together.
Alternately add flour mixture and bananas to the egg mixture.
Fold in nuts and cherries.
Bake in a greased tube pan for 1 1/2 hours at 300°.
May be frozen.

title: corn-on-the-cob
directions: In a large pan, bring to the boil, 4 cups water.
Add corn and reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes or until corn is tender-crisp.
Drain.
Season with butter, salt and pepper.

title: two layer upside-down cake(microwave)
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons margarine in each of two 8-inch microwave cake dishes.
Blend half of the brown sugar with the margarine in each dish and spread evenly over bottom of dish.
Arrange pineapple and drained cherries over brown sugar.
Prepare cake mix according to package directions, substituting reserved pineapple juice for liquid called for on package.
Add water, if necessary, for a full measure.
Pour 2 2/3 cups batter over fruit in both dishes. Spread evenly. (Any extra batter can be used for cupcakes.)
Cook on Medium-high (70%) for 8 to 10 minutes.
Invert one layer onto serving dish and second layer on top of the first. Can be served warm.

title: zucchini vegetable dish
directions: Mix everything but zucchini and cheese.
Simmer until rice is nearly done.
Add zucchini, making sure it does not overcook. (You don't want it soft.)
Take off heat, top with cheese, cover and serve.

title: white fudge
directions: Put sugar and milk in pan and bring to a boil.
Cook for 4 to 5 minutes.
Remove from stove and add butter, vanilla, peanut butter and marshmallows.
Spread in buttered pan.
When cold, cut into squares.

title: italian beef
directions: Mix spices in water.
Pour over meat.
Cook in covered pan for 3 hours at 325°.
Cool in liquid.
When chilled, slice very thin.

title: rita's chili rellenos casserole
directions: Shred cheeses and combine; divide into thirds.
Clean chili peppers, removing any seeds or skin.
Spray 8 x 8-inch square Pyrex baking dish with Pam.
Layer cheeses and chilies in baking dish, starting with cheese and ending with cheese so you have three layers of cheese and two layers of chili peppers.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Beat cake mix, oil, eggs, oranges with juice for 4 minutes. Make 3 layers and bake as directed on box.
Cool.

title: jardinare
directions: Put prepared vegetables in large bowl.
Add 1 cup white cider vinegar and 1/3 cup water and pickle juice if necessary.
Add celery seed and allspice.
Marinate 24 hours minimum.

title: mexican pizza
directions: On round platter, layer beans and then mayonnaise/sour cream mix.
Sprinkle with taco seasoning.
Layer remaining ingredients in order given.
Chill and serve with corn chips.

title: chicken cilantro
directions: Saute the chicken breasts in 1 tablespoon oil.
Set aside. Saute onion and cilantro; set aside.
Place uncooked rice in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch casserole. Top with 1/2 of the tomato slices, onions and cilantro.
Sprinkle with 1/2 of the cheese. Repeat layers of vegetables.
Place chicken breasts on top.
Pour broth over all. Cover and cook in
a 350° oven. Check condition of rice and add more broth, if necessary. Top with cheese and cook, uncovered, until cheese is melted.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Combine remaining ingredients and mix until well blended.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake about 55 minutes at 350°.
Cool before slicing.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Melt oleo, brown sugar, syrup and salt; bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil for 5 minutes more.
Add soda and vanilla.
Pour over popped corn.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump pineapple in buttered 9 by 13 inch pan. Add cherry pie filling on top. Sprinkle dry cake mix over fruit. Dot with butter. Top with chopped nut, if desired. Bake for 45 minutes at 375°. Serve warm with sweetened whipped cream or ice cream.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook, drain and mash squash; salt and pepper to taste.
Mix all ingredients; pour into greased casserole.
Bake at 350°, covered, until set.
Uncover and top with seasoned bread crumbs; lightly brown.

title: batchlin's chili verdi
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper; dust pork cubes in flour mixture.
Combine pork cubes, soup and salsa sauce in pan; cook on low temperature 3 to 4 hours.
Thicken pork mixture with seasoned flour the pork was dusted with.

title: easy vegetable stew
directions: Boil stew meat. Mix meat, vegetables and tomato juice in pot. (May need to add some water.) Add salt and pepper to taste. Let it come to a boil, then simmer.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together and pat into bottom of 9 x 13-inch
pan.
Mix	last 4 ingredients together and spread over top of first ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix pie filling and pineapple. Spread in a long baking dish. Combine cake mix, nuts and oleo.
Sprinkle over pie filling. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Chop shrimp in half or thirds, depending on size.
Chop fine and add parsley, green onions, white onions, pickles and celery. Add pinch of cayenne, salt and black pepper to taste.
Fold in mayonnaise.
Serve on lettuce leaves with crackers.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Cook onions and celery in butter in a covered pan until clear over low heat or medium heat.
Add mushroom soup, crab meat, Lea & Perrins sauce, parsley and seasoning.
Combine well and heat to a complete boil.
Serve warm.

title: taco salad
directions: Chill lettuce.
Brown ground beef with cumin seasoning and onion (if desired).
Drain grease and let cool to room temperature.
Grate cheese.
Add cheese and hamburger to lettuce and place in a bowl.
Mix hot sauce into mayonnaise.
This is your dressing.

title: reduced fat sloppy joes
directions: Cut chicken into small serving pieces; coat with flour.
Heat butter in pan until melted.
Add the chicken and cook until browned on both sides.
Add mushrooms and saute briefly.
Add beef bouillon and Marsala.
Mix together.
Simmer 15 to 30 minutes, turning occasionally.
Season to taste.
Add flour and bouillon; will thicken.
Add more bouillon for more stock.
Add spices (garlic, parsley, etc.), if desired.

title: french onion soup
directions: In large heavy saucepan, melt butter.
Add sliced onions and saute slowly, stirring until golden.
Sprinkle in flour and stir a few minutes.
Add salt and pepper.
Add broth, stirring constantly.
Bring to a boil; lower heat and simmer, partially covered, for 3 minutes.
Toast bread slices.
Sprinkle with a tiny bit of Parmesan.
Press into soup bowl.
Pour soup over bread and top with Swiss or Monterey Jack cheese.
Brown cheese in oven under broiler and serve immediately.
(I put ceramic soup bowls on sturdy cookie sheet on baker's rack.)

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix pecans and coconut together; place in the bottom of pan.
Prepare cake mix as directed.
Pour mixture over pecans and coconut.
Mix sugar, cream cheese and melted margarine together; spoon over cake, here and there.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: holiday eggnog deluxe
directions: Beat egg yolks until thick and lemon colored; gradually add 3/4 cups sugar, vanilla and 1/4 teaspoon nutmeg, beating well at medium speed of an electric mixer.
Cover and chill 8 hours. Place chilled mixture in a punch bowl; gradually stir in cream and milk.
Beat egg whites (at room temperature) in a large mixing bowl until soft peaks form.
Gradually add 1/4 cup sugar and beat until stiff.
Fold whites into chilled mixture.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Yield:
about 3 quarts.

title: french pastry icing
directions: Cook cornstarch and milk until thick.
Cool.
Place all ingredients in a small mixing bowl and beat at high speed for 10 minutes.

title: cranberry sparkler punch
directions: Combine juices, stir until sugar is dissolved.
Add soda and serve over ice.

title: ndiwa za mpiru wotendera(mustard greens with peanut sauce)
directions: Wash greens, trim off any tough stems.
Tear into small pieces.
Bring small amount of water to a boil.
Add salt and greens.
Cook until greens are tender.
Add chopped onions, tomatoes and pepper.
Cook until slightly limp.
Form paste with peanut butter and water.
Pour paste over entire surface of greens.
Cook slowly for 10 minutes, stirring continually to blend.
Continue to cook until moist.
Serve over rice.

title: mom's bourbon bon bon
directions: In large bowl, stir together cookie crumbs, 1 cup confectioners sugar, pecans and cocoa. Stir in bourbon and corn syrup. Shape mixture into 1 inch balls and roll in remaining sugar. Sprinkle confectioners sugar over and under balls in storage container - separate layers with wax or parchment paper. Makes 4 1/2 dozen.

title: crock pot country steak & gravy
directions: Cut steak to fit crock pot; cover steak with soup (do not dilute soup).
Cook on low 6-8 hours.
Serve with rice or potatoes.

title: picnic lemonade
directions: Combine corn syrup, sugar, lemon rind and 2/3 cup water in saucepan. Boil for 5 minutes, stirring to mix well.
Cool. Combine with lemon juice and 7 cups of water in pitcher and mix well.
Serve over ice and garnish with lemon slices.

title: killer ribs
directions: Trim excess fat from ribs.
Place in an 8 to 10-quart pan. Add onion, cinnamon, basil leaves, allspice, ginger, 1 teaspoon of the chilies, bay leaves and garlic.
Fill pan with water to cover ribs.
Boil on high heat.
Reduce to simmer for about 1 hour.
In blender, puree peaches. Stir in barbecue sauce and remaining chilies.
Drain ribs.
Lay on a grill 4 to 6-inches above bed of coals. Baste frequently with peach sauce and turn ribs as needed for a rich brown glaze, about 20 minutes. Add more sauce to ribs as needed and serve.

title: garlic shrimp
directions: Heat oil and butter in a large skillet.
Add garlic and shrimp; sprinkle with salt and pepper to taste.
Saute 2 to 3 minutes, until shrimp is pink.
Turn shrimp with a spatula and cook 2 minutes longer.
Remove shrimp; garnish with lemon wedges. Serve over rice.
Yield:
2 to 3 servings.

title: soda cracker pie
directions: Beat egg white until stiff.
Add 1/2 teaspoon vanilla and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Gradually add sugar.
Continue beating until quite stiff. Then stir in by hand, soda crackers, chopped pecans, baking powder.
Put in greased deep pie dish.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°. Let cool.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Prepare and bake cake mix according to package directions in a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Let cake cool about 10 minutes.
Using the handle of a wooden spoon, punch rows of holes in the top of the cake (about every 1 1/4-inch).
Pour the creme of coconut over entire cake (while still warm).
Let the cake finish cooling so that the creme of coconut will soak into the cake and set.
Ice cake with Cool Whip and sprinkle coconut on top.*

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs, 1 at a time; beat after egg.
Add red food coloring and vanilla.
Mix in flour, cocoa and buttermilk, alternating flour, cocoa and buttermilk when mixing. Mix baking soda and vinegar in small container and add to cake mixture.
Bake in 3 (8 or 9-inch) round pans at 350° for 25 minutes.
Frost with Red Velvet Cake Frosting.

title: impossible taco pie
directions: Grease pie plate (9-inch).
Preheat oven to 400°.
Saute onions, then brown ground meat.
Add seasoning mix and chillies. Blend in blender, milk, eggs and baking mix for one minute.
Pour over meat mixture.
Bake 25 minutes or longer, until knife comes out clean.
Top with cheese and tomato.
Bake additional 6 minutes.

title: whole wheat oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream together the first 6 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients except nuts and mix well.
Add nuts.
Drop by rounded teaspoon onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 350° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes about 5 dozen cookies.

title: sand cookies
directions: Beat margarine and sugar for 5 minutes.
Dissolve soda in vinegar.
Add to mix.
Add vanilla.
Beat in flour.
Fold in chocolate chips (if used).
Drop by teaspoonful onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 275° for 30 minutes.

title: tennessee boiled custard(makes 1 gallon)
directions: Mix sugar and eggs.
Add milk.
Cook and stir until it coats a silver spoon.
Let cool and add vanilla to taste.

title: round steak supreme
directions: Dice meat and remove all fat and strings. Dredge in flour. Add meat and diced onions to skillet with margarine. Cook until onions are done and meat is lightly browned. Add the can of soup and two cans of water. Cook until all is very hot. Add the shredded cheddar cheese. Mix well, until melted. Turn off heat and add sour cream.
Remove from stove and mix well.

title: easy oven
directions: Coat beef with flour, salt and pepper; toss with oil in a 3-quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 30 minutes. Cover and bake at 375° for 2 hours or until meat is tender.

title: quick chili
directions: Saute onions; add ground beef.
Add remaining ingredients. Simmer for 30 minutes, uncovered.

title: sweet maripin's episcopalian candy
directions: Boil sugar and water until soft ball forms when tested in ice water.
Add butter and remove from heat.
Stir in 2 cups of pecans and a pinch of salt.
Beat until a bit dropped on a buttered plate or waxed paper does not run.
Drop from a teaspoon.
Never substitute margarine for butter.

title: butter cookies
directions: Mix together thoroughly the butter, sugar and egg.
Stir in flavoring.
Sift together and stir in flour and baking powder. Chill dough.
Roll very thin (1/16-inch).
Cut into desired shapes. Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Press blanched almond or pecan half into top of each cookie.
If glazed cookie is desired, brush mixture of 1 egg yolk and 2 tablespoons water over top of cookies before baking.
Bake until they are delicately browned. Temperature:
425° (hot oven).
Time:
Bake 5 to 7 minutes. Amount:
Makes about 7 dozen 2-inch cookies.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: In a plastic bag, roll vanilla wafers until fine.
Roll walnuts until fine.
Mix coconut, nuts and wafers.
Set aside.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soak onion in vermouth until soft.
Mix all well.
Chill and form into ball and roll in chopped pecans after the mixture is cold.

title: tim's favorite cookies(raw apple cookies)
directions: Drop on greased sheet and bake in quick oven by teaspoonful.

title: salmon patties
directions: Mix all ingredients except vegetable oil. Shape into patties. Heat oil, 1 1/2 to 2-inches, in heavy skillet until hot.
Fry patties, turning once, 10 minutes or until lightly browned. Drain. Yields 6 patties.

title: cream cheese bars
directions: Cream butter and brown sugar; add flour and nuts to make crumb mixture.
Save 1 cup for topping.
Press the rest into an 8-inch square pan.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: potato deluxe
directions: Mix
all ingredients, except onion rings.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Last 10 minutes, top with onion rings.

title: blackberry cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs and beat well.
Add flour and spices which have been sifted together alternately with milk. Fold in berries and nuts gently.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl and mix well.
You can use cayenne pepper instead of the jalapeno peppers (use to your desired taste).

title: caramel cake
directions: Cream butter, Crisco and sugar together.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.	Add flour alternately with milk.
Mix	well.
Add
flavoring and coloring; mix well. Bake in three cake pans at 300° for about 30 minutes.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Proceed in the same way as making a cake.
Reserve enough flour to sprinkle over the berries.
Fold in berries last.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: brown bread
directions: Bring to a boil only the water, raisins and baking soda, then cool.
When cool, add the sugar, egg, flour, vanilla and nuts. Spray pan lightly.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour or until done.

title: sarah salad
directions: Alternate 3 layers of greens in bowl.
Dot each layer with 2 tablespoons mayonnaise, 1/3 cup onions, peas and cheese.
Sprinkle 1 teaspoon sugar, salt and pepper.
Top with bacon.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours or overnight before mixing.
Serves 8.

title: rhubarb pie deluxe
directions: Mix ingredients and cook slowly until like jelly.
Pour into a baked pie shell and cover with meringue and brown.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream butter until fluffy.
Add sugar gradually.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Blend in remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour 25 minutes.

title: sandies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add water and vanilla.
Mix well and add flour and pecans.
Chill 3 to 4 hours.
Shape into balls. Bake at 325° for about 20 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: baked cinnamon doughnuts
directions: In a mixing bowl, dissolve yeast in water. Add milk and butter. Stir for 1 minute. Add eggs, 1/4 cup sugar, nutmeg, salt and 2 cups flour. Beat on low speed until smooth. Stir in enough remaining flour to form a soft dough. Cover and let rise in a warm place until doubled, about 1 hour. Punch dough down. Turn onto a floured surface. Roll out to 1/2-inch thickness. Cut with a 2 3/4-inch doughnut cutter. Place 1-inch apart on greased baking sheet. Cover and let rise in a warm place until doubled, about 30 minutes. Bake at 450° for 7 to 8 minutes or until lightly browned. Brush with butter.

title: spicy beef and vegetable stir-fry(weight watchers recipe)
directions: In a small bowl, combine the beef broth, soy sauce, cornstarch and mustard; stir until the cornstarch is dissolved.
Set aside. Cut the broccoli into bite size pieces.
In a nonstick wok or large nonstick skillet, warm the oil over medium-high heat until hot but not smoking.
Add the broccoli, cauliflower, onion and garlic; stir-fry until the vegetables are crisp-tender and the onion begins to brown, 4 to 5 minutes.

title: souffle sandwiches
directions: Place 8 buttered slices of bread in bottom of well-greased baking dish.
Top each with slice of boiled ham and cheese.
Put remaining buttered bread on top.
Beat eggs and milk and seasoning. Pour over top of sandwiches.
Refrigerate overnight.
Remove from refrigerator 1/2 hour before baking.
Have 1 cup crushed corn flakes and mix with 1/2 cup melted butter.
Sprinkle over top before baking.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 8.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: In 1 1/2-quart microwave-safe bowl stir together sugar and syrup.
Microwave on High 4 minutes.
Stir in peanuts.
Microwave on High 4 minutes until light brown.
Add butter and vanilla, mixing well.
Microwave on High 2 minutes more.
Peanuts will be lightly browned and syrup very hot. Add baking soda and gently stir until light and foamy.
Pour mixture onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Cool 1 to 1 1/2 hours. Break into pieces and store in airtight container.
Makes about 1 pound.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Use hand mixer to blend. Pour into ice cream freezer; freeze.

title: orange cake
directions: Mix filling; cook until thick.
Spread between layers and over cake.

title: deviled eggs(for 6 eggs)
directions: Mash yolks with remaining ingredients.
Refill egg whites; put dash of paprika over egg and top with slice of olive.

title: rena's crock-pot
directions: Brown beef and onion and put in crock-pot with remaining ingredients.
Stir to blend.
Cook on either low for 5 to 6 hours or medium for 3 to 4 hours or until flavors are blended together.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients well and drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 325° for 10 minutes or until lightly browned. May add chips, coconut, nuts or candied fruit.
May also be iced or sprinkled with powdered sugar.

title: curry chicken casserole
directions: Arrange in 3-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 10 to 12 generously.

title: cheese cake
directions: Butter a 9-inch spring-form pan and dust with graham cracker crumbs, coat all sides.

title: homestyle chicken noodle soup
directions: Boil chicken breasts until cooked.
Cube them into bit sized pieces.
Fill soup pot 3/4 full with water and remaining chicken stock.
Add chicken bouillon, salt and pepper to taste.
Boil and add several cups (1 1/2 to 2) carrots.
Cook until about half cooked.
Add 3/4 package R-F brand, Kluski noodles (I always use these because they taste homemade.)
Cook until tender.

title: corinne's cherry delights
directions: Cook and boil apples, sugar, water or liquor, raisins or dates, oleo, cinnamon, cloves and nutmeg for 5 minutes.
Sift flour, baking soda and salt.
Add to apple mixture along with nuts.
Dough will be firm.

title: crab casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Put crabmeat in a mixing bowl.
Set aside.
In a small bowl, place eggs, mayonnaise, dry mustard, Old Bay seasoning and parsley.
Mix well.
Scatter bread on top of crabmeat.
Pour egg mixture over top.
Gently toss ingredients together.
Lightly grease a casserole or a deep dish pie plate. Add mixture.
Bake about 25 to 30 minutes, until golden brown.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix milk, sugar, vinegar, mayonnaise, salt and celery seed. Pour over macaroni, onion, carrots and
pepper. Will keep in refrigerator for 1 week and can be frozen.

title: soft molasses cookies
directions: Combine sugar and melted shortening in mixing bowl; mix well. Add molasses and vanilla.
Mix egg in mixture.
Have ready the flour, mixed and sifted with salt, cream of tartar and spices. Dissolve the soda in hot water; add to molasses mixture.
Mix well.
Add sifted ingredients all at once.
Stir to thoroughly mix.
Cover the bowl; refrigerate overnight or longer to make rolling easy.
When ready to bake on lightly greased cookie sheet, roll a portion of the dough and cut with a 3 or 3 1/2-inch cookie cutter.
Place 2 inches apart.
Bake at 400° for about 9 to 10 minutes.
Remove immediately when baked.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Grease and flour casserole dish. Place a layer of potatoes, then a layer of onions.
Salt and pepper and sprinkle flour over potatoes and onions.
Next place a layer of cheese over potatoes and onions.
Put 4 or 5 dabs of butter on cheese.
Continue layering until finishing potatoes and onions.
When finished, pour milk over casserole and bake 1 hour and 15 minutes or until thickened and done to fork touch.

title: zucchini vegetable medley
directions: Saute until vegetables are crisp tender in a little olive oil.
As the vegetables begin to saute; add all other ingredients.

title: red cabbage - polish style *
directions: Saute chopped onion until golden and add shredded cabbage (cabbage should be of rather coarse consistency, so food processor would spoil the character of the dish).
Add water as necessary so cabbage does not stick; add brown sugar and vinegar to taste, then add chopped apple.
This dish can be stored, frozen and reheated.

title: zucchini corn bread
directions: Mix all the ingredients and pour into a greased 6 x 10-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: orange rolls
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in bowl, stirring until butter melts.
Add eggs; mix well.
Stir in yeast and 1/4 cup orange juice.
Beat in flour gradually.
Chill, covered, overnight. Divide into 4 portions.
Roll each into rectangle on floured surface.
Cut into 6 strips; tie in bowknot.
Place on greased baking sheet.
Let rise for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Glaze warm rolls with mixture of confectioners sugar and 2 tablespoons orange juice.
Yields 24 servings.

title: diet vegetable soup
directions: Mix all ingredients in a big pot; simmer for 30 minutes.
Good anytime!

title: sausage swirls
directions: In medium bowl, combine flour, cornmeal, sugar, baking powder and salt; blend in vegetable oil until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Add milk, stirring until well blended.
Turn dough out onto a lightly floured surface; knead lightly 3 or 4 times.
Roll dough into an 18 x 10-inch rectangle.
Spread sausage (at room temperature) over dough, leaving a 1/2-inch margin on all sides. Carefully roll dough from long end, jellyroll fashion.
Pinch seam and ends to seal.
Cover; chill at least 1 hour.
Slice dough into 1/4-inch slices.
Arrange 1-inch apart on baking sheets.
Bake in preheated 350° gas oven for 20 minutes or until lightly browned. Yield:
6 dozen.

title: orange delight salad
directions: Combine topping, sour cream and jello.
Drain pineapple and oranges; fold into sour cream mixture.
After combining all ingredients, cover and chill in refrigerator until firm.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: wacky cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Mix together.
Make 3 holes in mixture. Fill one with oil, one with vanilla and one with vinegar.
Pour water over all and mix well with a fork.
Bake at 350° until cake tests done, about 30 minutes.

title: polynesian beef
directions: Cover beef with onion rings in shallow pan, pour mixture of pineapple juice, soy sauce, salt and ginger over top.
Let stand 1 hour to season, turning once.
Place beef and onion in a deep electric stove or Dutch oven; simmer for 1 to 2 hours or until beef is tender when pierced with fork.
Reduce heat, add celery and carrots; simmer for 10 minutes.
Place mushrooms on top for 5 minutes, remove to heated serving platter.
Stir cornstarch to paste in water, stir into juices in pan, cook, stirring until gravy thickens and boil 3 minutes.
Season with additional soy sauce, if desired.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: saucy green vegetables
directions: Drain beans and peas.
Add cream, mayonnaise and seasonings and stir together.
Place in a large, greased casserole and top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: salmon spread
directions: Mix all together and chill. Serve with crackers.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix all of the
ingredients
and
pour in a long, Pyrex dish. Congeal overnight.

title: potato-egg casserole
directions: Cut potatoes in half; place in large saucepan with bouillon cubes and 1 inch cold water. Bring to a boil; cover, reduce heat and simmer 20 to 25 minutes or until tender. Drain reserving liquid. Remove potato skins and slice 1/4 inch thick. Arrange potatoes in 8 x 12-inch shallow baking dish. Saute bacon until crisp; discard all but 1/3 cup bacon fat. Saute onions until soft in bacon fat. Arrange over potatoes and add sliced eggs. Blend flour into remaining fat. Stir over medium heat 2 minutes. Add enough milk to reserved potato liquid to make 2 1/2 cups.
Add to mixture; cook, stirring constantly, until sauce thickens. Add seasonings and pour over potatoes. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump pineapple and cherry filling into 9 x 13-inch baker. Sprinkle dry cake mix over top evenly.
Dab butter pieces over the top.
Bake about 30 minutes at 350°.
Best when served hot with a little ice cream.

title: favorite hot chocolate
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa and salt in a large Dutch oven; mix well. Slowly stir in water; bring to a boil. Add milk; cook until thoroughly heated. Place marshmallows in individual cups, if desired; fill cups with hot chocolate.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Mix chicken, soup, salt, pepper, lemon juice, sour cream and 1 1/2 tablespoons poppy seed.
In a casserole dish, put 1/2 of the chicken mixture.
Top with 1/2 bread crumbs, 1/2 butter and 1 1/2 tablespoons poppy seed. Repeat.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: jello salad
directions: Beat together the Cool Whip and strawberry jello, then add pineapple, nuts, coconut, cherries and marshmallows; chill.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix dry pudding mix with pineapple.
Add Cool Whip and marshmallows.
Mix well and chill before serving.
(Can use lite Cool Whip.)

title: spanish rice casserole
directions: Brown hamburg, onion and pepper.
Slightly cook celery and carrots. Cook the 1 cup rice.
Mix together.
Place in 2 medium casseroles.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
The last 1/2 hour, sprinkle with cheese. Freezes well.

title: company gourmet potatoes
directions: Place all ingredients in a large bowl and mix well.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with crushed barbecue potato chips.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: christmas hard candy
directions: Mix sugar, syrup and water in saucepan.
Cover and heat to boiling.
Uncover and cook to 285°.
Add flavoring and color, if desired.
Pour into greased pan.
When hard, turn out of pan and cut into bite-size pieces.

title: asparagus with parmesan vinaigrette
directions: Cook asparagus until just tender.
Mix everything (oil, vinegar, mustard, salt and 2 tablespoons grated Parmesan cheese) together.
Put the asparagus into a baking dish, pour the vinaigrette over the asparagus. Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate.
Sprinkle with remaining 1 tablespoon Parmesan cheese and Prosciutto just before serving.

title: fried turkey
directions: Break the neck of the turkey to allow it to drain better when you take it out of the hot grease when done cooking.

title: daddy's favorite
directions: Brown hamburger. May add a little onion and/or salt and pepper if you like. Add soup, green beans and Worcestershire sauce to hamburger once it is browned. Can either use remaining ingredients to make mashed potatoes or use instant, depending on your time frame. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: java cheese pie
directions: Stir until coffee has dissolved completely and is uniform in color.
Spread evenly over pie.
Bake 10 minutes in preheated 400° oven.
Cool on rack for 20 minutes.

title: gazpacho jigger salad
directions: Mix together vegetables, seasonings, vinegar and Worcestershire in bowl.
Let stand.
Dissolve jello in hot water and add gelatin that has been dissolved in 1/4 cup cold water.
Chill until it begins to thicken.
Stir in vegetables.
Chill until firm.

title: peanut butter bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix sifted flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Mix in peanut butter with a fork until well blended.
Beat eggs slightly; add milk to eggs.
Add milk and eggs to dry ingredients; stir just enough to mix.
Pour into well-greased loaf pan.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: carolina dream frosting
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in top of a double boiler.
Beat at low speed for 30 seconds.
Bring water to a boil.
Reduce heat to low and cook, stirring constantly, until mixture is slightly thickened.
Remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients.
In a large bowl, pour egg mixture over fruit and nuts.
Mix well.
Cool completely.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Stir eggs, oil and sugar together.
Add flour and vanilla, then apples and nuts.
Mix well and place in slow oven at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Use tube pan, well-greased and floured.

title: dried beef and green onion cheese ball
directions: Let the cream cheese set out at room temperature until softened.
Chop the green onion, dried beef and corned beef real fine.
Mix the first 4 ingredients real good in a mixing bowl. Them, while you still have it in the bowl, begin adding the garlic salt or powder.
I would add about a 1/2 teaspoon and mix in real good and taste.
Then, continue adding a small amount of garlic salt or powder until you get the taste you like.
Roll into a ball and let set in refrigerator overnight for best results.
Serve with your favorite crackers.

title: country corn casserole
directions: Saute peppers, onion and mushrooms.
Mix with rice and corn. Bring flour, milk and mushroom juice to a boil.
Mix with corn mixture.
Bake in a greased casserole at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: unbaked fruit cake
directions: Cut up marshmallows and soak in cream.
Add fruit and nuts (cut in small pieces).
Add cracker crumbs.
(Use your hand and mix well).
Put on foil paper.
Shape into a loaf.
Cover outside with cracker crumbs.
Wrap well.
Keep in cool place.

title: coconut custard pie
directions: Pour milk
over
coconut and set aside.
Cream oleo and sugar and
add
eggs
and beat well.
Add milk and coconut and vanilla. Bake 30 minutes at 350° or until set.

title: pistachio pudding dessert
directions: Mix together the first 4 ingredients.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: spinach lasagna
directions: Boil the lasagna, a few at a time, in plenty of salted water with 1 teaspoon oil for 12 minutes.
Lift them out and allow to drain.
Thaw the spinach; fry it lightly in 1 1/2 tablespoons oil. Add salt, pepper and grated nutmeg; then add the Ricotta or cottage cheese.
Dry completely.
Fry the crushed garlic and chopped onion in 1 tablespoon oil.
Add the chopped tomatoes, seasoning and spice; let the sauce boil, uncovered, for 10 minutes to reduce it.
Grease the baking dish; put a thin layer of tomato sauce.
Put 3 sheets of lasagna.
On it put spinach and a little grated cheese, another layer of lasagna sheets, tomato sauce and grated cheese.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: gerken salat(cucumber salad)
directions: Peel and slice cucumbers. Mix other ingredients and pour over cucumbers and chill.

title: ice cream crepes
directions: Cook pancakes accordingly, adding vanilla and evaporated milk for thinning out batter.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Drop mixture into hot oil and flatten with a spoon.
Brown both sides until golden; drain on paper towel.
Serves 4 to 6.
Serve with meat for supper or spread with jelly and roll for a hot snack.

title: lemon mousse
directions: Whip canned milk until stiff. Slowly add sugar and then add the juice of 3 lemons.
Pour into pan lined with graham cracker crumbs.
Sprinkle crumbs on top. Cover and put in freezer.
Serve like ice cream.

title: shrimp surprise casserole
directions: De-stem and wash spinach.
Chop onions and celery.
Melt margarine; mix with lemon juice and spices.
Pour margarine mixture over vegetables in a large casserole dish.
Stir in bread crumbs, water and salt and pepper.
Mix well with shrimp. Sprinkle top with more bread crumbs.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes or so.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Beat eggs and sugar together. Add other ingredients and mix well. Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes.

title: bedford kids' saturday morning breakfast biscuits
directions: Wake up early on Saturday morning. Tiptoe through the house and quietly wake up Daddy.
Tiptoe out of the house to the car. Drive to Hardee's drive-through window. Order butter biscuits with extra jelly.
Go home.
Wake up Mom and say, "Surprise!
Breakfast is ready!"
Eat and watch T.V.
(O.J. and coffee are optional.)

title: coney island sauce
directions: Saute meat and crumble into small pieces.
Drain grease.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 1 hour.
Arrange hot dogs in buns; top with sauce.

title: ambrosia
directions: Simmer at least 45 minutes or put in crockpot (low) for 6-8 hours.
Toppings:
corn chips, sour cream, shredded lettuce, shredded cheddar cheese, chopped tomatoes.
Spoon soup into bowls; top with desired toppings.

title: barbecue baked beans
directions: Drain beans well.
Mix all ingredients together in a 2-quart baking dish.
Bake covered at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Can be baked 5 to 10 minutes in a microwave instead.

title: standing rib roast
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients and rub over roast.
Place roast with fat side up in a large roasting pan.
Insert meat thermometer.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° until roast reaches desired doneness.
Allow 23 to 25 minutes per pound for rare (140° on thermometer), 27 to 30 minutes for medium (160°) and 32 to 35 minutes for well done (170°).
Remove to serving platter and keep warm.
Let stand 15 minutes before carving.

title: sand tarts
directions: Cream butter, sugar and vanilla.
Mix in flour and pecans. Roll into little balls.
Put on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for about 20 to 25 minutes.
Take out of oven and let cool slightly.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: mormon tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: cracker spread
directions: Mix all together and roll into ball.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Serve with crackers.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Beat egg, add milk, bread crumbs and seasonings.
Add meat and mix well.
Shape into small balls and cook in microwave a few minutes, then brown quickly in little oil.
Simmer in gravy 1/2 hour.

title: freezer slaw
directions: Mix vinegar and salt in pan and bring to a boil.
Cool for 1/2 hour.
Mix all other ingredients together and pour cooled liquid over it.
Let stand 1/2 hour.
Put into containers and freeze.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Combine sugar, butter, eggs and vanilla.
Add flour and mix well.
Stir in pecans and chips.
Pour into unbaked pie crust. Bake at 350° for about 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve warm with ice cream!

title: grasshopper
directions: Combine ingredients in blender until smooth.
Top with whipped cream.
Yields 1/2 gallon.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Add mushrooms and all soups together in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix well and add 1/2 cup milk.
Mix in rice.
Place chicken pieces on top. Bake at 275° for 2 hours.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken, celery, salt, eggs, onion, relish and mayonnaise.
Mix well and refrigerate.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Cook carrots in salted water for 15 minutes and drain.
Melt butter; stir in flour and gradually add milk.
Add cheese and stir until melted.
Put 1/2 of carrots in a
1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Cover with 1/2 can of onion rings.
Repeat process, adding rest of carrots.
Pour cheese sauce over layers.
Sprinkle remaining 1/2 of onion rings on top.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: kibbet-et-roohib(monk's soup)
directions: Boil lentils and salt in water.
Cool for 30 mins. over medium heat.
Mix together cracked wheat, flour seasoning, pepper, salt and cumin.
Form wheat mixture into small balls.
Add to lentils and water.
Add crushed garlic, lemon juice and oil.
If desired, add more water.

title: kentucky pecan pie
directions: Mix well in order given.
Pour into unbaked 9-inch pie shell. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until crusty on top.

title: easy pork chops and rice
directions: Season pork chops and cook until done. Remove from skillet. Add butter and onion to same skillet and cook onion until clear. Add milk and soup and mix well. Add
Minute rice and place cooked pork chops on top. Cover and cook on low heat for about 5 minutes. Let stand another 5 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Boil chicken and remove from bone.
Place chicken in bottom of baking dish.
Top with broth, soup and vegetables (drained).
Make topping of flour, margarine and milk.
Mix thoroughly and pour over top of chicken mixture.
Bake at 350° until brown, about 1 hour.

title: pecan torte
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Add flour and keep out 1 cup.
Mix eggs, sour cream and baking soda and add to dry ingredients. Spread pecans on bottom of 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan and pour batter in and top with the 1 cup of dry ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: zucchini puffs
directions: Mix together milk, egg and zucchini.
Add dry ingredients until all wet.
Drop by tablespoon into hot crisco.

title: banana pudding
directions: Melt butter, then add flour.
Stir in 1 cup of milk at a time.
Stir until it bubbles.
Add sugar; stir well.
Remove from heat, then add vanilla.
Pour over vanilla wafers and bananas. Chill.
Put Cool Whip on for topping.

title: brunch toast
directions: Mix eggs, vanilla, cinnamon and water.
Set aside.
Chop pecans.
Zap cream cheese in microwave so it is easily spreadable.

title: zucchini and corn
directions: In a large skillet, place on grill rack.
Heat oil and saute tomatoes until mushy.
Stir in zucchini and corn kernels.
Add oregano.
Stir to blend.
Cover and simmer, stirring occasionally, until zucchini is tender.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.

title: fat-free chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray a 9-inch pan with cooking spray. In a large bowl, combine dry ingredients until well mixed.
In medium bowl, whisk egg whites, water and corn syrup.
Stir into dry ingredients until smooth.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake 30 minutes or until cake springs back when lightly touched.
Cool on wire rack 10 minutes.
Makes 16 servings at 130 calories each.

title: sauteed cabbage and carrots with ginger
directions: Heat vegetable oil in a large skillet or wok over medium heat; add the green onions, garlic, ginger and hot red pepper flakes. Saute for 3 minutes until onions start to wilt.
Add shredded cabbage and carrots.
Stir-fry for 5 minutes, tossing frequently. Cover and cook over low heat for 3 or 4 minutes until cabbage is tender.
Transfer to a serving bowl.
Serve immediately.

title: italian beef
directions: Place meat in Dutch oven or heavy saucepan.
Add celery, onion, garlic salt, salt, pepper, bay leaf and soy sauce.
Cover roast with water.
Bring to a boil; cover and simmer for 3 hours.
Cool the roast in the broth in the refrigerator overnight or several hours.
Thinly slice the roast.
Simmer the green pepper for about 5 minutes.
Place the sliced meat in a shallow pan (13 x 9-inch) in layers.
Cover the meat with the peppers.
Pour the juice over the meat; add more garlic salt and soy sauce, if desired.
Cover with foil and heat in a slow oven (300°) for about 15 to 20 minutes or until warmed through.

title: pizza appetizers
directions: Lightly brown sausage and drain well.
Add remaining ingredients, mixing until cheese is melted and all is blended. Trim crusts from bread and cut into 4 pieces.
Put a spoonful of mixture in middle of each piece of bread.
Place on cookie sheet and freeze.
Then place in plastic bag and leave in freezer.
Use as needed, heating in 350° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Mix together.
Place in casserole dish and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: jello dessert
directions: Line 9 x 9-inch pan with graham crackers.
Mix oleo, sugar, pineapple and pecans; spread over crackers.
Now add another layer of graham crackers.
Mix black cherry Jell-O as directed on package.
When this begins to set, pour over graham crackers. When set, top with Cool Whip and chopped pecans.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Mix ingredients and chill.
Slice 1/4 inch thick.
Whip in white sugar.
Bake at 350° until very crispy.

title: katie's favorite onion soup
directions: Saute onions in small amount of oil.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer.
Top with a generous amount of shredded Mozzarella and serve.

title: healthy apple-walnut muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease 12 standard size muffin pan cups or line with paper liners.
Mix together flour, baking soda, cinnamon, ginger, allspice, nutmeg and salt.
Mix together eggs, apple juice and buttermilk.
Stir flour mixture and oat bran into egg mixture until dry ingredients are just moistened.
Do not overmix.
Gently stir in chopped apples and nuts.
Spoon batter into prepared pan, filling cups two-thirds full.
Garnish each muffin with an apple slice. Bake muffins until lightly golden and tops spring back when pressed, 25 minutes.
Transfer pan to a wire rack to cool slightly.
Turn muffins out onto rack to cool completely.

title: chicken crescent squares
directions: In medium bowl, blend cream cheese and margarine until smooth. Add the next 5 ingredients.
Separate crescent dough into rectangles; press perforation to seal.
Spoon 1/2 cup meat mixture into center.
Pull corners; twist and seal.
Brush tops with melted margarine.
Sprinkle bread crumbs on top.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet.
Can be made ahead and refrigerated.
Well liked by children and adults!!

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: Add cornstarch, sugar and cocoa.
Cream in oleo.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla.
Cook until thick.
Pour in baked pie shell. Beat egg white; put on top and brown.

title: strawberry pie(club member: clint hudson)
directions: Blend together first 3 ingredients in a boiler; cook until thick. Remove from heat and stir in 1 (3 ounce) box strawberry jello. Stir in 1 pint fresh strawberries. Pour into graham cracker pie crust. Let jello cool and top with Cool Whip.

title: raspberry ice cream fruit salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add ice cream - stir until melted.
Mix bananas with pineapple so bananas do not darken and add to the jello.
Add all remaining ingredients.
Chill until set.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except the Fritos.
When ready to serve, crush Fritos and mix in salad.

title: pear honey
directions: Combine all the ingredients and cook over low heat for 20 minutes and seal.

title: gourmet potatoes au gratin
directions: Combine cheese and 1/4 cup butter in saucepan; stir over low heat until almost melted.
Remove from heat.
Blend in sour cream, seasonings and 2 green onions.
Fold in potatoes.
Turn into greased 2-quart casserole.
Dot with remaining butter and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 35 minutes.

title: granny's sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Blend in egg.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together and add to mixture.
Add vanilla. Divide dough in 2 parts.
Chill 1 to 2 hours.
Roll dough 1 part at a time to 1/8-inch thick.
Cut with cookie cutters.
Keep other part of dough chilled until ready for it.
Bake cookies at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Yield:
2 dozen.

title: marinara sauce
directions: Heat olive oil; add onion and garlic.
Do not burn.
Add tomatoes and cook slowly for about 10 minutes.
Add tomato paste and cook gently for about 25 minutes.
Add basil to taste and pinch of red pepper.
Excellent for meatless meals.

title: baked sweet potatoes
directions: Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes, until sticky.
Cover with marshmallows and brown lightly until marshmallows begin to melt.

title: easy mousaka
directions: Peel eggplants and slice 1/2-inch thick.
Brown slices quickly in skillet in 4 tablespoons butter or oleo (set aside).
Heat 4 tablespoons butter or oleo in skillet.
Saute onions until light brown.
