Add ground meat and cook 10 minutes.
Combine tomato paste with wine, parsley, cinnamon, salt and pepper.
Stir into meat. Simmer, stirring frequently, until all liquid is absorbed.
Remove from heat.

title: buttermilk coffeecake
directions: Mix flour, spices and salt and cut in the 1/2 cup Crisco with a pastry blender or fork.
Take out 1/2 cup of the mixture to be used as topping.

title: ooey gooey cake
directions: Mix and press into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: apricot muffins
directions: In bowl, pour buttermilk over high fiber bran cereal buds. In another bowl, combine flour and baking soda.
Add brown sugar, vegetable oil and egg to cereal mixture; stir into flour mixture. Spoon into 12 greased muffin cups.
Sprinkle with chopped walnuts. Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: ambassador hotel beef short ribs
directions: Sprinkle each rib with salt, pepper and rosemary to taste. Place in baking pan with celery and carrots.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Add red wine and brown gravy.
Cover with foil and bake 1 1/2 hours or until meat is tender when fork is inserted.

title: grandmother's cranberry bread
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, baking soda, sugar and salt into large bowl.
Cut butter or margarine into mixture until crumbly. Add orange peel, orange juice and egg all at once.
Fold raisins and cranberries into mixture.
Pour into 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until toothpick stuck into center comes out clean.
Remove from pan.
Cool on wire rack.

title: tomato bisque
directions: Put tomatoes in saucepan, juice too.
Chop tomatoes into small pieces.
Add the butter, sugar, pepper, soda and salt; bring to a boil.
Boil about 5 minutes.
Add milk and bring again to a boil. Serve as is, without straining.
Don't ask me why it doesn't curdle, but it doesn't.
Serves 6.

title: praline sweet potato pie
directions: Combine white and brown sugar and spices.
Blend in eggs and sweet potatoes.
Stir in hot milk.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: Skin and cut up chicken.
Put in pot; cover with water and boil for 2 hours.
Debone chicken.
Saute celery, carrots and onions.
Pour into chicken pot.
Bring to boil and add noodles. Add salt, pepper and herbs to taste.

title: golden corn bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients into bowl.
Add egg, milk and shortening. Mix until smooth. Pour into greased skillet. Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Roll in balls and bake on large cookie sheet at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: zucchini nut muffins
directions: Sift flour and dry ingredients. Combine sugar and eggs; beat 2 minutes. Gradually add oil, beating 2 to 3 minutes. Add zucchini and vanilla and blend well.
Stir in nuts and raisins.

Fold in dry ingredients just until batter is slightly moistened. Spoon into muffin tins. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Let stand 10 minutes to cool and turn out of muffin tins onto rack. Makes 28 muffins.

title: brown and serve rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in cup of warm water.
Mix dry ingredients; add oil and yeast mixture.
Add water until stiff batter.
Let rise until double in size, about 30 minutes.
Knead and pinch off in rolls; let rise again.
Prebake for 30 minutes at 250° for brown and serve rolls, then bake at 400° for 5 minutes.
Serves 30.

title: lime cottage cheese salad
directions: Dissolve jello with water and vinegar.
Cool.
Add pineapple and juice. When this starts to thicken, fold in cottage cheese and sprinkle in a dash of salt.
Beat in mayonnaise; pour in mold.

title: easy banana pudding
directions: Cook pudding according to package directions.
When cool, layer some vanilla wafers in bottom of 3-quart casserole dish. Slice half the bananas over this.
Pour half the pudding over this.
Repeat layers and top with a meringue.

title: herbed pork chops
directions: Mix rosemary, sage, garlic, salt and pepper in small bowl. Rub mixture over pork chops.
Place chops in large, greased skillet.
Add water and cover.
Simmer until all water has evaporated, about 45 minutes.
Remove cover and brown chops in their own fat.
Add wine and cook about one minute, turning chops occasionally.
Allow to cook until wine is almost evaporated.

title: fat free fruit salad
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine pineapple, strawberries, grapes and marshmallows.

title: quick baked potatoes
directions: Cut the potatoes in half lengthwise.
Brush each cut half with melted butter.
Sprinkle with paprika, salt and cheese.
Place cut side down on oiled cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until potato is fork-tender.

title: beef casserole
directions: Brown beef; drain well. Add all other ingredients to meat and mix well. Pour into casserole dish and bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: homemade french dressing
directions: Put all ingredients in blender or large covered jar and blend until smooth.
Makes about 1 quart of dressing.

title: instant hot cocoa mix
directions: Mix well.
Store in airtight container.
To serve, use 1/3 to 1/2 cup mix to 1 cup water.

title: frosted shortbread squares
directions: Mix the sifted flour with brown sugar.
Cut in (with a pastry blender or fork) margarine to this mixture until it resembles coarse meal.
Press firmly in ungreased jelly roll pan (10 x 15 x 1-inch).
Bake at 325° for about 25 minutes.
While still hot, spread on the chocolate chips and sprinkle with nuts.
Cut while warm.
May be refrigerated also.

title: classic potato salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine the sour cream, celery, black pepper, parsley, dill, garlic, mayonnaise and mustard.
Add the potatoes and toss gently to coat.
Top the salad with bacon, egg slices and scallions.
Cover and refrigerate at least 30 minutes.
Servings: 8.

title: veal cordon bleu
directions: Cut ham into strips.
Cut veal into 4 pieces.
With a meat mallet, pound each veal piece to 1/8-inch thickness.
Place some ham and cheese in center of each veal piece.
Fold in sides, then overlap ends, forming bundles.
Secure with wooden picks.
Combine bread crumbs, parsley and 1/8 teaspoon pepper.
Roll meat bundles in flour, egg, then crumb mixture.

title: half-hour raised doughnuts
directions: Mix warm water, sugar and yeast.
Let stand until foamy.
Add egg, salt, shortening and flour.
Roll out on floured board.
Cut and let rise on lightly greased wax paper for 30 minutes.
Fry until golden.
Yields 24 doughnuts.

title: potato cabbage soup
directions: Quarter cabbage.
Peel potatoes and cut in halves.
Place in soup kettle with 5 cups water.
Bring to boil and simmer for 25 to 30 minutes until vegetables are tender.
Melt butter in saucepan. Add onions and continue to cook until onions are brown.
Remove from stove and add 1/2 cup cold water and flour.
Bring to boil and stir until smooth.
Add vinegar and then add to brown sauce. Blend into potatoes and cabbage.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Store in one pint jars to use for gifts.
Put directions on each jar.
Use 1/3 cup mix to 1 cup boiling water.

title: broiled tomatoes with dill sauce
directions: Core and cut tomatoes crosswise.
Place in broiling pan, cut side up.
Sprinkle with seasoned salt and dot with butter.
Set aside.

title: clam chowder
directions: Melt butter; add onion and grated carrot (optional) and cook until tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients and heat until good and hot.
Do not boil.
Stir to prevent scorching and sticking.

title: monkey bread
directions: Tear biscuits into little pieces; roll into little balls; shake in bag of sugar and cinnamon.
Mix butter, sugar, water and syrup together.
Pour enough syrup mixture in bottom of pan to cover; put cinnamon-covered biscuits in pan.
Pour over the rest of the syrup mixture and add nuts.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes.

title: glorified macaroni
directions: Combine macaroni, mayonnaise, soup, mushrooms and juice, pepper, onions, pimento and cheese.
Pour into large casserole dish.
Top with cracker crumbs and melted butter.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Melt cheese in double boiler; mix well with Bisquick and sausage.
Roll in small balls.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 400°. Serve hot.
Can easily be frozen.
Makes approximately 80 balls.

title: pride of iowa cookies
directions: Mix ingredients all together (in order listed) and bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: bacon spaghetti
directions: As the spaghetti boils, cut the bacon into small pieces and chop the onion. Fry until bacon is crisp and the onion translucent.
Drain the fat (as much as possible), then add the tomato sauce and tomatoes. Gradually add as much of the juice from the stewed tomatoes to get the desired thickness.
Add the cooked spaghetti and heat until the flavors are blended.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Cook chicken in a
4-quart
Dutch
oven
with
salt and water for
2 to 2 1/2 hours if using stewing hen or for 40 to 50 minutes if using fryer or broiler chicken.
Remove chicken from broth and let cool.
Remove meat from bones and cut into chunks. Skim
fat from broth.
Set aside 3/4 cup of broth for dumplings and also set aside 5 cups of broth for soup.

title: peanut butter play dough
directions: Mix equal parts of peanut butter and dry milk.
Add honey, optional.
Knead and mix until a good dough-like consistency. Model and experiment as any play dough.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix cake as directed, but set aside 1 cup of batter.
Pour remainder of batter into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake as directed.
When done, gently punch holes in cake with a fork.

title: mock wine punch
directions: Serve in punch bowl or pitcher with ice and sliced oranges.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add strawberries and undrained pineapple; mix well.
Pour 1/2 into dish; cool until congealed. Mix cream cheese or sour cream and pecans.
Spread over jello; add remaining strawberry mixture and chill until set.

title: candy cake
directions: Mix together.
Spray a 10 x 14-inch pan with Pam.
Pour into pan and bake at 350° for approximately 17 minutes.
Cool and cut. Very chewy.

title: gumbo
directions: Fry okra in oil until slime is out and browned. Keep mixing until browned. Put in a bowl and set aside. Fry onions and garlic until light brown in a pot. Add chicken broth and 2 cans water. Add tomato sauce and okra in and boil 1/2 hour. Add peeled shrimp and cook for 1 hour on low. Add extra seasoning for taste.

title: stromboli
directions: Mix together water, salt, yeast and vegetable oil.
Add 2 cups flour slowly.
Mix with a fork until flour is moist.
Add remaining 2 cups flour.
Mix with hands.
Make dough into 3 balls. Knead a little.
Lightly grease balls with shortening.
Let lay 15 minutes.
Roll out each ball on a lightly floured surface.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Combine green beans, corn, soup, sour cream, onions and cheese. Mix well and pour into a 9 x 12-inch casserole dish. Crumble crackers on top of casserole.
Sprinkle almonds on top of crackers.
Melt margarine and pour this on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook spinach; squeeze dry.
Add all ingredients.
Form into balls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Freezes well after baking.
Yields 3 1/2 dozen.

title: honey banana cake
directions: Mix wet ingredients. Sift dry ingredients.
Add together; pour into greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: belgian waffles
directions: Preheat Belgian waffle maker.
Put all ingredients except egg whites in a large mixer bowl.
Beat on low until moistened. Increase to medium, mix until smooth.

title: breakfast sausage bread
directions: Allow dough to rise until nearly doubled.
Meanwhile, in a skillet over medium heat, cook and crumble sausage.
Add mushrooms and onions.
Cook and stir until sausage is browned and vegetables are tender; drain.
Cool.
Beat 1 egg; set aside.
To sausage mixture, add 2 eggs, cheese and seasonings; mix well.
Roll each loaf of dough into a 15 in.x12 in. rectangle.
Spread half the sausage mixture on each loaf to within 1 inch of edge.
Roll jelly-roll style, starting at narrow end; seal edges.
Place on a greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350 degrees for 25 minutes; brush with beaten egg. Bake 5-10 minutes more or until golden brown. Serve warm.
Serves 6 to 12.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Hint:
Put 1 teaspoon vinegar in regular milk to make sour.

title: pumpkin squares
directions: Mix together the first 3 ingredients.
Press in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix the rest of the ingredients except for the last 4 ingredients
and pour over crust.
Take 1 cup cake mix, sugar, cinnamon and margarine and mix.
Sprinkle over pumpkin mix. Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes. Insert knife to test if done.

title: apricot nectar cake
directions: To cake mix, add egg yolks, oil, nectar and extract.
Mix. Beat whites and fold into cake mix.
Bake in a tube pan for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: crab meat casserole
directions: Mix above ingredients (crab and eggs last), except buttered croutons or bread crumbs.
Put in casserole.
Top with the buttered croutons or buttered bread cubes.
Bake for 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: rice-broccoli casserole
directions: Sprinkle over rice-broccoli mixture.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: hamburger-vegetable soup
directions: In saucepan over high heat, heat 5 to 6 cups water to boiling. Add bouillon cubes and stir until dissolved.
Add vegetables and meat which has been browned in skillet until almost done.
Simmer for 20 minutes until all is done.

title: rhoda's tomato casserole
directions: Mix well and bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.

title: hamburger steaks
directions: Mix together ground beef and 1/2 onion.
Make into patties. Brown in a skillet on both sides until about 1/2 done.
Pour grease off.
Add butter, other half of onion, can of mushrooms and green pepper.
Cover and simmer over low heat for 30 minutes. Every 10 minutes, baste with the sauce the patties are simmering in.

title: macaroni-chicken salad
directions: Prepare macaroni according to package directions; drain.
In medium bowl combine macaroni, oil and vinegar; toss to coat.
Add remaining ingredients; toss gently to mix.
Cover; chill thoroughly.
Stir gently before serving.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: zoom koom(welcome water)
directions: Mix all together; pour through cheesecloth to strain.
Stir again before serving in a gourd.
If you like you can add a few flies, knats or mosquitoes to be realistic.

title: silky cocoa creme
directions: In small bowl, sprinkle gelatin over water; allow to stand 2 minutes to soften.
In medium saucepan, stir together sugar and cocoa.
Stir in milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture is very hot.
Add gelatin mixture, stirring until gelatin is dissolved.
Pour into medium bowl.
Refrigerate until mixture is chilled (do not allow to gel).
In blender container or food processor bowl, beat Ricotta cheese and vanilla until smooth. Stir into whipped topping.
Gradually fold into cocoa mixture. Pour into 2-cup mold and chill until set.
Unmold and serve with strawberries.

title: mint frosted brownies
directions: Thoroughly cream butter, sugar and vanilla; add eggs and beat well.
Blend in chocolate.
Stir in flour and nuts.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan in a slow oven (325°) 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool.
Frost with Mint Frosting.
Makes 32 (2-inch) squares.

title: coke punch
directions: Mix all juices, sugar and water.
Stir until sugar is melted. Fill glasses with ice.
Fill 2/3 full of juice mixture and finish with Coke.

title: ice cream pie
directions: In top of double boiler, dissolve gelatine in cold milk.
Cook until hot.
Cream the egg yolks, sugar and salt.
Gradually add to hot milk and cook until thick, 10 to 15 minutes. Cool. Whip the cream.
Beat egg whites and fold into cooled, cooked mixture. Pour into 2 baked graham cracker crusts.
Grate chocolate on top.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Cook chicken with seasonings until tender.
Add chicken soup to chicken broth.
Beat egg; add water and Crisco.
Mix and add flour and salt.
Divide into 2 parts; roll dough as thin as possible and cut into squares.
Coat well with flour.
Drop, one at a time, in rapidly boiling broth.
Sprinkle black pepper along as the dumplings are dropped.
Cook, covered for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: baked salmon croquettes
directions: Melt butter over low heat and saute onion until tender. Add flour and cook, stirring constantly, about 3 minutes. Gradually stir in milk and cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened. Add seasonings. Remove from heat and add salmon, lemon juice and 1/2 cup corn flake crumbs. Combine well and chill until firm. Shape and roll in corn flakes. Bake on lightly greased cookie sheet 30 minutes at 375°.

title: creamed tacos
directions: Brown beef and drain off excess fat. Add chili, 1/2 of the cheese, tomatoes, beans and cream. Cook for 45 minutes on low heat, stirring often to prevent scorching. Serve over Fritos, topped with chopped tomatoes, lettuce and remaining cheese. Makes a fair amount. It's great and serves several.

title: homemade biscuits
directions: Mix lard and flour well, then add buttermilk; mix well until nonsticky.
Grease 8-inch biscuit pan, then roll out dough and cut. Makes 10 biscuits.

title: hot rice
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a casserole dish.
Bake 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Prepare one large or two 9 x 13-inch pans with Pam.
Spread a thin coat of enchilada sauce in pans.
Use remainder in the chicken.
Combine remaining ingredients and spread about 1/3 cup mixture on each tortilla shell.
Roll up and place in a baking dish.
Sour cream and Longhorn or Cheddar cheese (grated) is spread over the top and baked at 350° for about 25 minutes. Jalapenos and picante sauce may be added, if desired, or may be added when serving.
Makes 12 servings.

title: chess pie bars
directions: Combine cake
mix, butter and 1 egg.
Press into bottom of a 13
x 9-inch cake pan.
Combine sugar, cream cheese and 3 eggs. Pour over first mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: spice dip
directions: Mix sugar with spices.
Fold into whipped topping.
Garnish with additional cinnamon, if desired.
Store in refrigerator. Makes 1 2/3 cups.

title: garden soup
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large Dutch oven.
Cover and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 45 minutes to 1 hour. Serve hot.
Yields 10 servings at 1 cup each.
Calories:
84. Exchanges:
1 starch.

title: holiday cranberry slush
directions: Place jellied cranberry sauce in large mixer bowl; beat until smooth. Add cranberry apple juice concentrate, partially thawed lemonade concentrate and spices.

title: tuna cakes
directions: In medium bowl, combine all ingredients, except margarine. Shape into 6 equal patties.
In a 10-inch nonstick skillet, heat margarine until bubbly and hot.
Add patties; cook over medium heat, turning once until browned on both sides.

title: macaroni and ham scallop
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons margarine.
Saute onions.
Add flour, salt, mustard, paprika and pepper.
Slowly stir in milk.
Cook 15 to 20 minutes over medium heat until thick.
Mix with mac and ham.
Put in casserole, top with cheese and dot with margarine.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: rosemary potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350.
Peel a decorative strip around the middle of each potato, set aside.
In a large skillet melt the butter over medium heat.
Add the onions, sprinkle with brown sugar and saute until the onions are lightly caramelized.

title: barbecue meat balls
directions: Mix all the above ingredients together; shape into balls. Place in
9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Drain grease.
Cover with sauce and bake for 30 minutes.
(Cover with foil while baking during last stage if desire lots of sauce).

title: bran muffins
directions: Sift salt, soda and flour together. Add bran, mixing thoroughly. Stir in molasses, egg and milk.
Beat well.
Pour into greased muffin tins and bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: scotch crispies
directions: Melt chips and peanut butter over water or in microwave until smooth.
Put into large bowl and add rice cereal.
Mix well then press into aluminum foil lined 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Chill until firm (1 hour).

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: Mix 1 cup Crisco and 1/2 cup flour.
Store in airtight container and keep on hand to use when greasing and flouring cake pans.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Bring first 6 ingredients to a boil.
Let boil for 5 minutes; must stir at all times!
Use fairly large saucepan or it will cook over.
Pour boiling liquid into large bowl and add peanut butter and Marshmallow Creme.
Mix together with spoon; mixture stiffens quickly.
Dump into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill then cut into 40 squares.

title: cornbread casserole
directions: Mix all these ingredients and bake in large cornbread pan. Same as you would to make cornbread. Bread will be a little gummy when done. While bread is cooking prepare mixture and topping.

title: farrell pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops in Crisco.
Drain 1/2 of liquid from canned peas.
Mix together tomato soup, peas and remaining pea liquid. Pour over pork chops.
Simmer 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Serve with rice or mashed potatoes.

title: john's salsa
directions: Chop vegetables and simmer with other ingredients for 15 minutes or until desired thickness.
Pour into 6 clean, hot, half pint or pint jars, leaving 1/2-inch headspace.
Process in boiling water bath for 20 minutes.
Makes roughly 12 half pints or 6 pints.

title: potato salad
directions: Combine potatoes, eggs, pickles, celery, onion and pimentos. Add remaining ingredients, except paprika; mix well.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Serves 8.

title: party punch
directions: Freeze cherries on a plate or tray.
Mix all the ingredients and add frozen cherries last.

title: peanut butter streusel pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and milk together. Add egg yolks and vanilla. Cook over low heat until it thickens. Then mix together; mix until mealy the peanut butter and confectioners sugar. Put all but a little of this dry mixture into a cooked pie crust. Save a little to sprinkle on top. Put in cooked pie filling and top with meringue. Sprinkle rest of peanut butter mixture on top.

title: creamy low calorie rice pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients in medium saucepan.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Pour into 1 quart casserole or individual dessert dishes.
Place plastic wrap directly on surface of hot pudding.
Chill 30 minutes; remove plastic wrap.
Sprinkle with additional cinnamon, if desired. Makes 8 servings.

title: no bake oatmeal bars
directions: Combine margarine, sugar, cocoa and milk.
Boil 1 minute. Remove from heat and add oats, peanut butter and vanilla.
Pat into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: tangy ham with rice salad
directions: In 10-inch skillet over medium heat, cook onion in hot salad oil until tender, about 10 minutes, stirring frequently.
Stir in rice, water, catsup, bouillon and thyme; heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low, cover and simmer 25 minutes or until all liquid is absorbed and rice is tender.
Remove skillet from heat.
With fork, stir ham, green pepper and vinegar into rice mixture.
Cover and refrigerate until well chilled.

title: cabbage slaw
directions: Grate cabbage in food processor until fine.
Add remainder of ingredients.
Refrigerate.

title: scrumptious chocolate layer bars
directions: Combine chocolate chips, cream cheese and evaporated milk in saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until chips are melted and mixture is smooth.
Remove from heat.
Stir in walnuts and 1/2 teaspoon almond extract.
Set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients in large mixer bowl; blend well with mixer until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix and beat vanilla pudding and milk until thick. Add Eagle Brand, lemon juice and then Cool Whip. Alternate layers of vanilla wafers, bananas and pudding. Top with Cool Whip. Garnish with crushed vanilla wafers.

title: best chocolate cake
directions: Coat nuts and chips with 1 tablespoon cake mix; set aside. Combine mix, eggs, oil, water, vanilla, pudding mix and sour cream and blend 3 minutes in large bowl of automatic mixer at medium speed.
Fold in coated chips, nuts and raspberries.
Turn into well-greased and floured tube or Bundt pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until knife inserted in center of pan comes out clean. Cool for 30 minutes and turn out on cake rack to glaze.

title: holiday morning french toast
directions: Combine brown sugar, butter and 1 teaspoon cinnamon in a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.	Add apples and cranberries.
Toss to coat well. Spread mixture out evenly and arrange bread slices on top.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Grease and flour tube cake pan. Preheat oven to 325°. Cream butter; add sugar gradually, beating constantly. Add 2 eggs, 1 at a time, beating well. Add sour cream; beat well. Add 4 eggs, 1 at a time, beating well after each addition. Sift together flour, soda and salt; add to sour cream mixture. Beat well, scraping sides often. Add flavorings. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: baked potatoes in cream(serves 6)
directions: Peel potatoes and place in cold water.	Preheat oven to 300°. Mince
garlic.
Butter casserole.
Dry and thinly slice 1 potato at	a
time.
Place a layer of potatoes in casserole. Sprinkle with
garlic,
salt and plenty of pepper.
Pour cream over to just
about cover.	Repeat procedure.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours. Sprinkle with cheese and bake for 30 minutes more.

title: meat loaf
directions: If pork is not used, a little butter is good. Chopped green pepper, celery and tomatoes may be added in small portions, if desired.
Bake 1 hour or perhaps a little more.
Enjoy the Meat Loaf.

title: baked chicken wings
directions: Mix all except chicken.
Add wings, so all pieces are covered. Marinate overnight or all day in refrigerator.
Place on single layer on cookie sheet covered with foil.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°. Baste after first 30 minutes with marinade (discard remaining). Wings may be frozen and reheated.

title: chili cheese dogs
directions: Fill hot frankfurters with corn chips and cheese cubes.
Broil until cheese spread melts.
Top with hot chili; serve immediately.

title: beef tortillas
directions: Brown ground beef with spices; drain and set aside.
Skim fat off canned chili and warm remainder in saucepan with the water. Spray 2-quart casserole with Pam.
Place small amount of warmed chili in bottom.
Cover with 1 layer of torn tortillas.
Top with layer of chili, then beef, then onion, then cheese.
Repeat layers.
Cover and bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: vanilla sauce
directions: To serve hot on plain cake squares, mix well the cornstarch, sugar and salt.
Add boiling water and butter; cook until thick, stirring all the time.
Add vinegar and vanilla. Stir well and serve over cake.

title: fritos chili pie
directions: Cook for 5 hours in a Brown-in-Bag at 300°.
Then, open it up and cook for one more hour.
Let it set for 20 minutes.

title: easy rolls in muffin pans
directions: Mix in order given.
Stir well.
Fill muffin pans about 1/2 full.
Bake at 400° until brown, approximately 20 minutes.

title: *mexican fried rice
directions: In hot bacon drippings, pour the rice and cook over medium heat until light brown.
Add onion and green pepper; cook for a few minutes longer.
Add the tomato.
Pour in the stock and bring to a boil.
Lower heat and simmer until liquid is absorbed and rice is tender, about 25 to 50 minutes.

title: chicken supreme casserole
directions: Cook rice according to directions on package.
Add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Put in casserole; cover with almonds.
Bake at least 1 hour at 350° or until bubbly.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, soda, salt and cocoa, then add mayo, milk and vanilla.
Blend until smooth.
Bake for 25 minutes, or until done, at 375°.

title: flour tortillas
directions: Mix flour, salt and baking powder.
Cut in shortening.
Add enough warm water to make a soft dough.
Knead until smooth.
Roll out into thin round circles.
Cook on griddle (no grease) about 1 minute on each side, just until very lightly brown in spots.

title: rice and chicken
directions: In a well-greased pan (9 x 13-inch), measure 1 1/2 cups of raw rice; mix in the soups.
Spread over the bottom of pan.
Salt chicken thighs and legs and place on top of rice.
Sprinkle the dry onion soup mix over chicken pieces.
Wrap securely and tightly with foil.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.
Do not open until ready to serve.

title: french dressing
directions: Put all in blender and mix well.
It will not separate.

title: stewed tomatoes (mom's)
directions: Open cans of tomatoes and drain juice.
Take tomatoes and squash with your hands to get more juice out.
Saute onions in large frying pan then add tomatoes, salt and pepper and sugar; mix well.
Tear pieces of bread and add to tomato mix.
Stir well. Cook on simmer for several hours and stir often.
Serve piping hot.

title: sand tarts
directions: Cream softened butter and sugar.
Add eggs and beat until well blended.
Add flour and soda.
Use a little more flour, if needed. Roll out onto floured surface and cut with cookie cutters.

title: cranberry-almond punch
directions: With fork, crush cranberry sauce. Beat until smooth with hand beater. Beat in water, orange juice, lemon juice and almond extract. Chill. At serving time, stir in ginger ale. Garnish each serving with lemon slices and cranberries. Serves 4.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix sugar and shortening.
Stir in eggs, water and pumpkin. Add remaining ingredients.
Using a greased bread pan, bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cinnamon ornaments
directions: Mix and knead. Roll out and cut with cookie cutters. Punch hole in top (for ribbon to hang ornament).
Let dry on wax paper for a few hours. Turn over and continue to dry for 2 days.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix sugar, shortening and eggs; add mashed bananas.
Add dry ingredients and nuts.
Bake 45 minutes at 350° or until done.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Beat until smooth with rotary beater. Heat oil to 360°.
Place 1/2 cup batter in a funnel. Hold finger under spout.
Release over oil moving different directions until funnel is empty. Cook until brown, then turn and brown.
Drain on paper towels and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown meat in skillet.
Add vegetables and cook until tender. Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Cover and simmer slowly for 20 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: salmon snack
directions: Drain salmon.
Remove dark skin and bones.
Combine all ingredients except almonds and parsley.
Chill covered at least 2 hours.
Shape into 1 or 2 balls.
Roll in nuts and parsley.
Serve with crackers.

title: sweet-sour beans
directions: Brown, until crisp, 2 strips bacon.
Cook 1 cup minced onion in bacon grease until yellow.
Stir in 1 tablespoon flour.
Add vegetable liquid, vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper and bring to boil.
Stir in 2 cups cut green beans.
Stir until heated. Sprinkle bacon on top.

title: broccoli balls
directions: Mix all ingredients and form into balls. Place on cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown hamburger and onion together, then add tomato paste and water.
Stir in until blended, then add spices and simmer for 1 hour.
Serve over cooked spaghetti.

title: graham cracker cake
directions: Combine graham crackers, sugar, oleo, egg yolks, nuts, dates, baking powder, milk and coconut.
Mix well.
Beat egg whites and fold in last.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Will keep like a fruit cake.

title: bread(martha mulligan's)
directions: Cream the yeast with a good pinch of salt and sugar.
Add warmed milk, sugar, eggs and about 4 cups flour.
Mix and beat well. Add butter and oil. Add more flour and knead until dough is soft and pliant and comes from the sides of the bowl.
Brush top of dough lightly with oil. Let rise until double in bulk.
Punch down and form into 2 braids (or loaves or rolls).
Let rise again. Brush with egg wash (optional).
Bake in a 350° oven for about 40 minutes or until golden brown.
Brush very generously with melted butter.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Bring pineapple to a boil and stir in jello.
Let cool and stir in remaining ingredients except Cool Whip.
Fold in Cool Whip and chill overnight.

title: sandwich spread pickles
directions: Let the first 2 ingredients stand 1 hour; drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Boil together 20 minutes.
Pack in jars; seal.

title: cape cod banana bread(easy!)
directions: Mix in order given and bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: mushroom beef tenderloin
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in bowl; stir well.
Place tenderloin in a large shallow dish; pour wine mixture over tenderloin.
Cover and marinate in fridge for 6 to 8 hours.

title: molasses sugar cookie
directions: Melt shortening in saucepan on stove.
Add sugar, molasses, egg.
Beat well.
Sift flour with baking powder, salt, and spices; add to first mixture and mix well.
Chill well.
Form into balls and roll in white sugar.
Place on greased or sprayed cookie sheet or on cookie sheet lined with parchment paper.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese to room temperature.
Mix sour cream; mix as directed on package.
Mix cream cheese and sour cream mixture thoroughly.
Chop onions and add to mixture.
Shred beef in and stir.
Refrigerate.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs in large bowl.
Stir in oil, sugar, zucchini and vanilla, then flour, baking powder, salt, soda and cinnamon.
Add raisins and nuts.
Spoon batter into two greased 8 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: nisu - finnish coffee bread
directions: Warm the milk and butter to melting.
Add sugar, salt and cardamon.
Combine the yeast and lukewarm water.
Beat eggs and add, with the yeast mix, to the COOLED milk.
Gradually add flour and mix to a stiff dough.
Let rise until doubled.
Put on a floured board.
Cut into 4 chunks and then cut each chunk into 3 pieces.
Roll each piece and make a braid of the 3 long pieces. Let rise in greased pans for 1 hour.
Makes 4 loaves.

title: ground round vegetable soup
directions: In a large kettle (6 quart or larger), crumble meat into water.
Add vegetables, celery, salt and pepper.
Start on high until it comes to a boil.
Reduce heat to medium-low.
Cover and let simmer for 1 hour or longer until vegetables are tender.
Add V-8 juice, celery salt, Season-All and sugar.
Stir to dissolve sugar.
You may have to add a little more water.
Cover and let simmer for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: sesame chinese noodles
directions: Boil noodles until al dente.
Rinse cooked noodles under cold water.

title: hot fudge sundae pie
directions: Mix crumbs, sugar and butter.
Spoon evenly into 9
or 10-inch pie plate.
Chill covered for 30 minutes.

title: mock champagne punch
directions: Pour concentrates and water into punch bowl.
Carefully pour ginger ale, sparkling water and grape juice down side of bowl. Add ice ring or cubes containing mint leaves and maraschino cherries to punch to float on top of punch.

title: chile corn chowder
directions: In a 4 to 5-quart saucepan, cook bacon over medium heat until crisp.
Remove from pan.
Drain, crumble and set aside, then discard all but 2 tablespoons of the drippings.
Add sausage and onion to drippings in pan; cook, stirring occasionally, until onion is soft and sausage slices are browned (about 10 minutes). Stir in potato and water.
Bring to a boil over high heat.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer until potato is tender when pierced (about 15 minutes).
Stir in corn, chiles, pimentos and half and half. Heat, stirring occasionally, just until steaming (do not boil). Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Garnish individual servings with bacon.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cool chicken and arrange in 9 x 13-inch dish, covered with broccoli.
Mix lemon juice, mayonnaise, curry powder and chicken soup.
Pour mixture over chicken and broccoli.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese over top; also sprinkle bread crumbs over all. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: hardee's biscuits
directions: Mix first five ingredients. Work in shortening until mealy. Mix together yeast and warm water.
Dissolve well and add to 1 1/2 cups buttermilk.
Add to flour mixture.
Mix well, then knead lightly.
Refrigerate overnight.
Roll out about 1/2 inch thick, butter and overlap dough; cut into your favorite size and bake at 450° for 8 to 12 minutes.
Makes about 20 average biscuits.

title: peach-nuttiest topping
directions: In saucepan, combine first 4 ingredients.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture boils.
Cook 1 to 2 minutes.
Stir in butter and vanilla.
Add pecans.
Serve warm over ice cream.
Makes 3/4 cup.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Mix together baking mix, cold water and cheese.
Cut biscuits with a cutter and place onto a baking pan.
Melt butter and seasonings together.
Brush biscuits with the butter and spices and bake 8 to 10 minutes.

title: chinese casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Sprinkle the other 1/2 can of Chinese noodles on top and bake 15 more minutes.

title: corn and frank chowder
directions: To make ground oat flour, place oats in blender and process for about 60 seconds (1 1/2 cups oats makes 1 cup flour).

title: caramel brownies
directions: Melt caramels in 1/3 cup evaporated milk.
Mix together the cake mix, butter and remaining milk.
Put half of mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan already greased.
Bake 6 minutes in a 350° oven. Sprinkle chocolate chips over the top and then pour melted caramels over this.
Crumble the rest of the mixture over the top.
Bake 15 minutes in a 350° oven.
Cool and refrigerate for at least 30 minutes.

title: all american casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in a pot or casserole dish that holds at least 2 1/2 quarts.
Bake at 400° for 35 minutes or until bubbling hot.
Makes 8 servings.

title: ranch oyster crackers
directions: Combine first five ingredients.
Pour over crackers, stirring to coat.
Place on baking sheets and bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 275°. Cool on paper towels.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients into large bowl.
Add oil and eggs.
Stir until ingredients are moistened.
Do not beat.
Stir in bananas, nuts, vanilla and pineapple.
Bake in a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes. Remove from pan in about 10 minutes and cool on wire rack.

title: rob's biscuits
directions: Mix ingredients together in bowl.
Drop on cookie sheet with tablespoon.
Bake at 425° until golden brown.
Makes approximately 6.

title: doritos salad
directions: Chop lettuce; add tomatoes, cheese and beans.
Break Doritos into small pieces.
Do not mix until time to serve.
Then mix and pour Catalina dressing over mixture.

title: frijoles borrachos(drunken beans)
directions: Roast and skin the chillies, slitting open the side of the chilli; remove the seeds and veins, but be careful not to break the flesh.
Into each chilli, insert a piece of cheese stuffing; taper the end of cheese slightly.
If necessary, roll the peeled, deseeded, stuffed chillies in flour.
Beat the egg yolks and whites separately; the whites should be beaten to the stiff peak stage.
Re-combine the eggs; beat together quickly.
Dip the chillies in the egg batter; be sure to cover the whole surface evenly; fry in fat or oil that is more than 1-inch deep.
Keep them warm in the oven until they are ready to serve.
Serve with refried beans and rice.

title: double chocolate chunk ice cream
directions: Take most any harmless event, fold in an ugly motive and a suspicious tone.
Stir in your own opinion.
Put in a good measure of "they say".
Add imaginary details to heighten taste.
Sprinkle well with spice of rumor.
Heat slowly over flame of envy.
Serve secretly and often to whoever will listen.

title: chocolate butter pecan ice cream
directions: In a small skillet, over medium heat, saute pecans in butter 2 minutes.
Cool.
In a small saucepan, combine cocoa and water; bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; stir in milk and vanilla.
Pour into square pan, 9 x 9 x 2-inch.
Freeze until mushy.
In a large bowl, beat cream until stiff.
In a chilled bowl, whip the chocolate mixture.
Fold into whipped cream.
Blend in pecans.
Return to pan, cover and return it to freezer, stirring frequently during first hour.
Makes about 1 1/2 quarts ice cream.

title: ham and cheese whirlers
directions: Spread bread with dressing; add 1 slice each ham and cheese. Roll with pickle in center, jelly roll fashion.
Fasten with toothpicks.
Slice each roll in thirds or fourths.

title: chinese almond cookies
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients well.
Blend in flour mixture and almonds.
Shape into 1-inch balls on ungreased cookie sheet. Flatten with a glass; brush with slightly beaten egg white.
Place an almond half on each cookie, pressing in slightly.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: old fashion applesauce cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add to sugar, applesauce and butter which has been mixed together.
Add raisins.
Bake in tube pan at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: homemade mincemeat
directions: Pare and core apples; grind with beef and suet.
Add remaining ingredients, except pastry.
Cook, covered, in a large kettle over medium-low heat for 30 minutes.
Uncover; cook until desired thickness, approximately 1 hour.

title: frozen mint desserts
directions: In a large bowl beat butter and sugar until light and fluffy. Beat in chocolate, eggs, vanilla and peppermint until light and fluffy.
Spoon into 18 paper-lined muffin cups.
Sprinkle with optional graham cracker crumbs.
Freeze at least 5 hours, or up to 2 weeks.
To serve, remove from freezer, top with whipped cream if desired, serve immediately.

title: lime cottage cheese salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add marshmallows and let them melt.
Stir in salt and pineapple.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Fold in cottage cheese, whipped cream and nuts.
Pour into 8 x 8-inch pan.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix together pudding and pineapple. Stir in nuts and marshmallows. Then fold in Cool Whip. Refrigerate.

title: applesauce-oatmeal tea bread
directions: In bowl, mix well flour, oats, baking powder, salt and soda; set aside.
Beat egg, sugar, applesauce and water until blended. Add to flour mixture; stir just until moistened.
Turn into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour (until pick inserted in center comes out clean).
Cool in pan 10 minutes; remove to rack.

title: icebox cheese wafers
directions: Cream together cheese, butter, salt and pepper.
Add flour. Make into roll.
Wrap in waxed paper and put in refrigerator. Will keep a month.
When needed, slice into thin wafers and bake in moderate oven, 300°.
A pecan half on each wafer is decorative. Makes 6 to 8 dozen.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix the first seven
ingredients together and pour into a casserole dish.
Mix
together the remaining ingredients and pour over top of corn mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: dirt cake
directions: You will need flowers (plastic or silk).

title: dishpan cookies
directions: Cream together sugars, vanilla, oil and eggs.
Add flour, baking soda and salt.
Mix together.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Drop on ungreased cookie sheet by teaspoon and bake at 350° until light brown.

title: orange-chocolate pudding
directions: Place large roasting pan in oven and fill with 1-inch hot water.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 6-cup mold, Bundt pan or bowl.

Place egg yolks in small bowl. Beat slightly and set aside. In a large bowl with electric mixer on high, beat egg whites until soft peaks form. Continue beating, gradually adding sugar until stiff peaks form.
In medium saucepan over low heat, cook chocolate and butter until melted, stirring constantly.
Place in a large bowl.
Gradually stir 1/2 cup chocolate mixture into egg yolks.
Stir egg mixture, flour, vanilla and orange peel into chocolate. Stir about 1/3 egg whites into chocolate, then fold in remaining egg whites.
Pour into mold. Cover tightly with lid or foil. Place in roasting pan in oven.

title: cheese ball ii
directions: Mix all together. Form into a ball. Roll in nuts. Refrigerate.

title: spicy cider
directions: Mix apple cider,
cranberry juice,
and orange juice then pour into percolator.
In the basket put sugar,
allspice, and cinnamon.
Percolate about 30 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well.
Add 1/2 of the flour and 1/2 of the cram.
Mix well.
Add remaining flour and cream.
Add vanilla. Pour into a greased and floured 12-cup Bundt pan and put in cold oven.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 300°.
Cool in pan for 10 to 15 minutes.
Turn out on wire rack to finish cooling.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: crawfish etouffee
directions: Thaw crawfish tails or shrimp, if frozen.
Rinse and pat dry with paper towels.

title: savory rice casserole
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in butter; stir in all remaining ingredients and one soup can of water.
Pour into casserole.
Bake at 325 F for 1 hr.
Let stand for several minutes before serving.

title: christmas cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Chop dried beef.
Mix cream cheese, Accent, onions, beef, pimentos, Worchestershire sauce, pimento cheese, dash of red pepper and a dash of garlic powder.
Form a ball or log.
Sprinkle with chili powder and paprika.
Roll in pecans.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: chicken broccoli turnover
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in a large warm bowl.
Add sugar, salt, margarine and 1 1/2 cups flour; beat until smooth.
Stir in enough flour to make a soft dough.
Knead 6 to 8 minutes.
Set in greased bowl; turn to grease top.
Cover; let rise until doubled, about 1 hour.
Punch dough down; divide in half.
Roll each half into 10-inch circle.

title: kelly's microwave peanut brittle
directions: Microwave sugar, Karo syrup and peanuts for four minutes on High.
Remove from microwave and stir.
Then cook 3 to 5 minutes and add butter and vanilla.
Microwave 1 to 2 minutes, then remove and stir in baking soda.
Pour on buttered pan.

title: mistakes
directions: Brown meat separately and drain well on paper towels.
Combine with both cheese and seasonings.
Cool slightly.
Spread on bread. Freeze on cookie sheets (about 1/2 hour).
Put in plastic bags to use when wanted or bake immediately at 350° until cheese is bubbly.

title: cranberry pumpkin ring
directions: In a mixer bowl, combine 1/2 cup flour and yeast.
In a saucepan, heat 1/2 cup milk, 1/3 cup sugar, 1/4 cup butter or margarine, 1 teaspoon cinnamon, nutmeg, cloves and 3/4 teaspoon salt until warm (115° to 120°).
Add to flour mixture.
Beat with an electric mixer on low speed 1/2 minute, scraping sides of bowl. Add egg and pumpkin.
Beat 3 minutes on high speed.
Using a spoon, stir in whole wheat flour and as much of the unbleached flour as you can.

title: diet oatmeal cookies
directions: Bring raisins and 1/2 cup warm water to a boil. Boil 1 minute. Set aside and let cool. In large bowl, mix eggs and butter together. Add remaining ingredients. Add raisins and water. Mix well. Drop by teaspoonfuls on lightly greased baking sheet. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: fruit bread
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly by hand.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan or 2 loaf pans.
Bake at 300° for approximately 1 hour and 45 minutes.
(Makes great Christmas gifts!)

title: beef 'n' beans
directions: Cook beef and onions in margarine until tender (drain grease). Add beans, mushrooms and broth.
Cover and simmer for 15 minutes. Combine mushroom juice and cornstarch.
Slowly add to skillet. Heat and serve over rice.

title: sunshine slush
directions: Bring water and sugar to boil then let cool.
Mix pineapple juice and bananas in blender.
Mix all ingredients and freeze. Keeps at least three months in freezer.

title: potatoes with rosemary
directions: Wash and peel potatoes then cut into thin, round slices. Arrange them in an oven pan that has been greased with olive oil. Wash rosemary and trim the leaves.
Sprinkle over potatoes.

title: calico beans
directions: Cook bacon for 5 minutes, stirring frequently.
Drain well. Continue cooking bacon and add onion, stirring frequently, until onion is tender.
In 2 1/2 to 3-quart casserole, stir together brown sugar, ketchup and vinegar.
Stir in bacon mixture and all of the beans; mix well.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until bubbly.
Makes 12 servings.

title: easy baked nacho dip
directions: Mix refried beans with 2 tablespoons sour cream and package of taco seasoning mix.
When well mixed, spread it out along bottom of shallow casserole dish.
Next, spread a layer of sour cream on top of bean mixture.
Top with a layer of grated Cheddar cheese. Bake at 350° until heated through and cheese melts (approximately 20 minutes).
Serve with warm nacho chips.

title: raw broccoli salad
directions: Wash broccoli and drain on paper towels.
Blot out all excess moisture.
Chop fine.
Add other ingredients; mix well and chill.

title: chiffon chocolate pie
directions: Add chocolate to milk and heat in a double boiler.
When chocolate is melted, beat with an eggbeater until blended.
Sift sugar, cornstarch, and salt together and add small amount to chocolate mix, stirring until smooth.
Return to double boiler. Add butter and stir constantly until thickened.
Cook 10 minutes longer, stirring occasionally.
Pour a small amount over egg yolks, stirring vigorously.
Return to double boiler and cook until thickened.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 325 for 20 minutes.

title: dump salad
directions: Mix all together and let set for 2 hours. Arrange in a 2 quart bowl - very pretty.

title: old-fashioned oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream Crisco with sugar.
Add eggs.
Sift dry ingredients together and add first mixture.
Add vanilla and oatmeal.
Stir in nuts.
Shape in rolls and store in refrigerator overnight or drop on a cookie sheet.
Bake 12 minutes at 375°.
(Do not substitute ingredients.)

title: topsy turvy strawberry cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour marshmallows in bottom of pan.
Pour prepared cake over marshmallows.
Sprinkle gelatin over cake batter.
Slice and place frozen strawberries over gelatin.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: pineapple marshmallow cake
directions: Butter a 13 x 9 x 2-inch cake pan.
Line with marshmallows. Mix cake mix as directed on box.
Pour over marshmallows.
Pour pineapple over cake batter.
Bake as directed on box.
No need to ice. Makes very moist cake.

title: meat loaf i hope!
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Knead until well mixed.
Shape into a loaf.
Bake at 350° until done, about 50 minutes.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: chocolate chip nut brownies
directions: Mix brown sugar and margarine.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Add flour, nuts and chips; mix well. Pour into greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Brown hamburger with onion and garlic powder.
Chop cabbage and layer in a 9 x 13-inch pan (will be above edge of pan).

title: barbecue
directions: Cook picnic ham and pull apart.
Boil ingredients for 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat and cook, uncovered, for 5 to 10 minutes.
Pour sauce over meat and toss.

title: green tomato catsup
directions: Squeeze juice out of the above after grinding up.
Put in vinegar mixture and add 1 tablespoon black pepper, 8 cups sugar and let boil full 15 minutes.
Fill pint jars and seal with hot two piece jar lids.
Makes a lot of catsup so you can make 1/3 or 1/2 of this recipe.
Will keep sealed a long time.

title: layer salad
directions: Layer lettuce, celery, green pepper and onion in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle the peas on top.
Mix Miracle Whip and Good Seasons salad dressing together and spread on top of lettuce mixture. Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese and bacon.

title: eskimo pie
directions: Mix ice cream and Cool Whip (has to be a little soft).
Layer 1/2 of the crushed Oreos in a 9 x 13-inch pan, then ice cream. Spread rest of the Oreos on top.
Sprinkle 1 cup chopped pecans on top with hot fudge topping.
Freeze 2 to 3 hours.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Grease 2-quart casserole dish.
Spread rice evenly in bottom of dish.
Mix flour, chili powder, salt and pepper.
Sprinkle 1/3 of mixture over rice.
Dot with 1/2 tablespoon melted margarine. Mix ground beef with onion and garlic.
Cook in skillet until slightly browned.
Spread over rice.
Spread with 1/3 of flour mixture and dot with margarine.
Make a layer of tomatoes, including the liquid; repeat with flour and margarine.
Spread corn on top and dot with remaining margarine.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: unusual corn
directions: With mixer, blend egg, sour cream and margarine.
Add corn muffin mix and blend.
Fold in both corn.
Bake in greased 8 x 8-inch pan or 2-quart dish at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: old fashion raisin pie
directions: In a pot mix raisins, water and salt.
Let simmer until raisins are soft.
In a bowl mix well sugar and flour.
Add to raisin and water mixture.
While mixture is still hot, add oleo or butter.
Stir all this in real well; use a wire whisk and cook until thickens (soft gel).
Pour into pie crust.
Top with pie strips or a solid crust with slits.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: cracker pie
directions: Prepare crust for a double crust pie.
Combine and boil sugar, water, oleo, cream of tartar, cinnamon, nutmeg and vanilla in a saucepan.
On medium heat, bring to boil and boil 3 to 4 minutes. Break up crackers in the crust that's in a pie pan.
Pour boiled mixture over crackers.
Put top crust on and sprinkle a little sugar on top crust.
Bake in 350° oven 30 minutes until golden brown.

title: blueberry surprise
directions: Place graham crackers in bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Prepare pudding according to directions; fold in Cool Whip.
Layer the pudding mixture with graham crackers for two layers.
Chill overnight.
Spread blueberries on top and serve.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Drain.
Add salt, pepper, spaghetti sauce, tomato sauce, and water.
Simmer.
Cook noodles according to package directions.
Spray large baking dish with Pam.
Layer ground beef mixture, noodles, and cheese. Repeat layers.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: zesty deviled eggs
directions: Cut eggs in half lengthwise and spoon out yolks.
Put yolks in a bowl and smash.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Fill whites heaping full.
Refrigerate until serving time.

title: onion rings
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Slice up onions.
Dip into mix. Pan or deep fat fry.

title: irene's chicken
directions: Layer beef on bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Then lay chicken on beef.
Pour combined soup and sour cream over chicken. Place bacon on top and season.
Dust with paprika.
Bake at 275° about 3 hours.
Serve with Rice Side Dish in Vegetable section.

title: broccoli rice
directions: In a medium saucepan, add the butter. Gently cook the onion until wilted. Stir in the mustard, then add the cheese spread. Gradually add the soup and stir. Add the broccoli and rice and stir gently, but well. Turn into a buttered shallow 2-quart baking dish. Sprinkle with the onion rings. Bake in a preheated oven at 350° until hot through, about 20 minutes. Makes 6 servings.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Cook the first 5 ingredients in saucepan, stirring until sugar is dissolved.
Continue cooking, without stirring, until it forms a brittle ball in cold water.
Add vanilla and stir just enough to fold it in.
Pour syrup slowly over popped corn.
With buttered hands, shape into balls.

title: stuffed flounder
directions: Melt margarine; add onions, celery and pepper and cook slow until soft. Add crab, stuffing mix, egg and other ingredients. Add hot water, small amount at a time, until well mixed. Split flounder in center and cut almost to fins. Stuff and bake at 400° for 15 minutes and broil until brown. This will stuff about 4 medium flounders. If you like, brush with melted butter and lemon juice before serving.

title: cajun coated catfish
directions: Wash and drain catfish fillets.
Cut into large bite size pieces.
Season on both sides with Tony Chachere Creole seasoning (use sparingly, hot!).
Dip fish into cooking oil and then coat well with Special K. Lay each piece of fish in an ungreased glass pan and cook for 15 minutes in a 450° oven.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Make pudding.
Decrease the milk by
cup
for each box. Add Cool Whip.
First and last layers must	be crackers. Chill, then frost.

title: carrot cake
directions: Beat together all ingredients until smooth and creamy.
Spread between layers and on outside of cake.

title: oatmeal pudding cookies
directions: Cream first 4 ingredients until fluffy.
Add eggs beating well.
Mix soda with flour and add to batter, beating at low speed.
Stir in oats, raisins and nuts.
Drop on ungreased cookie sheet about 1 teaspoonful 2 inches apart.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool on baking sheet 10 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: uncooked fruit cake
directions: Add cracker crumbs and nuts to fruit (cut up the pineapple just a little, leave cherries whole).
Heat milk, add marshmallows; stir until melted (do not burn).
Then add milk and marshmallows to nuts, fruit and crumbs.
Mix with hands.
Pack tightly into pans lined with wax paper or plastic wrap.
Refrigerate to cool.
Wrap and freeze.
Keeps up to a year.
(Mini loaf pans 2 1/4 x 4 1/4-inch can be used or other loaf pans.)

title: orange snack cake
directions: Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mounds cake
directions: Bake cake according to package directions in 2 round pans. Cool.
Cut each layer lengthwise (4 layers).
Bring sugar and cream to a boil and cook to soft ball stage.
Add marshmallows; allow to melt.
Add coconut and spread between layers.
Spread frosting on top and sides of cake.

title: brisket
directions: Mix liquid smoke, garlic, onion and celery salts into a paste. Rub on meat.
Wrap in foil and marinate in refrigerator overnight.

title: lattuge in brodo(lettuce in broth)
directions: Remove the outside leaves of the lettuces and extract the hearts, leaving heads intact.
Soak the mushrooms in lukewarm water to cover for 30 minutes.
Drain the mushrooms and chop together with 2 lettuce hearts, the marjoram, garlic and breadcrumbs.
Mix in 2 eggs, Parmesan, salt and pepper.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Drain asparagus; reserve liquid.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup of crumbs in bottom of buttered casserole dish.
Top with half of the asparagus, then half of soup.
Add asparagus liquid.
Repeat layers of asparagus and soup.
Top with remaining crumbs.
Dot with margarine.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 minutes or until crumbs are browned.
Serves 8.

title: lemon crisp
directions: Chill evaporated milk and a mixing bowl overnight.
Mix together lemon jello, water, lemon juice and 1/2 cup sugar.
Let stand until jelly-like.
Take graham crackers and crush.
(Putting into a sealed plastic bag and using a rolling pin over it works well.)
Then mix margarine or butter, sugar and all but 1/2 cup of graham cracker crumbs.
Place this mixture in bottom of a serving dish.
Take chilled milk and bowl.
Beat milk in chilled bowl until foamy like cream.
Add jello mixture and mix.
Pour into serving dish on top of crumb mixture.
Refrigerate until firm. Sprinkle remaining 1/2 cup of graham cracker crumbs on top. Serve.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix ingredients and form into loaf.
Place in loaf pan.
Cover with ketchup and bake in preheated oven at 350°.

title: enchiladas
directions: Cut up onion and cook in small amount of oil.
Set aside. Fry your tortillas in just a little bit of oil in the bottom of a pan. Drain the grease off of them.
Lay tortillas flat.
Spoon or spread chili colorado or canned Enchilada sauce over tortillas one at a time.
Then put onion on them and shredded cheese.
Roll them up and place them side by side in a shallow baking dish.
Cover again with small amount of chili sauce.
Bake at 350 degrees for just a few minutes until heated through.

title: overnight breakfast casserole
directions: Butter (or spray) a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Line bottom of pan with bread.
Brown sausage. Drain to remove as much fat as possible.
Beat eggs, milk, mustard, salt and pepper together. Spread sausage evenly over bread slices. Top with mushroom pieces. Layer cheeses over mushrooms.
Pour egg mixture over everything. Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° (325° for glass pan) for 45 minutes or until knife inserted into center comes out clean.

title: quick tuna casserole
directions: Cook macaroni according to directions on box.
Add tuna, corn or peas, soup and onion.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Pour in a casserole dish.
May add additional cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or microwave until heated through.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add oil, sugar, vanilla and zucchini. Mix lightly, but well.
Add dry ingredients and nuts.
Mix thoroughly. Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan or divide into two loaf pans. Generously grease and flour pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Time varies according to oven.
Test with toothpick for doneness.

title: quick apple cake
directions: Blend first 3 ingredients together. Mix and sift the next 4 ingredients. Mix together. Then add apples and vanilla flavoring; stir well. Spread in baking pan. Bake in a 375° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: pralines
directions: Cook sugars and milk until it reaches soft ball stage.
Remove from heat and add butter, vanilla and pecans.
Stir until it loses its shine.
Spoon out on wax paper.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream together good the margarine, vegetable oil and sugar. Add flour, milk, baking powder, salt and eggs, one at a time.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Place chicken, skin side up, in casserole dish.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over chicken.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix margarine, sugar and milk; bring to full boil and boil 5 minutes.
Take off stove and add 1 small jar Jif peanut butter. Mix well; add 1 small jar Marshmallow Creme.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Mix well and pour in buttered 13 x 9 1/2-inch pan. Garnish with pecan halves.

title: wild mushroom toss
directions: In a large skillet cook mushrooms, peppers and onion in hot margarine or butter until tender.
Stir in seasoned salt and pepper.
Toss with hot pasta.
Top with cheese.
Makes about 2 cups sauce.

title: molded cucumber salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Stir in remaining ingredients; blend well.
Pour into mold.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: white cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add cup of cold water, alternately with flour in small amounts sifted together with other dry ingredients.

title: hawaiian sandwich
directions: Slice King's Hawaiian bread in 4 horizontal slices. In a bowl, mix cream cheese, crushed pineapple with juice and green onions. Spread mixture on bottom slice and layer with turkey and ham. Put the next piece of bread on and layer with mixture, turkey and ham. Continue to layer with the rest of the bread slices. Refrigerate for a couple of hours. Slice into wedges and serve.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Heat pineapple with 1 1/4 cups water.
When hot (not boiling), add jello.
Add cheese and stir well.
Chill.
Add whipped cream and maraschino cherries.
Let stand overnight.

title: cheese ball
directions: Cream the cheese and dressing well with a fork or with an electric mixer. Form into a ball and roll in nuts or bacon bits. Wrap ball in waxed paper and chill. Allow ball to come to room temperature before serving.
Serve with Sociables crackers or Triscuits.
(Easy and a real taste treat.)

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix together and roll into meatballs.
Brown in oil.
Take out and drain.
Add a little more oil, if needed.

title: teriburgers
directions: Mix soy sauce, sugar, ginger and garlic.
Shape meat into 4 patties.
Place patties in shallow glass dish. Pour soy sauce mixture over patties.
Cover; refrigerate at least 30 minutes. Remove patties from marinade.
Place patties on grill 4 inches from hot coals.
Cook about 7 minutes on each side, basting with reserved marinade.
Serve in buns.

title: spicy salad
directions: Dissolve red
hots
in water.
Remove from heat and add Jell-O and
when it is dissolved, add the applesauce.
When it is cool, put in the refrigerator to set good.

title: chocolate cherry cake or bars
directions: Combine all ingredients until well mixed.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: salami
directions: Mix hamburger and salt.
Let stand in refrigerator 4 hours or overnight.
Add liquid smoke, garlic and pepper; mix well.

title: holiday salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add cranberry sauce and strawberries.
Mash with potato masher.
Add nuts.
Pour in mold. Refrigerate.
Goes well with turkey and dressing.

title: creamy chicken divan
directions: Prepare dinner as directed on package.
Melt margarine in saucepan on low heat.
Blend in salad dressing, flour and salt. Gradually add milk; cook, stirring constantly, until thickened. Layer dinner mixture, broccoli and chicken in a 10 x 6-inch baking dish.
Top with sauce.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: beer bread
directions: Mix together the flour and sugar. Stir in the beer, using a fork. Beat egg yolk. Grease pan lightly. Put in dough mix and then spread the beaten egg yolk over the top of the dough. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: zucchini, onions and tomato casserole
directions: Slice zucchini, onions and peeled tomatoes.
Alternate layers of zucchini, onion, tomatoes and bread crumbs in a baking dish. Repeat layers and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Sprinkle with grated cheese just before baking time expires.

title: pepper steak
directions: Melt shortening in skillet.
Cut meat into 1-inch strips; sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Fry meat, onion and garlic until brown.
Add peppers and bouillon; cover and cook 30 minutes.
Add tomatoes; simmer 5 minutes.
Combine cornstarch, soy sauce and water.
Add to meat mixture and cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Serve over cooked rice.
Serves 6.

title: grandma's hickory nut cake
directions: Cream together sugar and butter; add eggs and beat on medium (mixer) speed for 2 minutes.
Mix together lightly with fork the salt, baking powder and flour.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Mix well.
Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 8-inch layer pans and bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Cream the butter, sugar, vanilla and salt until fluffy.
Stir in raisins, then oats until well blended.
Gradually stir in flour until blended.
Use hands if necessary.
Press 1/4 mixture into 3-inch cookie.
Bake in a 325° oven for 15 to 17 minutes or less if chewy cookies are preferred.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Cook beef and chicken.
Mix with other ingredients.
Simmer until vegetables are done.
Okra can be added last 15 minutes if desired.
Add chicken broth for desired thickness.

title: ice cream cake
directions: Bake a plain cake in a square pan.
Cut each layer crossways, so it
will fit in a loaf pan.
Put a layer of cake in dish.
Add a layer of fresh frozen fruit, such as strawberries or peaches or your favorite.
Cover with a layer of ice cream, which has been slightly softened.
Add the same mixture again on top of the first layer; top with chopped nuts.
Store in freezer; slice for serving.

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix flour, margarine, and 1/4 cup confectionary sugar together.
Press in ungreased 8 x 8 or 9 x 9 pan, building edges up 1/2 inch. Bake crust at 350° for 20 minutes.
Beat remaining ingredients except confectionary sugar, with electric mixer on high speed about 3 minutes or until light and fluffy.
Pour over hot crust. Bake 25-30 minutes or until no indentation remains when touched lightly in center.
Cool in pan.
Dust with confectionary sugar.
Cut into 5 rows x 5 rows.
If desired, may add 1/2 cup coconut into the egg mixture.

title: corn flake candy
directions: Dissolve corn syrup and sugar; bring to a boil. Take off when bubbles form around edge.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter and corn flakes. Form in balls and place on paper.

title: divinity
directions: Boil sugar, syrup and water together until it forms a hard ball in cold water.
Beat egg whites very stiff.
Pour in hot syrup.
Beat continually.
Add the nuts.
Beat.
Spread on buttered pan.
Refrigerate until chilled.
Cut and serve.
This recipe will serve 12 people.

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Shape into balls, about 3-inches in diameter.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: bubble bread
directions: Grease Bundt pan.
Place rolls in pan evenly, in one layer. Mix both sugars, cinnamon and pudding mix.
Sprinkle over rolls, then put nuts over this.
Finally pour the butter over all.
Let stand overnight or all day to rise.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°. Keep in pan 15 minutes before removing.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Combine above ingredients.
Do not overmix.
Drop by spoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.

title: seafood spread
directions: Beat the cream cheese for 1 to 2 minutes with electric mixer until creamy.
Blend in remaining ingredients (except walnuts and paprika).
Spread mixture in 9-inch pie plate.
Top with walnuts and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes approximately 3 cups.

title: strawberry sour cream salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
Add strawberries, pineapple and bananas.
Pour half of mixture in 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Chill until firm.
Spoon sour cream over top.
Spread evenly.
Cover with remaining jello mixture.
Chill.
Cut in squares and serve on lettuce.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes with bay leaf; drain and remove bay leaf.
Cool, peel and slice.
Combine with all other ingredients, except cheese, and put in a greased casserole.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top.
Cook, covered, in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish for 30 minutes at 375°.

title: yummy dressing
directions: Combine and refrigerate.
Shake well before using.

title: fruit punch
directions: Mix the juices, Kool-Aid, water and sugar to taste.
Right before serving, slice the bananas and put in frozen strawberries.

title: delicious rice
directions: Combine ingredients and bake in greased casserole.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes or until all is hot.

title: ham salad sandwiches
directions: Put meat, eggs and pickles through food grinder. Mix with mayonnaise.
Spread slices of bread with mixture.
Cover top slice with butter and toast.
Serve with dill pickle.

title: diet salad dressing
directions: Mix cottage cheese, buttermilk and salad dressing mix in a bowl.
Pour into a 1-quart container and shake well.
Refrigerate and shake again before serving.

title: strawberry "pizza"
directions: Mix well.
Press into 2 pie pans.
Bake at 350°
for 15 minutes, or until brown.

title: kidney bean dip
directions: Drain liquid from beans through strainer and set aside.
Grind onion and pepper; press as much liquid out as possible through strainer.
Press liquid from sweet relish and horseradish. Dispose of liquid and mix all ingredients together.
Chill.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients until clear.
Add everything else. Cool.
Pour into baked pie shell.
You can add dots of whipped cream if you want too.

title: pecan crispies
directions: Cream butter, shortening, sugar and eggs. Beat well. Sift dry ingredients. Add to creamed mixture. Add nuts. Drop from teaspoon 2-inches apart onto greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes. Makes about 5 dozen cookies.

title: turkey squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Blend cheese and butter until smooth.
Add turkey, pepper, salt, onion and pimento; mix well.
Separate rolls into 4 rectangles.
Firmly press perforations to seal.
Spoon 1/2 cup meat mixture into center of roll.
Pull 4 corners to center. Twist slightly; seal edges.
Brush with butter.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet 20 to 25 minutes until brown.

title: veal parmigiana
directions: Pound veal cutlets thin.
Combine egg and milk in a pie plate. Combine bread crumbs and cheese in another pie plate. Dip each cutlet into the egg and milk mixture, then into the bread crumb and Parmesan cheese mixture.

title: caramel pie
directions: Put the condensed milk in crock-pot and cover with water. Cook on high for 5 hours. Remove from crock-pot. Cover and cool. Place in graham cracker crust. Top with Cool Whip.
Cut into small pieces as it is very rich.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix together dry ingredients and add carrots, oil, pineapple and eggs.
If desired, add orange rind. Bake in oiled and floured tube pan for 1 hour or until done. Cool and serve plain or frosted.

title: chicken in a skillet
directions: Spray chicken cutlets with cooking spray.
Place in heated skillet.
Saute on each side for 2 minutes, remove from skillet. Keep warm.

title: rice casserole with dill, pine nuts and tomatoes(makes 4 to 6 servings)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly oil an 8 x 10-inch baking dish. Heat oil in a large skillet.
Add vegetables, garlic, herbs and half the parsley.
Saute over medium-high heat for 6 minutes.
Add sugar, paprika, salt and rice.
Cook 1 minute.
Add tomatoes, water and currants or raisins; bring to a simmer.
Transfer to baking dish, cover and bake until rice is tender, about 1 1/2 hours.
Toss with pine nuts or almonds and remaining parsley.
Garnish with lemon wedges.
Serve hot.

title: chicken livers and bacon rolls
directions: Roll chicken livers in flour and wrap 1/2 slice of bacon around the liver.
Have the bacon overlap the liver.
Use enough oil to cover halfway up on the liver and bacon.
Get oil real hot.
Place livers and bacon in oil, with overlap toward skillet.
Fry until bacon is crisp.

title: poppy seed zucchini
directions: In a large skillet, simmer the first 3 ingredients, covered, until the zucchini is tender. Add the remaining ingredients and heat through.
Serves 4.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cook chicken until well done; remove from bones and dice. Drain the Veg-All; add to chicken.
Add gravy; mix well.
Place one pie crust in bottom of pie pan.
Add chicken mixture; cover with second crust.
Bake at 325° for about 20 to 25 minutes, or until brown.

title: party mix
directions: Mix all together and put in a tight container for 24 hours.

title: cherry pie salad
directions: Mix whipped topping and sour cream.
Fold in powdered sugar. Drain oranges and pineapple.
Mix together all ingredients and refrigerate until chilled before serving.

title: cranberry salad supreme
directions: Dissolve raspberry flavored gelatin in 1 cup boiling water. Stir in cranberry sauce.
Pour into 9 x 9 x 2 inch baking pan. Chill until almost firm.

title: cheese grits
directions: Prepare grits with first 3 ingredients.
Cook 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add eggs, milk, margarine and cheese to grits and cook until cheese melts.
Serve warm.

title: sock it to me cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 10 inch tube pan. Sift together the flour, baking soda and salt.
Set aside.
In a large bowl, cream together the butter and white sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in the eggs one at a time, then stir in the sour cream and vanilla.
Beat in the flour mixture until well blended. Pour half of batter into prepared tube pan.
Sprinkle with cinnamon, brown sugar and nuts.
Pour in remaining batter.
Bake in the preheated oven for 90 minutes, or until a toothpick inserted into the center of the cake comes out clean.
Let cool in pan for 10 minutes before removing.

title: ham-it-up skillet
directions: Heat oil in skillet, saute ham in oil.
Gradually stir in liquid.
Add rice.
Now cover skillet and simmer.
Add parsley and olives to garnish.

title: rice the fast way(servings:  6)
directions: In glass bowl, microwave water, salt and butter 5 minutes or until boiling.
Add rice.
Cover and microwave 15 minutes.
Remove and let stand 5 minutes.

title: hot water cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together real good.
Then add 3 cups boiling water. Spoon in skillet with shortening or Crisco oil. Skillet should be hot.

title: swiss steak
directions: Brown meat in large skillet.
Add undiluted soup, undrained mushrooms, minced garlic, wine, salt and pepper.
Simmer for approximately 4 hours.
Serve over noodles, rice or grits.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Mix baking soda with persimmon juice.
Mix sugar, flour, cinnamon and salt.
Mix milk, eggs, margarine and persimmon juice mixture.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in a margarine greased pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cheese soup
directions: Melt butter and saute onions, celery and carrots over low heat. Add chicken broth and simmer 30 minutes.
Add potato soup, cheese, parsley, Tabasco sauce, salt and pepper.
Stir in sour cream and simmer 15 minutes.
Add sherry.
Stir and serve.
Yields 10 cups.

title: baked macaroni
directions: Spray Pyrex dish with no-stick cooking spray.
Add boiled macaroni.
Beat eggs and milk together; add seasonings.
Pour over macaroni.
Put grated cheese over top and add several pats of margarine.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes, uncovered.

title: fig preserves
directions: Sprinkle ginger over figs.
Cover with boiling water and let stand for 15 minutes.
Mix sugar with enough water to boil. Remove figs from the water and add syrup.
Cook until syrup is thick.

title: spuds
directions: Heat oven to 475°.
Pour butter in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Cut scrubbed white Idaho potatoes into very thin slices and add to butter, turning to coat in the butter.
Bake 20 minutes, turning once during this time.
After 20 minutes, broil 6 inches from heat until crisp and brown.

title: pennsylvania dutch bread pudding
directions: Toast bread and cut into 1/2-inch cubes.
Put in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Add hot milk and butter.
Let stand 30 minutes.
Beat eggs until fluffy.
Add salt, sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg, raisins and apples.
Pour over bread mixture and bake, uncovered, in 300° oven for 45 minutes.
Serve with lemon sauce and cream.

title: simple oven fried chicken
directions: Wipe the pieces of chicken with paper toweling.
Melt the margarine in a saucepan.
Mix the salt, pepper, bread crumbs and cornstarch together thoroughly.
Dip each piece of chicken into the melted margarine, then into the bread crumb mixture.
Place the chicken pieces, skin side down, in a shallow baking pan.

Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes, then turn each piece of chicken over, skin side up, and continue to bake at 350° for 25 minutes longer, or until rich brown and each piece can be easily pierced with a fork.
Serve at once, piping hot.

title: cranberry vinegar
