directions: In a saucepan, bring all the ingredients to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer for 5 minutes or until the cranberries burst. Cool. Strain through a fine sieve into bottles or jars. Seal tightly. Throw away cranberries and cinnamon stick. Chill until ready to use in your favorite dishes.

title: sausage cornbread
directions: Brown sausage and onion; drain.
Mix together remaining ingredients.
Add sausage mixture and mix well.
Pour into well-greased large iron skillet.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour to 1 hour and 25 minutes.

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix and put half in bottom of pan.
Save rest for top.

title: curried chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Simmer slowly in frying pan for 2 hours.
Thin with water if necessary.
Serve on rice.

title: fancy coleslaw
directions: Combine all ingredients with enough dressing to moisten, mixing well.
Chill to serving time.
Serves 6.

title: fresh cranberry sauce
directions: Dissolve sugar in cider and bring to a boil.
Add orange rind, berries and cinnamon.
Lower heat.
Simmer uncovered 20 to 25 minutes.
stir occasionally.
Goes good with turkey, chicken or ham.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together well and serve with thin crackers.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Bake for 1 hour at 325° in 2 well-greased loaf pans.

title: pie crust
directions: In a saucepan, bring oil and water to a boil. Remove from heat. Add flour. Stir thoroughly; let cool. Spread in GLASS pie plate. Yield: 1 crust.

title: three fruit compote
directions: Drain syrup from all three fruits; combine with all remaining ingredients in a sortable serving dish; chill.

title: lava flow
directions: Blend the first 6 ingredients until slush. Ahead of time, thaw the strawberries and puree. In a tall clear glass, pour 1/4-inch strawberry puree; fill remaining glass with blended ingredients and top with real whip cream. Add cherry on top.

title: barbecue meat sandwich
directions: Brown meat.
Add other ingredients.
Simmer slowly for 30 minutes.

title: almond tart
directions: Cream together the oleo and sugar. Add eggs; mix well.
Add flour alternately with milk. Add almond flavoring.
Bake at 350° for about 18 to 20 minutes.

title: vegetarian pizza
directions: Spread crescent rolls flat on large cookie sheet.
Blend the seams together and stretch as large as you can.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Let cool.
Mix sauce ingredients together and spread on cooled crust.
Put chopped vegetables on one at a time. Press into sauce.
Sprinkle on cheddar cheese.
Cut into pieces.

title: apple torte
directions: Beat egg well and add sugar gradually.
Sift together and stir in flour, baking powder and salt.
Add vanilla, apples and nuts. Pour into greased pie plate or 8-inch square pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 minutes.
Top with whipped cream.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs, 1/4 cup sugar and 1/4 cup margarine. Spread in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Refrigerate 1 hour. Combine powdered sugar, 1/2 cup soft margarine, vanilla and egg. Beat well. Spread over the graham cracker crust. Cool 1 hour. Combine all the fruit except cherries and spread over the first 2 layers. Cover with Cool Whip or Dream Whip. Add chopped nuts, if desired. Top with cherries. Refrigerate several hours.

title: waffle dessert topping
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Store in fridge. Microwave on Medium to warm before serving.

title: zucchini frittata
directions: Heat oil in a wide frying pan over medium-high heat. Add onion, garlic, chard and zucchini. Cook, stirring occasionally, until vegetables are soft (about 5 minutes).
Remove form heat and let cool slightly. Beat eggs lightly with pepper, basil and oregano.
Stir in cheese and vegetables.
Pour into a greased 9-inch pie pan and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes until puffed and browned.
Serve hot or at room temperature.
Makes 6 servings.

title: divinity candy
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine sugar, syrup, water and salt. Without stirring, cook over low heat until temperature on candy thermometer reaches 265° (approximately 10 to 15 minutes) or until a small amount of mixture dropped into very cold water forms a soft ball that will not flatten when pressed between finger and thumb.

Just before temperature reaches 265°, in a large bowl with mixer at high speed, beat egg whites until stiff peaks form. Slowly pour in hot mixture a little at a time, beating at high speed until mixture begins to lose its gloss.
Reduce mixer speed to low.
Add vanilla and nuts and using a spoon, stir until candy holds its' shape when dropped from a spoon.
Drop by spoonful onto wax paper or foil to cool.
Store in covered container.

title: cheese dip
directions: Mix together in ovenproof bowl.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.
Serve with crackers.

title: pumpkin torte
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine the next 3 ingredients and pour over pan mixture. Bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Combine the last 7 ingredients and cook until thick (about 10 minutes).
Add more milk, if too thick.
Cool, then pour over cheese mixture.
Top with more graham cracker crumbs and whipped cream when served.
Refrigerate overnight before serving.

title: ranch beans
directions: Brown meat, bacon and onion.
Drain.
Add all ingredients but beans, stir.
Add beans.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: stir and drop sugar cookies
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix eggs, sugar, salad oil, lemon peel and vanilla thoroughly. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop dough by teaspoonfuls about 2-inches apart onto ungreased baking sheet. Flatten with greased bottom of glass dipped in sugar.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Eight minutes for soft, 10 minutes crispy.

title: party potatoes
directions: Place frozen potatoes in 9 x 13-inch pan or baking dish.
In bowl, stir soup, sour cream, cream cheese, salt, pepper and garlic.
Pour mixture over potatoes.
Melt butter and pour over top.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Put cheese on top and bake another 15 minutes.
If you put them in a crock-pot, bake them first in the oven.
Add the cheese after the potatoes are in the crock-pot.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken, bacon, water chestnuts, celery and grapes in large bowl.
In separate bowl, whisk remaining ingredients.
Add to salad and toss to coat; chill.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Spread cookie dough on nongreased pizza pan.
Bake at 350° until lightly brown (approximately 10 minutes).
Cool.
Mix cream cheese and sugar and spread on crust.
Top with pie filling.
Soak fruit in pineapple juice.
Arrange fruit on pizza.
Slice and serve.

title: apple butter(crock-pot)
directions: Put all ingredients in crock-pot on high for 2 hours.
Do not uncover for 2 hours, then remove lid and cook 6 to 7 hours longer. Stir occasionally to keep from scorching.
Put into scalded jars immediately and seal.

title: broccoli cheese casserole
directions: Mix cheese, chicken soup and milk until creamy.
Add butter, celery and onions. Add rice and broccoli.
Pour into casserole dish and sprinkle stuffing mix on top. Put pats of butter over stuffing mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mexican dip
directions: Mix the taco seasoning with the sour cream.
Layer the ingredients in an oblong dish in order.
Let chill overnight.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift together all dry ingredients.
Beat eggs into sugar, one at a time.
Add oil to dry ingredients, a little at a time.
Add this mixture to eggs and sugar.
Add carrots and nuts.
Bake in three 8-inch pans at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: king ranch chicken casserole
directions: Stew chicken in water in large pot until tender.
Reserve 1 cup chicken broth.
Bone chicken; cut meat into bite size pieces.

title: flour tortillas
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening.
Add water.
Knead 15 to 20 times.
Let sit for 10 minutes.
Divide dough into 12 equal balls and roll out each tortilla.
Cook on hot griddle, turning once.
Makes 12 large tortillas.

title: russian creme(the peachtree tea room)
directions: In a small saucepan, add sugar to half and half and heat until lukewarm.
Stir constantly with a whisk until sugar dissolves. Soften gelatin in water and add all to warm half and half mixture. Continue to stir over heat until gelatin is dissolved.
Remove from heat and refrigerate until the mixture begins to thicken.

title: butterscotch pecan pound cake
directions: Mix in usual manner, adding flavorings and pecans last.
Also morsels.
Bake in Bundt pan (greased and floured) at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Cool on rack.

title: shredded potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes for 20 minutes.
Cool and peel.
Shred potatoes.

title: date pudding
directions: Mix all together and cook slowly (300°) in baking pan set in pan of hot water.
Serve warm with whipped cream.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Melt butter.
Pour butter on the bottom of an 8 1/2 x 11-inch dish.
Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs on top.
Then add 1 layer of chocolate chips, 1 layer of coconut and 1 layer of nuts.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 minutes.
Cool.
When cooled, cut into squares.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix well and refrigerate.
Best if made a day ahead.

title: peach crisp
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a medium bowl; cut butter into oat mixture with a pastry blender until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Stir in pecans.
Spoon peaches into a lightly greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Spoon crumb mixture on top.
Bake at 400° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Serve with ice cream.
Yield:
12 servings.

title: daddy's chicken pie
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Debone and cut in small pieces. Place in bottom of casserole dish.
Melt butter and pour over chicken.
Next mix milk and flour and pour over chicken.
Mix soup and broth together.
Heat and pour over top.
Do not stir this dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix together cream cheese, sour cream and taco seasoning mix. Fold into dish.
Add layer of shredded lettuce and Mozzarella cheese.
Make 1 layer of chopped tomatoes, onions, green pepper and sliced black olives.
Top with shredded Cheddar cheese. Chill.
Serve with tortilla chips.
Yields 1 (11 x 7-inch) Pyrex dish.

title: easy muffin tin rolls(makes 20 to 24 rolls)
directions: Grease muffin tins.
Combine ingredients in order given.
Mix well.
Break off sections of dough to half fill muffin well. Allow to rise in a warm place until doubled.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve hot with butter and honey or jam.
Note: Can use all white flour, if desired.

title: easy crust chicken pie
directions: Remove bones and skin from chicken.
Cut up and place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix chicken broth, celery soup, melted margarine, 1 teaspoon of salt and pepper.
Pour over cut up chicken pieces. Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Add milk and other half of margarine and mix well.
Pour this over chicken and bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: apple walnut cake
directions: Combine apples and sugar; let stand.
Beat eggs and add oil and vanilla.
Mix and sift flour, baking powder and cinnamon. Stir in alternately with apple sugar mixture.
Add walnuts.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until cake is done.
Let stand in pan to cool.
Ice with lemon butter icing or whipped cream.

title: water chestnut dip
directions: Mix well.
Better if left overnight in refrigerator.

title: classic leek soup
directions: Simmer leeks and potatoes in chicken broth until vegetables are soft, about 15 minutes.
Whirl mixture in blender until smooth, a small portion at a time, or rub through a wire strainer. Return soup to cooking pan and blend in cream, 3 tablespoons wine (or to taste) and salt to taste.
(This soup can be made ahead, covered and chilled.) Heat soup to simmering.
Sprinkle with chives and serve.
Makes 10 cups or 6 to 8 main servings.

title: linguine with brie and cherry tomatoes
directions: Cook pasta as directed.
In a large serving bowl, mix cheese, tomatoes, pepper and salt. Ladle 1/4 cup pasta water into bowl with cheese mixture. Stir until cheese melts.
Drain pasta. Add to cheese mixture.
Toss.
Sprinkle with chopped herbs and toss.

title: aunt pat's corn muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients together to form batter.
Spoon into greased muffin pans and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: italian chocolate cookies
directions: Grease pan.
Mix all dry ingredients.
Add the liquids (eggs and brandy) and knead.
Pinch off pieces of dough, have hands greased with cooking oil, it coats the cookie while cooking. Place on pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Keep dough cool.

title: barbecued squirrel
directions: Put some bacon on pan.
Lay the squirrel on them and lay 2 slices of bacon on top of them.
Place in oven and cook until done. Lay them on a dish.
Take out the bacon.
Sprinkle on tablespoon of flour in the sauce and let it brown, then pour 1 cup of water, 1 tablespoon of butter and tomato catsup.
Cool and pour over squirrel.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 3 tablespoons of liquid.
Combine sugar and flour.
Stir in pineapple juice.
Add cheese and pineapple, mixing well.
Spoon mixture into greased casserole dish.
Combine butter and cracker crumbs; stir well and sprinkle over pineapple mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: dream cake
directions: Combine cake mix, Dream Whip, instant vanilla pudding, milk, eggs and vanilla.
Beat 10 minutes at medium speed.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 9-inch layer pans or 3 (8-inch) layer pans. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes for 9-inch layers, 35 minutes for 8-inch layers or 45 minutes for 10-inch tube pan.
Cool in pans 10 minutes.
Remove from pans and cool on racks. Ice with desired topping.

title: gravy (not sauce)
directions: Fry 3-inch pieces of sausage in oil with spices.
In large saucepan, simmer paste with 3 cans of water and cooked sausage and spices until well mixed.
Add puree, 1 can of water and Parmesan cheese.
Stir and bring to boil.
Lower heat to simmer for about 1 1/2 hours, stirring often.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Mix well.
You may use any flavor of yogurt that you prefer.
Fresh sliced fruits for dipping could be apples, pears, peaches, nectarines, pineapple and bananas.
Also you could use strawberries, grapes and melons such as cantaloupe.

title: lou's cole slaw
directions: Grate cabbage, carrots and minced onion.
Place all into a bowl.
In a separate bowl, mix the vinegar, sugar and mayonnaise. Mix into the cabbage and carrots.
Toss well and add salt and pepper.
(If too dry, add a little more mayonnaise.)

title: beef stew
directions: Brown meat (salt to taste).
Brown onions and add to meat. Cover with water and simmer in covered pan until meat is almost tender.
Add the rest of the ingredients and continue cooking until meat is tender and flavors are blended.
Thicken slightly.
Serve with toasted crackers or hard rolls, iced tomato juice and a light dessert.

title: hot brown sugar sauce
directions: Mix together and bring to a boil.
Serve over white cake.

title: chocolate delight pie
directions: Mix together and spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 400°.
Cool.

title: thelma treynor's fudge
directions: Melt chocolate in a saucepan.
Combine sugar, flour and salt and add to melted chocolate.
Gradually add milk.
Boil slowly in a covered sauce pan for two minutes.
Remove cover and boil until the mixture forms a soft ball in cold water (232°).
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and butter.
Beat at high speed with mixer for 3 to 5 minutes.
Pour into greased pie plate.

title: zucchini squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease an 11 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Mix all ingredients.
Bake 25 to 35 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: chicken wild rice casserole
directions: Cook rice in 2 cups of chicken broth.
Do not pour off any excess broth after cooking rice.
Mix all ingredients well.
Bake in 3-quart casserole dish at 350° for 25 minutes.
Top with 1 can French fried onion rings and heat approximately 5 minutes.

title: pastor bill's favorite country fried ham and red eye gravy
directions: *Ham is best when sliced thin.

title: beef stew
directions: Use covered roasting pan.
Put everything in at once.
Do not brown meat.
Once I have all the ingredients in the pan, I stir it to sort of mix all of it together.
Cover and bake at 250° for 4 hours or longer.
Take off cover and turn up heat about 15 minutes, until the stew is consistency you like best.

title: nikki's margaritas
directions: In a blender, add equal parts of beer, lemon juice, lime juice and tequila.
Add approximately 8 cubes of ice; blend again.
Add additional beer to make it thinner, if needed.
Salt the edge of glasses to be used, if desired.
Serve.

title: easy chicken fettuccine
directions: Mix all ingredients until melted.
Stir in chicken and fettuccine.
If dry, add chicken broth from cooked chicken.

title: shrimp buena vista
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Lightly oil a rack large enough to hold shrimp in a single layer.
Put the rack on a baking sheet and set aside.

title: kahlua chocolate cake
directions: Set oven to 350°. Grease and flour two 9-inch cake pans. Beat egg whites until soft peaks form. Gradually add the granulated sugar while beating; set aside. Cream shortening and brown sugar until fluffy. Add egg yolks one at a time, beating well after each. Sift flour, cocoa and soda together. Add them to the creamed mixture alternately with the coffee and Kahlua. Beat well after each addition. Fold egg whites into the batter. Bake for 30 to 35 minutes or until tests done. Cool for 10 minutes and remove to wire racks. Cool completely and frost.

title: easy corn flake cookies
directions: Bring syrup and sugar to a boil in a saucepan. Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter until smooth. Add corn flakes and stir until flakes are well coated.
Let cool in pan for 2 or 3 minutes. Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper to set. Makes 36 cookies.

title: hot water pie crust
directions: Pour water over shortening and beat creamy.
Add dry ingredients.
Chill.
Makes 4 large or 5 small crusts.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush Oreos.
Let margarine and cream cheese soften.
Mix milk, sugar and pudding together.
Mix in Cool Whip, cream cheese and margarine.
Put aside.
Line the bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan with half of the Oreos.
Pour the filling over this layer evenly. Put the remaining Oreos on top of the filling.
Let refrigerate for several hours.

title: lebanese chicken
directions: Salt and cinnamon chicken pieces. In a large skillet, melt the butter or margarine, then add the chicken and brown thoroughly on both sides. Add potatoes and onions. Add the tomato paste and water or the tomato sauce. Cover and simmer for 1 hour. Serve over Lebanese Rice. Add pine nuts.

title: baked apples
directions: Line a pan with the apple slices.
Mix together sugar, flour and water; pour this sauce over apples.
Sprinkle red hots all over in bottom.
Bake at 415° for 45 minutes.
Take from oven; add marshmallows and bake until they melt a little.
You can also cut recipe in half for smaller amount.

title: smoked turkey salad
directions: Mix ingredients in order listed; arrange lettuce on 8 plates. Make a small mound of salad mixture on each and garnish with strawberry fans.

title: special k bars
directions: Bring syrup and sugar to rolling boil.
Turn off heat and add peanut butter and cereal.
Press into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Melt in microwave the chocolate chips and butterscotch chips.
Spread over top of cereal mix.
Cut before cooled.

title: little pizzas
directions: Toast buns.
Add other ingredients. Place back in oven to melt cheese.
Goes good for kids parties.
They love them.

title: pumpkin nut bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 2 loaf pans or a Bundt pan.
In large bowl, cream shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Stir in eggs, pumpkin and water.
Blend in flour and remaining ingredients, adding nuts, fruits and raisins last and mixing well.

title: quick lasagna
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
In a large skillet, brown meat, stirring frequently.
Add onion soup mix, tomato sauce and water.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
In 2-quart oblong baking dish, alternate layers of noodles, meat sauce and cheese. Bake 15 minutes or until bubbly.

title: my cousin's chili
directions: Brown onion in a little bit of olive oil; set aside. Brown hamburger; drain. In a large pan, add onion, hamburger and all other ingredients. Stir well to mix ingredients together. Cook over slow heat for about 45 minutes. Serve with fresh French bread. Can top with grated Cheddar cheese.

title: chocolate cake cookies(boy are these easy!)
directions: Mix ingredients and refrigerate 1 hour.
Roll into balls. Cover with powdered sugar.
Bake at 350° for 7 to 10 minutes. Makes 2 to 3 dozen.

title: devil's food cake(cheap)
directions: Cream the sugar and shortening; add melted chocolate and pinch of salt.
Add whole eggs.
Alternate flour and baking powder with milk and vanilla.
Bake in moderate oven at 350°.
Ice with seven-minute icing with marshmallows added.

title: red lobster's cheese garlic biscuits
directions: Mix together Bisquick, milk and cheese until soft dough forms, about 30 seconds. Drop by spoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 450° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: vanilla fudge
directions: Mix and cook on low heat to firm ball stage, stirring constantly to keep from sticking and burning.
Remove from heat. Cool to lukewarm.
Beat.
Add nuts.
Pour in buttered pan.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Combine cake mix and oil; mix per package directions.
Add eggs and the mandarin oranges.
Beat until correct consistency. Pour into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake as directed on package.

title: pumpkin special
directions: Mix together the pumpkin, sugar, Eagle Brand milk, pumpkin pie spice and eggs.
Pour into greased, flat 3-quart Pyrex pan. Sprinkle cake mix over pumpkin mixture, carefully spreading so top is level.
Spread nuts over top of cake mix.
Carefully pour melted butter or oleo (I used oleo) over top so that it is very evenly distributed.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes and then 325° for 20 minutes, until evenly browned.
Cool completely.
Cut in squares and serve with Cool Whip as topping.
Can be prepared the day before.
Makes 24 servings.

title: crunchy sandwiches
directions: Melt butterscotch bits and peanut butter; add Rice Krispies. Spread half of mixture in 8 1/2 x 11-inch pan and press down.

title: country roast beef(makes 8 to 10 servings)
directions: Trim roast of excess fat, then pierce all over with fork.
In small bowl, mix together beer, vegetable oil, garlic, onion flakes, salt, pepper and liquid smoke flavoring.
Stir well. Place roast in deep bowl; pour beer marinade over roast.
Cover bowl with plastic wrap and refrigerate 1 to 2 hours, turning every half-hour or so, to marinate.
Transfer roast to microwave meat rack (set in baking dish, if necessary, to catch drippings). Return marinade to refrigerator temporarily.
Spread top of roast with Worcestershire sauce and sprinkle with beef bouillon granules.
Cover roast loosely with wax paper and zap at Low/Defrost (30% power) for 40 minutes.
Turn roast over; insert meat thermometer and zap 30 to 45 minutes longer at Low/Defrost or until thermometer registers 150°.

title: brown sugar fudge
directions: Cook until forms a soft ball in 1/4 cup cold water.
Beat until creamy.
Quickly add nuts and pour into buttered plate or pan.

title: dinner rolls
directions: Mix 3/4 cup of flour, sugar, salt and yeast.
Heat milk, water and margarine.
Add dry ingredients and beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Add 1/4 cup flour and beat for 2 more minutes on high speed.
Add remaining cup of flour.
Knead on floured board. Divide into 12 pieces and shape into balls.
Put into 8-inch cake pan; cover and place in cold oven with pan of boiling water.
Let dough rise about 30 minutes.
Remove water.
Uncover rolls and bake at 350° until brown.

title: slap your brains out biscuits
directions: To 1/2 cup warm water add 1 tsp. sugar.
Add pkg. dry yeast. Mix together and set aside for
5 minutes. Sift together dry ingredients.
Make a well in dry ingredients and add 2 cups buttermilk, 1/2 cup oil and the yeast mixture.
Mix well.
Cover bowl and put into refrigerator and use as needed.
Roll out and cut with biscuit cutter. Place in greased pan and bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: rice in heavy skillet
directions: Fry 5 minutes.
Add 2 cups broth or water and salt; boil covered 15 minutes.

title: new york state concord wine
directions: You will need a 1 gallon jug and a large balloon (very important).

title: cranberry tea
directions: Note:
Unsweetened or low calorie products may be used.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Coat chicken cutlets with bread crumbs.
Brown coated cutlets in a little oil until brown.
Coat baking dish with tomato sauce. Place cutlets in pan and put more tomato sauce on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
During last 10 minutes place Parmesan cheese on each cutlet.

title: deep dish pizza
directions: Brown ground meat; drain.
Add onions and green peppers.
Cook until tender.
Stir in tomatoes, pizza sauce and herb mix.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Heat oven to 425°.
Prepare pizza dough.
With greased fingers, press dough into bottom and halfway up sides of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with half of Mozzarella cheese and meat sauce.
Repeat with remaining cheese and meat sauce.
Top with grated Parmesan cheese.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.

title: fried rice
directions: In skillet, cook onions and green peppers until onions are clear.
Add rice.
Stir well.
Add bacon and eggs.
Heat through well until egg is cooked.

title: quick and easy apple cherry crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, place apple filling on one end of pan and cherry filling on the other end. Cover with cake mix, sprinkle cinnamon on apple side.
Pour melted margarine over cake mix.
Bake until golden brown, about 30 minutes.
Cool and serve or serve hot with vanilla ice cream.

title: slaw for sandwiches
directions: Boil 1 minute.
Cool.
Add to one head of grated cabbage.

title: coconut dream bars
directions: Combine crumbs, 1/3 cup margarine and sugar.
Pat mixture into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 5 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Combine coconut and condensed milk.
Spread over crust.
Return to oven and bake 15 minutes.
Remove from oven and cool for 5 minutes.
Melt chocolate chips with remaining margarine over low heat.
Pour melted mixture over all.
Allow to cool before cutting into bars.

title: chili
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain.
Add remaining ingredients, except potatoes; simmer.
Peel and dice potatoes (like for potato salad).
Cover with water; cook until tender.
Add undrained potatoes to ground beef mixture.
Simmer and serve.
May top with sour cream and grated cheese.
Serves 6.

title: sock-it-to-me cake
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add sour cream and nuts; mix well.
Pour half of batter into well-greased tube pan.
Sprinkle sugar and cinnamon mixture over top, then add remaining batter.
Bake 50 minutes at 350°.
Let cool 15 minutes before turning out of pan.

title: pink passion salad
directions: Mix salad dressing and whipped topping in a bowl.
Gently fold in remaining ingredients.
Spoon onto lettuce leaves to serve.

title: barbecups
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Brown beef and onion; drain.
Add barbecue sauce and brown sugar.
Place separated biscuits into muffin cups.
Scoop a tablespoon of mixture onto each biscuit. Top with cheese.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.

title: curried spaghetti
directions: Combine soups, milk and water and simmer 10 minutes on low heat.
In 1/4 cup lukewarm water, add curry powder, mushrooms with liquid, onion and herbs.
Simmer all together; add tuna fish and mix in cooked spaghetti.

title: chilled pumpkin soup
directions: Place stock and pumpkin in saucepan and bring to simmer; simmer 10 minutes until smooth. Add spices and simmer another 20 minutes.
Chill thoroughly and add cream when ready to serve; garnish with baguettes and cinnamon.

title: cheese ball
directions: Let cream cheese sit out for 1 hour.
Chop up desired amount of dried beef and green onions.
Mix all ingredients into cream cheese.
Make into ball.
Chill for at least 2 hours.

title: praline ice cream cake
directions: Melt butter in 3-quart pan.
Remove from heat.
Add ice cream, then eggs, flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and graham cracker crumbs.
Mix until smooth.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Mix sour cream and caramel topping and pour over warm cake.
Top with nuts.
Cut into squares.

title: broccoli quiche
directions: Beat eggs and milk well.
Add seasoning.
Brown meat, onions and pepper; drain.
Partly bake pie crust.
Layer meat and broccoli on bottom.
Add mushrooms.
Pour liquid (eggs and milk). Layer with cheese.
Bake until set, 45 minutes.
Remove from oven.

title: tortillas with layered dip
directions: Assemble in layers.
Cream together one 8 ounce cream cheese and one peeled and diced avocado.
Then cream together one 8 ounce cream cheese and 3 tablespoons salsa.
Then diced tomato, then sliced spring onions, shredded Cheddar cheese and diced black olives.
Serve with your favorite tortilla chips.

title: cheesy vegetable soup
directions: Saute onion in oleo.
Add water and veggies.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat, cover, simmer 10 minutes.
Add soup, milk, cheeses. Serve in hollowed out shepard's bread.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Peel potatoes; put in deep cold water until ready to prepare pancakes.
Grate potatoes; press out as much liquid as possible. Grate onions.
Blend potatoes with eggs, flour, salt and pepper. Add onions.
Heat 1 inch of oil in frypan.
Drop about 1 tablespoon of mixture into pan.
Fry; turn once when golden crisp on each side.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve with sour cream, sugar or applesauce.

title: pineapple cheese cake
directions: Beat eggs, cream cheese, sugar and salt.
Add vanilla and sour cream; fold in drained crushed pineapple.
Pour into graham crust. Sprinkle crushed graham crackers on top.
Bake 40 minutes at 375°.

title: banana pudding
directions: Layer sliced bananas and vanilla wafers in large serving bowl. Mix together sugar, flour, egg yolks, whole eggs, butter and salt in a saucepan.
Add milk and cook slowly until mixture thickens, stirring occasionally, approximately 20 minutes.
Cool for a few minutes and add vanilla.
Pour over bananas and wafers, alternating layers.

title: cheese spread
directions: Melt the Velveeta cheese.
Add other ingredients and mix well. Pour into a container and chill.

title: skimburgers
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Shape loosely into burgers.
Cook as you would any hamburger.
They freeze beautifully.

title: ham barbecue sauce
directions: Boil all ingredients for 1 to 2 minutes.
Pour over 1 to 2 pounds of cooked ham.
Serve on roll.

title: cocoa oatmeal cookies
directions: Sift flour, measure and resift twice with baking powder, salt, cocoa and sugar.
Combine beaten egg, milk and vanilla; add melted butter and shortening.
Mix thoroughly with the sifted dry ingredients, then stir in the rolled oats.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for 15 to 20 minutes. Makes 5 dozen.

title: cranberry banana nut bread
directions: Sift
together	dry ingredients.
Add everything.
Then fold in	cranberries,
bananas and nuts.
Stir just enough to moisten. Cook at 350° for 70 minutes in tube pan.

title: peanut butter pies
directions: Cream together cheese and butter.
Mix together with all ingredients and fill pie crusts and freeze.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix sugar and vinegar and pour over rest of ingredients and mix.
Let set overnight.

title: apricot chicken divine
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cover bottom of shallow baking pan with olive oil.
Meanwhile, shake chicken in a plastic bag filled with flour and salt until chicken is coated.
Place chicken in a single layer in the baking pan and bake for 25 minutes.
Combine apricot preserves, mustard and yogurt.
Spread apricot mixture on chicken and bake for 30 minutes more or until done.
Just before serving, brown almonds lightly in toaster oven.
Sprinkle almonds over chicken and serve over rice.
Serves 8. Per serving:
243 total calories; 11 sat-fat calories.

title: blue cheese walnut bites
directions: Cut cheese and butter into flour and pepper.
Add walnuts and egg yolks.
Knead and shape into 2 logs about 9 inches long.
Wrap and chill 2 hours.
Slice 1/4 inch thick.
Place 1 inch apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 8 - 10 minutes at 425°.

title: marinated mushrooms and artichokes
directions: Combine mushrooms and artichokes in a large bowl.
Combine olive oil and next 10 ingredients; stir well.
Pour marinade over mushrooms and artichokes, tossing gently to coat.

title: caramel frosting
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add brown sugar.
Boil over low heat for 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add milk and keep stirring until mixture boils.
Remove from heat and let cool down.
Add enough sifted sugar to make spreading consistency, beating well after each addition.
(If icing gets too stiff while icing cake, just add a little milk to make it spreading consistency.)
Add pecans or press on sides of cake.
Makes enough icing for a sheet cake.
Double for a layer cake.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Mix cookie dough according to directions and press into a pizza pan.
Bake as directed.
Cool.
Put bananas in reserved pineapple juice.
Spread Cool Whip on crust.
Arrange sliced fruit starting with strawberries around the outside, then the bananas, kiwi, pineapple, mandarin oranges, then finish with cherry pie filling in the center.

title: barbara's german apple cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients in large bowl with a fork.
Mix sugar, eggs, oil and vanilla in smaller bowl with whisk.
Add wet ingredients to dry and mix thoroughly by hand.
Add apples and walnuts; mix well.
Pour into greased 10-inch round spring-form pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Cool thoroughly. Top with powdered sugar before serving.

title: potato corn chowder(microwave)
directions: Microwave-safe bowl, cook bacon at Full power until crisp, about 2 to 3 minutes.
Add potatoes, onion and garlic; stir to coat with bacon drippings.
Cover bowl with plastic wrap.
Microwave at Full power 5 minutes.
Add broth and red pepper; cover.
Return to microwave and cook until potatoes are tender, about 8 to 10 minutes.

title: easy peach pie
directions: Combine cream cheese, sugar and extract.
Beat until smooth; fold in La Creme and peaches.
Pour into crust.
Chill about 3 hours.
Makes 6 servings.

title: graham cracker cookies
directions: Place 24 graham crackers on cookie sheet.
Keep remaining crackers for top.
In saucepan combine the butter or margarine, brown sugar, milk, beaten egg and salt.
Bring to a boil and remove from heat.
Add vanilla, coconut, nuts and 1 cup graham cracker crumbs.
Spread over crackers in pan.
Cover with remaining 24 crackers.
Frost as you like.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and add other ingredients except croutons.
Mix well and top with croutons.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: green rice
directions: Mix all ingredients well in a 2-quart buttered casserole. Bake 1 hour in a 350° oven.

title: refrigerator kahlua cake
directions: Grease an oblong Pyrex dish with butter.
In a skillet over low heat, mix 1 stick butter, pecans and flour.
Stir in skillet until butter melts, pecans toast and flour browns slightly. Spread in Pyrex dish on bottom and sides as for crust.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes; set to cool.

title: italian french dressing
directions: Put in quart jar.
Shake well.
Chill overnight or several hours.
Save up to 1 1/2 months, no longer.

title: west virginia stew
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Add other ingredients and simmer one hour.

title: yellow squash casserole
directions: Saute squash and onion in 2 tablespoons oleo in a large skillet for 5 minutes or until tender.
Stir in soup, water chestnuts, salt and pepper.
Pour into a lightly greased 2-quart shallow baking dish.
Combine breadcrumbs and 2 tablespoons oleo. Mix well, sprinkle over top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: bakery sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar and butter. Add egg and flavorings, mixing thoroughly. Sift together dry ingredients. Add to creamed mixture. Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours or overnight.

title: spinach dumplings
directions: Cook spinach thoroughly, seasoning with salt and pepper to taste.
Squeeze dry and chop up finely.
Melt butter in skillet over moderate heat.
Add spinach and onion, stirring constantly, for 2 to 3 minutes, until most of the moisture is absorbed.
Add Ricotta cheese and cook 3 to 4 minutes longer, mixing well. Remove from heat and let cool.

title: good cold fudge topping
directions: Combine milk, cocoa, sugar and salt in medium saucepan. Allow to boil one minute.
Remove
from
heat and add oleo and vanilla. Mix well.
Cool.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Put chopped pecans and coconut in bottom of a 10 x 14-inch pan.
Prepare German chocolate cake mix according to directions on the box and pour over pecans and coconut.
Soften cream cheese at room temperature.

title: rum sauce
directions: Heat water and milk in a small saucepan;
combine sugar, cornstarch and salt, stir into the heated milk until smooth;
add butter;
cool.

title: black russian cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 40 minutes in a Bundt pan, greased and floured.
Remove from pan and pour over the glaze.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Let Jell-O firm slightly. Fold in crushed pineapple, celery, cranberries and chopped nuts. Let become firmly set and serve in squares on lettuce leaf.

title: prune cake
directions: Soak prunes as usual and cut to raisin size.
Cover with boiling water and cook until tender.

title: snowball cake
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 4 tablespoons of water.
Add 1 cup boiling water and cool.
Add sugar, salt, pineapple and juice.
Cool in refrigerator until partially set.
Add 2 packages of Dream Whip (beaten stiff).
Line a 4-quart size bowl with waxed paper.
Break cake in small pieces to cover bottom of bowl.
Layer with gelatin mixture, press into cake until all is used; refrigerate overnight. Turn into plate; remove waxed paper.
Frost with 1 package of Dream Whip (not too stiff).
Cover with coconut.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Combine oil, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Add apples.
Sift together flour, soda, salt and cinnamon and stir into first mixture by hand.
Do not user mixer.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Use either tube or rectangular pan.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Heat butter in skillet and cook shrimp for 5 minutes by shaking pan.
Sprinkle the
shrimp
with 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper and
place
on warmed serving platter.
To the remaining butter in
skillet, add 2 cloves garlic, chopped and parsley.
Stir for 30 seconds and pour over shrimp.
Serve with lemon wedges.

title: chocolate chip pudding cookies
directions: Mix flour with baking soda.
Combine margarine, the sugars, pudding mix and vanilla in large mixer bowl; beat until smooth and creamy.
Beat in eggs.
Gradually add flour mixture; then stir in chips and nuts (batter will be stiff).
Drop from teaspoon onto greased baking sheet, about 2 inches apart.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 7 dozen.

title: meat sauce for spaghetti
directions: Use 1/2 pound of meat per person.
Saute onion and bell pepper in small amount of grease until tender (not too brown). Chop onion and bell pepper fine.
Add meat (season with salt and pepper before cooking).
Cook meat until it turns brown.
Add chili powder and Worcestershire sauce to taste (try 1 tablespoon of each).
Add tomato paste and water until right thickness.
Cook over low heat for about 1 1/2 hours.

title: chicken orin
directions: In a 10-inch baking dish, mix together rice and mix, soup and water.
Gently fold in drained vegetables.
Cover with wax paper. Cook on High 5 minutes.
Stir.
Place chicken on top of rice mixture.
Put a small amount of soy sauce on each piece of chicken. Cover with lid or wax paper.
Microwave on High for 10 minutes. Turn chicken pieces over.
Cover and continue to cook on High for 10 minutes or until chicken is tender.

title: ham roll-ups
directions: Mix softened cream cheese, horseradish and olives.
Add 2 tablespoons of milk or more to mix.
Spread on ham slices.
Roll up tight.
Use toothpicks to hold.
Chill, then cut with sharp knife.
Serve on party crackers.

title: chocolate peanut butter ritz crackers
directions: Take 1 package of chocolate bark.
Place in large bowl and microwave for 1 1/2 to 3 minutes until smooth and creamy.
Take 2 Ritz crackers and spread peanut butter as if to make a sandwich. Dip the "sandwich" into the melted bark.
Place on wax paper after dipped.
Let cool for about 15 to 25 minutes.

title: chocolate pie or pudding(microwave)
directions: Heat milk for 3 minutes in a 2-quart Pyrex bowl on High.
In another bowl, mix sugar, cornstarch, cocoa and water.
Add egg yolks and mix.
Pour into hot milk and microwave on High 2 minutes.
Stir; cook 1 1/2 minutes.
Stir; cook 1 1/2 minutes. Stir.
When thick, add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Spread with meringue.

title: wilted lettuce
directions: Wash and drain lettuce.
Tear into small pieces; add onion. Saute bacon until crisp.
Remove from pan and crumble over lettuce.
Pour off all but 1/4 cup of the bacon fat in the frypan; add sugar, vinegar and salt and pepper to taste.
Bring to a boil and pour over the lettuce.
Toss.

title: light and heavenly salad
directions: Mix altogether and chill at least 6 to 8 hours.

title: crunchy jumbo cookies
directions: Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Set aside.
Measure margarine and sugar into large mixing bowl; beat until well blended and smooth.
Add egg and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add sifted dry ingredients; mix until combined.
Stir in Rice Krispies and chocolate morsels.
Drop by level measuring tablespoons onto lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake in a moderate oven (350°) for about 12 minutes or until lightly browned.
Remove from baking sheets.
Yields about 3 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: tomato-corn casserole
directions: Place half of the bacon in the bottom of a 2-quart casserole and top with the bread crumbs, 1 cup chopped tomatoes, 1/2 can chopped chilies and 1 1/2 cups corn; salt and pepper to taste. Layer 1 cup chopped tomatoes, 1/2 can chopped chilies and 1 1/2 cups of corn; salt and pepper to taste.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Mix all together
by hand and put in unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve warm.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Cook eggplant in boiling water for 5 minutes; drain well. Place in a lightly greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Add Mozzarella cheese and top with marinara sauce.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and bake an additional 5 minutes.

title: jeff baker's authentic italian lasagne
directions: Brown meat slowly and break into small pieces in frypan.
Add bell pepper, onion and mushrooms.
Spoon off fat (drain).
Add garlic, basil, salt, tomatoes and paste.
Simmer for 30 minutes. Remove garlic.

title: chili bean dip
directions: Brown ground beef and drain. Stir in soup, tomatoes with green chilies and onions; simmer on low heat until heated through. Garnish with cheese and olives. Keep warm.

title: broccoli and mushroom chowder
directions: Cut broccoli in 1/2-inch pieces.
Steam in 1/2 cup water until tender.
Do not drain.
In a large pan over medium heat, melt butter.
Add flour; cook, stirring constantly, 2 to 4 minutes. Don't let it brown.
Stir in chicken broth.
Bring to a boil; turn heat to low.
Add broccoli, mushrooms, half and half and seasonings.
Heat through but do not boil.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix and fill the loaf of bread.

title: shoepeg corn salad
directions: Mix together and refrigerate overnight before serving.

title: tomato soup cake
directions: Mix cake according to package directions, substituting tomato soup for liquid, adding soda.
Fold raisins in and cook according to directions.
Good with lemon butter frosting or serve warm in squares topped with lemon sauce.

title: pig lickin cake
directions: This makes two larger layers or 3 medium layers.

title: italian crescent casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Drain.
Stir in sauce mix and tomato sauce.
Heat until bubbly.
Combine cheese and sour cream.
Pour hot meat mixture in ungreased 12 x 8 or 13 x 9-inch dish.
Spoon cheese mixture over meat.
Separate crescent dough into 2 rectangles.
Place over cheese mixture.
Melt butter and pour over rolls, then sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 18 to 25 minutes, or until deep golden brown.
Cut into squares.

title: cappuccino mix
directions: Combine and mix well.
Store in airtight container.
To serve, add 3 tbsp. mix to 6 oz. boiling hot water or milk, stir well.

title: pretzel jello salad
directions: Crush enough pretzels to make 2 cups.
Put in a colander and shake to remove some salt.
Add butter and 3 tablespoons sugar. Place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.
Cool.

title: chicken breasts deluxe
directions: Line casserole with sliced, chipped beef.
Wrap chicken breasts in strips of bacon.
Place on chipped beef.
Mix soup, consomme and sour cream together.
Pour over chicken.
Cook slowly at 225° for about 2 hours, adding bread crumbs and paprika at last to give a pretty brown crust.

title: easy frozen salad
directions: Mix all together and freeze in individual molds.

title: wiener wraps
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Cut crescent roll sections into thirds lengthwise. Wrap each sausage with a section of dough, rolling from shortest side of triangle to opposite point. Place point side down on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 10 to 13 minutes or until golden brown. Great dipped in hot mustard.

title: pork and apple pie
directions: Cook bacon in an ovenproof 12-inch skillet until crisp. Remove with a slotted spoon to paper towels to drain.
In drippings, saute onions until tender.
Remove with a slotted spoon and set aside.
Dust pork lightly with flour.
Brown a third at a time in drippings, adding oil if needed.
Remove from the heat and drain.

title: aunt helen's meat loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a bowl combine ingredients; mix well. Shape into a loaf.
Place in a baking dish.
Bake 1 hour.

title: danish pastry
directions: Part 1:
Mix 1 stick margarine, 1 cup flour and 1 tablespoon cold water like pie crust.
Roll between hands into a rope.
Lay on cookie sheet. Press out with hands until thin, 5 to 6-inches wide.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients. Roll into the shape of a ball. Roll in pecans on waxed paper.

title: cranberry cake with hot caramel sauce
directions: Sift together flour, sugar and baking powder in a bowl.
Cut in butter or margarine with a fork.
Combine until mixture resembles cornmeal.
Then stir in milk and cranberries.

title: quick chicken broccoli oriental
directions: In 10-inch pan over medium heat in hot oil, cook chicken 1/2 at a time, until browned.
Add onion and pepper; cook 5 minutes until vegetables are done.
Stir in soup and soy sauce.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 5 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Serve over rice.
Prep time: 10 minutes.
Cook time:
20 minutes.

title: big, big banana pudding
directions: In large bowl, combine the 6 cups milk with 2 boxes pudding mix.
Mix thoroughly and place in fridge to firm up.
In another large mixing bowl, mix the cream cheese (softened) with mixer. Add Eagle Brand milk until smooth and stir in vanilla.
Fold 1 container Cool Whip into pudding mix, then follow with cream cheese mixture and sliced bananas.
Stir bananas in well.
Arrange vanilla wafers in a big, big or two regular bowls and alternate with layers of pudding mixture.
Top with other container of Cool Whip.

title: jalapeno corn bread
directions: In large bowl, mix corn bread mix, cheese, onion, peppers, juice and garlic.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add oil, salt, milk and corn.
Mix together well. Pour batter into a slightly greased 9 x 13-inch or 9-inch pan; bake at 375° for 30 to 45 minutes or until golden brown.
Serves 12.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown meat; drain fat.
Add all ingredients (finely chopping onion).
Cook until hot, spoon on hamburger buns and enjoy.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots until barely tender; drain and cool. (I sometimes use canned carrots.)
Mix seasonings, soup, onion and bell pepper. Pour over carrots.
Place in covered bowl and refrigerate 12 hours before serving.
Keeps well for at least a week.

title: amish sugar cookies
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients, beat well.
Add eggs and vanilla. Mix well.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well again.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet and flatten slightly with a fork (dip the fork in ice water to keep from sticking).
Sprinkle with sugar or decorate with half pecan (optional).
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 7 dozen.

title: overnight salad
directions: Mix together lettuce, cauliflower, peas and onion.
Set aside.

title: hermits
directions: Beat shortening, sugar, egg and molasses.
Sift dry ingredients and add to mixture.
Mix well and add raisins.
Using wet hands, shape dough into long 1-inch thick ropes and place on cookie sheets flattened out a little.
Sprinkle with granulated sugar.
Bake for approximately 9 minutes at 375° until dough cracks on top.
Remove immediately from oven and cool.
Cut into 3-inch pieces.

title: corn pie
directions: Beat slightly eggs, milk, butter, salt, pepper and drained corn.
Pour into buttered 1-quart casserole dish and bake, uncovered, 45 minutes in 325° oven.

title: sloppy joe's
directions: Saute onion and green
pepper
in
small amount of oil. Add meat and cook until
brown.
Drain
oil
from meat and add rest of ingredients.
Salt
and pepper to taste.
Cook slowly, until mixture thickens.
Serve on buns.
Serves 30.

title: honey glazed rock cornish hens
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Place hens skin side up in large baking dish. Sprinkle with salt and add chicken broth. Cover tightly with aluminum foil and bake for 30 minutes.

title: candied yams
directions: Place sweet potatoes in large saucepan.
Add sugar, lemon juice, water and lemons (cut in halves).
Stir to dissolve sugar. Pour over potatoes.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Cook over medium heat until potatoes are tender.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: apple betty
directions: Peel and slice apples.
Put in an 8 x 8-inch casserole dish. Combine sugar, flour, spices and salt.
Cut in butter until mixture is crumbly.
Sprinkle mixture on top of apples.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until apples are tender and topping is crisp.

title: 5 pound potato salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and season to taste. Refrigerate.

title: shrimp egg rolls
directions: Mix cornstarch, soy sauce and white pepper; set aside.
Heat wok.
Add 2 tablespoons oil; rotate to coat sides.
Add cabbage, bean sprouts, shrimp, onion and five spice powder.
(You can also add 1 teaspoon minced garlic for extra flavor.)
Cook, stirring, for about 2 minutes.
Add cornstarch mixture and blend well. Cool.

title: lemon custard cake
directions: Tear the cake into bite-size pieces.
Place in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
In a mixing bowl, combine the pudding mix, milk and sour cream.
Beat until thickened, about 2 minutes. Spread over cake.
Spoon pie filling on top.
Chill until serving. Yields 12 to 16 servings.

title: broccoli pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Lightly grease 8 x 8-inch Pyrex pan.
Mix broccoli, onion, green pepper and cheese in pan.
Beat remaining ingredients on high for 15 seconds.
Pour over ingredients in pan. Bake for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt butter and put into dish.
Add both cans of corn and juice from corn.
Mix well.
Add the package of corn muffin mix and mix well.
Pour into cake pan.
Bake at 350° for approximately 55 to 60 minutes.

title: pancakes
directions: Mix all ingredients and cook on a preheated griddle over medium heat.

title: chili rellenos casserole
directions: Lay cut-up peppers and cheese in casserole.
Beat eggs and milk; beat in flour and salt.
Pour over cheese and chiles.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until done.

title: corn crisp catfish
directions: Pour milk into bowl.
Combine crumbs, salt and pepper in another bowl.
Dip steaks in milk; roll in crumb mixture.
Arrange in shallow pan.
Bake in preheated oven for 20 minutes.

title: dirt cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and cream cheese.
Make pudding and add to cream cheese mixture.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Cover bottom of 9 x 12-inch pan with 1/2 Oreo crumbs.
Add Cool Whip mixture.
Cover with remaining crushed cookies on top.
Chill overnight.
Serve.

title: tradd street chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in a lightly greased 13 x 9-inch casserole dish.
Bake at 350° until bubbly, 20 to 30 minutes. Serves 8.

title: pineapple pound cake
directions: Have ingredients at room temperature.
Cream shortening, butter and sugar; add eggs, 1 at a time.
Beat thoroughly.
Add flour alternately with milk.
Add pineapple and vanilla. Beat 4 minutes by clock. Pour into large tube pan (greased and floured). Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours. Do not preheat oven.
Place cake in cold oven.

title: corn muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Grease muffin tins and warm in oven. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Line casserole with tortilla chips.
Place chicken on top of chips.
Combine other ingredients except cheese and pour over chicken.
Top mixture with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Press pecans evenly in pie shell. Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs; beat. Add milk and vanilla; beat. Pour into pie shell over pecans. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: club sandwiches
directions: Separate the bread in half and lay side by side.
Then spread the margarine on both pieces of bread, then pour some Italian dressing on the buttered bread and spread all over.
Lay one side of the bread to the side.
Then put the lettuce on first, then the onions, tomatoes and then put the lunch meat on top of that and then the two cheeses.
Put the other half of bread on top of the other one and cut into 2-inch slices and wrap individually with Saran Wrap and refrigerate until ready to serve.
Just place on a plate and let your guest just take one.

title: microwave chicken
directions: Crush the crackers, melt the butter and cut up the chicken. Dip the chicken pieces in butter, then roll in cracker crumbs. Place on a bacon rack, bone down, meaty part out.

title: greek artichoke spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Smooth to slightly chunky.
Bake in glass casserole dish at 350° for 20 minutes or until golden brown. Top with remaining olives and serve with toast points, crackers or fresh veggies.

title: chocolate chip cookie cake
directions: Slice one package of the cookies and layer in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Thoroughly mix the other ingredients and pour over layer of cookie dough.
Slice the other package of cookies and layer over mixed ingredients.
Bake approximately 1 hour at 350°.
This dries out easily, so keep covered very tightly to keep it moist.

title: peppy dried beans
directions: Cover the beans with water and soak overnight or at least 6 hours.
Drain.
Add ham, onion, celery, bell pepper, parsley, bay leaves and garlic.
Cover with water and bring to a boil.
Reduce to low heat and cook for about 2 hours. Add the butter, black pepper, salt, Worcestershire sauce and Tabasco sauce.
Continue cooking over low heat for an additional hour or until tender. Remove bay leaves before serving.

title: curried fruit
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits in fourths.
Roll into balls.
Roll in cinnamon and sugar mixture.
Lay in sprayed angel food cake pan or Bundt pan.
Melt butter.
Add 1 cup sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon. Cook until bubbly.
Pour over rolls in pan.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Boil potatoes, carrots and onion.
Add soups and broccoli. Add cheese and let simmer until melted.
Season to taste.
Very good.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients well.
In another bowl, combine the pumpkin, sugar, salt and cinnamon. Fold the two mixtures together and pour into a greased tube pan. Bake at 325° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: nibblin fish snack mix
directions: Combine dry ingredients, mixing well.
Drizzle with oil until well coated.
Store in airtight container.
Makes about 12 cups of mix.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together and store in a plastic or glass container.
When mixing to drink, boil water and put 2 tablespoons of tea mix into cup.
Add boiling water and stir.

title: hot sesame sticks
directions: Cream butter.
Add flour, cayenne, salt and sweet basil.
Mix until butter is completely blended into the flour mixture.
This may be done in the food processor, using the steel blade.
Blend in the egg and work dough with hands until mixture looks like cookie dough.
Add Parmesan cheese and blend well.

title: shrimp pie
directions: Melt butter over medium heat in a large Dutch oven.
Whisk in flour and cook, stirring constantly, until caramel colored.
Add onion and cook for five minutes, stirring often.
Add bell pepper, celery, garlic, parsley, green onion and bay leaf and continue cooking for 10 minutes.
Add seasoned salt, pepper, cream and brandy.
Cook for 5 minutes until mixture comes to a boil.
Add shrimp and simmer for 10 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Preheat oven to 300 degrees.
Place thawed pie shells on a cookie sheet.
Mound the shrimp mixture into the pie shells.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs and dot with butter.
Bake 20 minutes until light brown.

title: mission friend punch
directions: Dissolve sugar in water.
Stir in Kool-Aid, ginger ale and pineapple juice.
Add crushed ice and serve.

title: corn flake treats
directions: Heat sugar and syrup until it boils and sugar melts. Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter and corn flakes. Place on wax paper with teaspoon. Roll into balls with hands, if desired, or leave as they are. Yields about 60 candies.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Place cabbage in a 3-quart shallow casserole or Pyrex baking pan.
Pour the milk over.
Sprinkle with a few caraway seed and minced onion.
Spread crumbs over cabbage.
Dot with butter.
Cover with lid or foil.
Bake in a preheated oven for 30 minutes. Uncover and bake 20 minutes more or until crumbs are lightly browned.

title: seafood quickie
directions: Put all ingredients in rice cooker.
Stir; cook.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cook noodles.
Combine beef, onions and seasonings and brown. Stir in soup, sour cream and cream of chicken soup.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: it's-a-snap cheesecake
directions: In large bowl, mix Knox and sugar; add boiling water and stir until gelatin is completely dissolved.
With mixer, beat in cream cheese and vanilla until smooth.
Pour into prepared crust; chill until firm, about 2 hours.
Top, if desired, with fresh or canned fruit.
Makes about 8 servings.

title: delightful crab salad
directions: I find	this
crabmeat	to
be very moist, so I squeeze some of	 the
liquid	out;
combine	it
with
the
other ingredients.
Toss well and place in covered dish and chill at least 2
hours.
Serve
on crisp lettuce with crackers of your choice.
Serves 6 to 8.
Delicious!

title: festive shrimp appetizer
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients.
Lightly toss until well blended.
Cover and refrigerate to allow all flavors to blend overnight.
Serve chilled.
Yields approximately 7 cups.

title: ann's apple butter
directions: Prepare apples and cook until tender; put in blender.
Mix in sugar and spice.
Cover and cook in oven at 350° until thick. Stir occasionally.
Put in jars and seal.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Drain blueberries and pineapple, reserving liquid.
Add enough water to liquid to make 1 cup and add to gelatin.
Pour into 2-quart flat pan and chill until firm.
Blend cream cheese, sour cream, sugar and vanilla. Spread over jello.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Refrigerate.

title: braided yeast bread
directions: Put flour in a bowl.
Move flour out of center.
Pour in warm milk.
Add sugar and yeast.
Let rise for at least 20 minutes until bubbles are forming.
Add the other ingredients.
Knead into a dough until it comes easily off your hands.
Let rise until double the size.

title: party appetizers
directions: Brown sausage and hamburger.
Drain off fat.
Chop cheese and stir until melted.
Spread on rye bread and freeze.
When ready to serve, bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: baked chicken in wine gravy
directions: Rinse chicken and pat dry.
Place in a 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Add mixture of soup and water; top with French fried onions.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour.
Add wine.
Bake for 1 hour longer.
Serve chicken with gravy over rice or noodles. Yield:
4 servings.

title: have anothers
directions: Melt chips together in saucepan and add corn flakes until thick.
Spread on greased pan and chill.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: raspberries st. moritz
directions: Place cake slice or shells on individual serving plates. Combine thawed raspberries and almond extract.
Top each cake slice with a scoop of ice cream, about 1/4 cup raspberries and a generous spoonful of whipped topping.
Makes 4 servings.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Cut up chicken in small pieces.
Put in a 13 x 9-inch pan. Add together soup, Ro-Tel and 1 cup of broth together.
Pour over chicken.
Dice up onion, pepper and cheese; put on next.
Add crushed chips.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Combine brown sugar, flour and salt in a double boiler.
Heat milk and slowly stir into flour and sugar.
Cook until thickened.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all together until well blended.
Put 1 heaping tablespoonful in cup, fill with boiling water and stir.

title: old fashioned banana pudding
directions: Separate eggs.
Save egg whites in bowl.
Mix egg yolks, milk and flavoring and sugar in pot.
Cook over medium heat.
Add butter; cook until boiling hard.
Add cut up bananas and thicken with cornstarch.
Add wafers.
Pour in pan.
Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form.
Add 3 tablespoons sugar; spread over pudding, mix and brown.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Press cookie dough over sprayed or greased pizza pan.
Bake at 350° until brown.
Let cool.
Mix 1/2 cup sugar, vanilla and cream cheese.
Spread over cooked and cooled cookie dough.
Slice fruit desired such as bananas, kiwi and strawberries or pineapple, bananas and strawberries.
Arrange fruit over cream cheese mixture. Mix orange juice, 2/3 cup sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Bring to boil and let boil for 1 minute.
Pour over fruit mixture.
Chill.

title: blueberry crunch
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch baking dish and layer in the following order:
pineapple, blueberries, 3/4 cup sugar, dry cake mix, melted margarine, pecans and 1/4 cup sugar.
Cook in preheated 325° oven for 35 to 40 minutes or until brown on top.
Serve warm or cold.
Delicious with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: bacon breakfast casserole
directions: Melt butter in 1 quart casserole and add bread cubes. Sprinkle with cheese and toss well.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Bring to a boil the margarine, cocoa and water.
Add flour, sugar and salt. Beat with hand mixer, then add sour cream, eggs and soda;
beat.
Bake at 375° for 22 minutes in a greased and floured 11 x 16 x 1-inch pan.

title: jogging in a jug
directions: Mix well and refrigerate.

title: after church roast
directions: Brown roast. Add onion soup mix and mushroom soup on top of roast. Add water to roast; bake, covered, in 300° to 325° oven for 2 hours before adding potatoes and carrots. Finish cooking while at church.

title: chili
directions: Brown meat and onion in frying pan.
After browning, mix in chili.
Mix and combine in large pot the beans and tomato soup, adding about 2 cans water, then put in meat and onion.
Simmer for about 1 hour.

title: macaroni and tuna casserole
directions: Cook and drain Creamettes macaroni.
Place in casserole dish. Add soup, tuna and peas.
Mix.
Top with cheese and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: In large bowl beat eggs and oil until well blended.
Rinse seeds out of chiles, chop chiles fine and add to eggs.
Add corn, sour cream, corn meal, baking powder, salt and 1/2 cup of the cheese.
Stir until thoroughly blended.
Pour into greased 9-inch square or round pan.
Sprinkle remaining 1/2 cup cheese evenly over the top.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour or until well done and crust is brown.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: fudge brownie pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425 degrees.
Melt margarine in saucepan. Remove from heat and add cocoa, sugar, corn syrup, vanilla, salt, and flour;
stir until well blended.
Mix in eggs and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Set pie on baking sheet and bake 5 minutes. Reduce heat to 350 degrees and bake an additional 25 to 35 minutes.
Pie will be done when a toothpick inserted in the middle of the pie comes out clean.

title: super fruit salad
directions: Cut apples in small pieces.
Add Cool Whip so apples do not get brown, then add grapes and nuts.
Cut up Snickers bars and add.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Mix hot
milk,
shortening and sugar.
Cool to lukewarm. Soften yeast in 1/4
cup
lukewarm
water and add to first mixture.
Add 2 cups
flour and mix well.
Cover and set in a warm place until doubled
in bulk.
Mix salt, soda and baking powder with 2 more cups
flour
and
add
to first mixture.
Mix well. Cover and store
in refrigerator until ready for use.
Shape as desired and allow
to double in bulk before baking.
Bake rolls at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Mix eggs, milk, flour, sugar and salt together.
Mix well. Heat oil or shortening.
Holding finger over bottom of funnel, fill funnel with about 1/3 cup batter.
Hold funnel near surface of hot oil; remove finger and drop batter into oil using a circular movement from center outward to form a spiral cake about 3-inches in diameter.
Fry cake until brown; remove from grease. Drain.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar and serve hot.

title: mexican chicken(low-fat)
directions: Put taco seasoning in plastic bag.
Put chicken in the bag and shake until chicken is coated.
Place chicken in casserole sprayed with cooking spray and bake in a preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes. Top each piece with 1/4 cup salsa and 1 tablespoon nonfat sour cream. Serve.
Makes 4 servings.

title: mushroom-stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove stems from mushrooms.
Chop into 1/4-inch pieces; set aside.
In heavy skillet, heat butter.
Add mushroom caps.
Saute over high heat for 30 seconds on each side or until just browned. Arrange bottom sides up on a heatproof serving tray.
To skillet, add stems.
Saute over high heat 2 minutes.
Add basil, salt and cream.
Heat to boiling.
Simmer until cream if reduced by half and slightly thickened.
Stir in cheeses.
Spoon mixture into mushroom caps.
Place under preheated broiler about 6 inches from heat.
Broil until heated through and lightly browned.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, stir contents of all cans together.
Add rice and stir again.
Pour into foil lined baking pan, approximately 9 1/2 x 14-inch.
Place chicken on top, skin side up.
Bake 2 to 2 1/2 hours in 350° oven.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Saute first 5 ingredients slowly for 1/2 hour.
Add ground beef and fry until delicate brown, without lid.
Drain any fat. Add tomato paste, basil, salt and pepper.
Add enough water to make thin.
Let simmer slowly until thickens, about 1 hour or more.
You can use this for stuffed peppers, also.

title: grape jelly
directions: In large saucepan, combine grape and pectin; bring to a rolling boil.
Stir in sugar and return to a rolling boil for one (1) minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and skim off foam.
Pour into hot sterilized jars, leaving 1/4 inch head space; adjust caps.
Process in boiling water for five (5) minutes. Yields about five (5) half pints.

title: barbecue meatballs(part iii)
directions: Mix thoroughly beef, sausage, crumbs and egg.
Shape into 24 meatballs.
In skillet, brown meatballs; pour off fat.
Add sauce mixture.
Cover; cook over low heat 20 minutes or until done.
Stir often.
Serve with rice.
Makes 6 servings.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Blend mayonnaise, lemon juice and onion.
Add chicken, celery, almonds and water chestnuts; mix well.
Put into greased casserole.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serves 4 to 6.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Sift together and set aside flour, cinnamon, salt, soda and baking powder.
Mix together eggs, sugar, oil and vanilla.
To this mixture, add ground zucchini squash.
Then add alternately the sour cream and dry sifted ingredients previously set aside, mixing after each addition.
Add chopped nuts.
Put into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes or until done.

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease deep pie plate.
Brown the beef and onion, drain, stir in salt and pepper, spread in plate.
Beat milk, Bisquick and eggs until smooth.
Pour into plate, bake 25 minutes, top with tomatoes, sprinkle with cheese.
Bake until knife inserted in center comes out clean, 5 to 8 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: chocolate icing
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and milk in a heavy saucepan and bring to a boil over medium-high heat. Let boil while stirring occasionally for approximately 8 minutes, until at the soft-ball stage. Take off heat and add butter and vanilla. Beat in enough confectioners sugar until the desired spreading consistency. Great for yellow cakes and brownies.

title: cheese straws
directions: Cream butter; add cheese and blend well.
Add pepper and salt. Gradually add flour and mix well.
Use cookie press and shape. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: homemade chili
directions: Scramble meat and onion; cook until done, then drain fat off. Add beans, tomatoes and tomato sauce; let cook for about 15 minutes.
Add seasoning; stir and let simmer for about 5 minutes. Add ketchup; cook on low for 5 minutes more.
Makes enough for 12 servings.
Serve with soda or Ritz crackers.

title: strawberry congealed salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water.
Cool.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Place in refrigerator to set.
This salad will keep for several days.
Delicious.

title: bloomin' cupcakes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Line 18 muffin cups with paper baking cups. Stir the toffee chips into the cake batter; mix well and fill the baking cups 3/4 full. Bake for 20 to 22 minutes or until a wooden toothpick inserted in the center of the cupcakes comes out clean; cool completely.

title: thumbprint cookies
directions: Cream together thoroughly butter and sugar.
Add yolk and vanilla.
Add flour and salt.
Mix well.
Roll into 1-inch balls. Dip in slightly beaten egg white, then in finely chopped nuts. Place about 1 inch apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 5 minutes at 375°.
Remove from oven.
Quickly press thumb gently on top of each cookie.
Return to oven and bake 8 minutes longer.
Remove. Cool.
Fill dent with jelly or candied fruit.
Makes about 2 dozen cookies.

title: tuna roll
directions: Drain tuna and absorb oil with paper towels.
Get out most of oil.
Mix well with softened cream cheese and onion.
Roll in finely chopped pecans or walnuts.
Wrap in aluminum foil and store in refrigerator.
One tablespoon Worcestershire can be added.

title: steve's favorite salsa stir-fry
directions: Combine picante sauce (salsa), soy sauce, water and cornstarch. Mix and set aside.
Heat one tablespoon oil in wok and stir-fry beef, garlic and ginger on medium-high until done.
Remove beef and set aside.
Add last tablespoon oil to wok and stir-fry mushrooms, broccoli and bell pepper.
When vegetables are crisp-tender, add picante mixture, beef and green onions.
Cook and stir one minute until sauce boils and thickens.
Serve over rice.
Makes 4 servings, calories 201, fat 8 g.

title: my best chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix shortening, butter and sugars; mix well.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat again until light and fluffy.
Mix together dry ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture.
(Stir the dry ingredients in, do not use mixer at this point.)
Add one package chocolate chips.
Make round balls (1 teaspoonful) and bake on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: no salt seasoning
directions: Mix together and use in place of salt.
Yields 1/3 cup.

title: glazed pork tenderloin
directions: In a blender, combine the fresh jalapeos with 1/2 cup of the cilantro, the garlic, lime juice, water, 1/2 teaspoon of the ground cumin and a generous pinch of salt. Puree the jalapeo-cumin sauce until smooth.

title: gertrude's squash casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine all ingredients and pour into a greased casserole dish.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes.
Top with sliced almonds before serving, if desired.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: anytime cucumber slices
directions: In a bowl, combine cucumbers, onions and dill. In a saucepan, combine sugar, vinegar and salt. Bring to a boil. Pour over cucumber mixture. Cover and chill 3 hours or overnight.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Combine all ingredients, except 3/4 cup peanut butter and frosting.
Spread mixture on buttered cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool slightly.
Spread 3/4 cup peanut butter on top.
When completely cool, spread with chocolate frosting.

title: barbecue lima beans
directions: Pour off some fat from bacon.
Mix limas and bacon together. Add mustard, ketchup and brown sugar.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour. May need more if it has been refrigerated.

title: turkey salami
directions: Mix all together; refrigerate 24 hours.
Wrap in foil; boil in water 1 hour.
Punch holes in foil to drain.
Re-wrap; refrigerate.
This is a diet salami, very good.

title: creamy beef dip
directions: Brown ground beef.
Set aside.
Mix together Ro-Tel tomatoes, cream of chicken soup and cheese.
Add ground beef.

title: crawfish fettucini
directions: Saute seasonings (onions, bell peppers, celery and garlic) in margarine.
Add crawfish and cook 10 minutes.
Add parsley, cream, flour and cheese.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Boil noodles and add to the mixture.
Sprinkle lightly with bread crumbs or Parmesan cheese.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spay pan with Pam
cooking spray.
Place crescent rolls on pizza pan and spread out to make crust.
Bake at 400° until brown. Cool.
Mix together
Miracle
Whip,
cream
cheese and dressing mix.
Spread on
baked
dough
and	top
with chopped vegetables and cheese.

title: peach pickles
directions: Peel peaches.
Boil sugar, vinegar, water and spices until a moderately thick syrup.
Add peaches, about a dozen at a time. Boil until tender enough to stick with a straw to the seed.
Stir occasionally.
Fill jars with peaches.
Continue until all peaches are cooked.
Fill jars with syrup and seal.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Begin 1 hour ahead:
In large bowl, combine first 6 ingredients with 3/4 cup cream; shape into 40 small meatballs.
On waxed paper, in about 1/4 cup flour, coat meatballs.
In 12-inch skillet over medium-high heat, in hot oil, brown meatballs well. Drain on paper towels.
Wipe skillet clean.
In same skillet over medium heat, melt butter or margarine.
Stir in 1 tablespoon flour until well blended and smooth.
Gradually stir in undiluted consomme and 1/2 cup cream; heat to boiling, stirring constantly. Add meatballs and bay leaf; simmer, covered, 15 minutes or until meatballs are tender.
Discard bay leaf.
Serve Swedish meatballs in chafing dish to keep hot.
Makes 40 appetizers.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes (should be still firm).
Cool and grate into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix the soup, butter, sour cream, onion and cheese together; pour over potatoes.
Top with crushed corn flakes (optional).
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Grease casserole dish.
Melt butter; stir in flour, salt, pepper and paprika until smooth.
Stir in milk.
Cook until thickened.
Pour over potatoes.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Cover and bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes longer or until potatoes are fork-tender.

title: cavatini
directions: Cook and drain pasta.
Mix all ingredients in large baking dish (14 x 11 x 2-inch).
Cover with foil and bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Remove foil and bake additional 10 to 15 minutes.

title: pizza pasta casserole
directions: You can use onions and green peppers if you like. Just add to beef while browning.

title: orange nut bread
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and baking soda. Stir in nuts and orange peel.
In small bowl beat eggs, milk, orange juice, and butter until smooth.
Stir into dry ingredients just until moistened.
Pour into 2 greased 8 x 4 x 2 inch loaf pans.

title: squash pickles
directions: Combine squash and onions.
Sprinkle with salt and set aside for 1 hour.
Combine vinegar, sugar, bell pepper rings and seed. Bring to a boil in a saucepan; add squash and onions and cucumbers. Bring to a boil again.
Put in jars and seal.
Better if chilled before serving.
Makes 4 pints.

title: big top casserole
directions: Cook noodles. Drain and rinse with cold water.
Brown burger, onions and green peppers in oil.
Add tomato sauce, cheese and seasoning.
Mix with noodles.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: sopaipilla mix
directions: Thoroughly mix dry ingredients, then add shortening and mix until it's dissolved.
Slowly add about 1 cup warm water and knead until smooth.
Your dough should be the consistency of pie dough or a little stiffer.
Cover dough with a damp cloth and let rise for about an hour.

title: cheesecake tarts
directions: You will need 2 1/2-inch baking cups (foil).

title: gingersnaps
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Roll into ball the size of a large walnut.
Roll in sugar.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 20 minutes.

title: squash garden casserole
directions: Cook squash, onions, garlic salt, pepper and brown sugar in small amount of salted water in saucepan until squash is tender; drain.
Add tomatoes; mix well.
Spoon into casserole.
Sprinkle with cheese and mixture of margarine and bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: cornish pasties
directions: Brown steak with onion, potatoes, carrots, celery, salt and pepper.
Place this mixture in crust; fold over and seal.
You will have a half moon shape.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes, then at 350° for 15 minutes.
Make sure you poke a hole in the center of each pasty to let the steam escape.
Make a gravy out of the juice left in the browning pan; use 2 tablespoons of flour for each cup of liquid.
Serve hot smothered in gravy.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix butter and sugar until smooth.
Add eggs and flour, 1 cup at a time.
Add mashed bananas (about 4).
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes in a greased pan.

title: banana cupcakes
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
