Add egg, milk, flour, baking powder and baking soda.
Add mashed bananas.
Bake at 350° for about 15 or 20 minutes.
Frost with your favorite buttercream frosting. Makes about 18 cupcakes.

title: "philly" cheese ball
directions: Combine cream cheese and salad dressing, mixing until well blended.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Chill.
Form into ball and roll in chopped nuts.
Serve with crackers.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Saute mushrooms and onion in butter.
Remove from pan.
Remove fat and bone from steak and cut into bite size pieces.
Put flour in bag.
Add meat to coat, then brown meat in 2 tablespoons butter.
After meat has browned good, add dissolved bouillon to pan and simmer for 1 hour or more. Add mushrooms, onion and sour cream and heat until all is warm.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: "summer" potatoes
directions: Fry potatoes.
Add ham.
Put cheese on top when done.
Cook until cheese melts.

title: microwave peanut patties
directions: Combine sugar, water, salt and corn syrup in a 2-quart glass bowl.
Bring to a boil in microwave, about 3 minutes.
Stir and add peanuts.
Cook 9 to 11 minutes more or until soft-ball stage. Remove and add oleo, vanilla and coloring.
Cool and beat until creamy.
Drop by the spoonfuls or pour onto greased cookie sheet.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix cream cheese with margarine.
Stir in corn.
Add sugar and stir in corn muffin mix.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes in a buttered 2-quart casserole dish.

title: turkey or chicken pot pie
directions: Melt margarine over low heat.
Add flour.
Stir until smooth. Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Gradually add milk.
Cook on medium heat.
Stir constantly until thickened and bubbly.
Stir in turkey, mixed vegetables, bouillon granules and pepper.
Cook until heated well over medium heat.
Spoon into 9-inch dish.
Cover with crescent rolls or pie crust.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes or until brown.
Let stand 10 minutes.

title: michigan cheese ball
directions: Beat ingredients together.
Let set in refrigerator overnight and roll into ball.
Chop walnuts and roll cheese ball onto them. (If Roka Blue cheese is unavailable, use 2 jars of Old English.)

title: chicken strips
directions: Beat egg.
Cut chicken in strips; dip in egg and then in bread crumbs.
Put in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes covered with foil.
Add bouillon liquid and bake 25 minutes more.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together except potato chips.
In casserole dish bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
After baking, crush potato chips on top.

title: turkey spaghetti(microwave)
directions: Melt oleo in a 1 3/4-quart Tupperware or any Tupperware-safe container.
Cook chopped vegetables in oleo until transparent. Add tomatoes and diced turkey; cook about 2 minutes longer.
Add olives.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Saute onion in oil in a Dutch oven until tender.
Add potato, celery, garlic, salt and pepper and saute for 10 minutes.
Add broth, broccoli and basil.
Stir well.
Bring mixture to a boil; cover, reduce heat and simmer for 20 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Transfer half of mixture to electric blender or food processor and process until smooth.
Repeat with remaining mixture.
Ladle soup into individual soup bowls.
Yields 8 cups.

title: cheese straws
directions: Combine ingredients.
Roll 1/4-inch thick; cut in strips and bake.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Drain all juice off fruit cocktail.
Blend all ingredients together and stir well.
Pour in fruit bowl.
Place in icebox until ready to serve.
Will serve 8 people.

title: sonya's sweet potato pie
directions: Put the mashed potatoes in a mixing bowl.
Add the lightly mixed eggs and blend with hand mixer until combined and smooth. Add sugar, nutmeg and flour and mix thoroughly.
Add the milk until blended.
Add the melted margarine and vanilla and mix on medium speed until incorporated.
Divide sweet potato mixture between 3 pie shells.
Bake in preheated oven at 375° for 45 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: roast and vegetables
directions: Take roast and cut in small pieces.
Put in large skillet and cook with lid on for 20 minutes.
Then add sliced mushrooms, onions and green peppers.
Add as much as you like.
Take your potatoes and quarter them, then slice them in small pieces and add to meat and other vegetables.
Cook until tender.

title: french salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in a 2-quart bottle and shake. Keeps in refrigerator forever.

title: texas bread
directions: Melt butter and a little garlic powder in baking dish.
Mix first 3 ingredients and drop in pan, using a tablespoon.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.
Fill with jelly or eat plain.

title: pepper cabbage
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients and bring them to a boil in small saucepan. Combine cabbage, onion and pepper in a bowl; pour sugar mixture over cabbage mixture. Chill. Serves 6 to 8.

title: mother's punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid, lemonade/water, orange juice/water, pineapple juice and enough water to make 1 gallon of punch; chill. Add 1 (2 liter) bottle cold ginger ale or 7-Up. Some of the punch base can be frozen in an ice ring mold to help keep the punch cold.

title: pierogi casserole
directions: Boil pierogies according to package directions.
Saute onion and mushrooms in oil or Pam spray.
Add tomatoes and spices.
Add boiled pierogies.
Heat thoroughly about 5 minutes.
Top with Parmesan cheese if desired.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: savory green beans
directions: Place hot cooked and drained green beans in a casserole. Cover with cheese sauce made from first 4 ingredients.
Dot with egg bits.
Add toasted bread crumbs.
Cover with cheese slices. Bake in oven until cheese melts.

title: velvet custard
directions: Add sugar, salt, nutmeg, milk and vanilla.
Beat eggs well; add to other ingredients and mix well.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350°.
Bake for 30 minutes.

title: aunt bee's squares
directions: Butter a large casserole dish.
Combine dressing mix and melted oleo, pressing half of mixture into a buttered dish.
In pan of boiling water, place squash, zucchini, onion, green pepper and celery.
Boil 5 to 10 minutes.
Drain well.
Add seasonings and water chestnuts; turn mixture into the casserole dish, over dressing mix.
Combine the soup and sour cream; spread over the vegetables.
Top with remaining dressing mix.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Put ground beef in bottom of a 9 x 9-inch baking dish. Sprinkle 1/2 package of soup mix over meat.
Layer 1 package frozen vegetables over seasoned meat.
Pour soup on top.
Bake 1 hour at 350° and then put Tater Tots on top.
Bake 30 more minutes.

title: steak and rice casserole
directions: Slice steak into 1/4-inch wide strips.
Melt one to two tablespoons
of the margarine in the skillet over medium heat; add meat
and
cook until brown.
Pour meat and uncooked rice into lightly greased dish.
Add consomme, onion, mushrooms and remainder of margarine.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Bring 1 c. water to a boil and pour over 1/2 cup c. shortening. Mix and let stand for 30 minutes or until completely cool. Stir together yeast, 1/2 c. warm water and 1 tsp. sugar. Let mixture stand about 5 minutes. Beat eggs at medium speed using a heavy duty stand mixer. Add 1/2 c. sugar and salt. Add shortening and yeast mixture. Reduce speed to low and gradually add 2 cups flour beating until well blended. Cover and chill for 12 hours or up to 5 days. When you are ready to use turn dough on a lightly floured surface and roll to 1/4 inch thickness. Cut with 2 1/2 inch round cutter. Make a crease across the middle

of each dough, round with a knife and fold in half. Gently press edges to seal and place rolls on lightly greased baking pan. Cover and let rise in warm place (85 degrees) free from drafts for 1 1/2 hours until doubled in size. Brush rolls with butter. Bake at 400 degrees for 15 minutes or until golden brown. Brush again with butter. This dough doesn't have to all be used at the same time. Break off what you need. It can be refrigerated for up to 5 days.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Combine jello and hot water; stir in cranberry sauce.
Add cold water with drained pineapple, celery, oranges and nuts.
Pour 1/2 of the mixture into pan and refrigerate until set.
Combine 1 package of cream cheese and sour cream.
Spread over and chill again.
When well set, combine cream cheese and 1 package prepared Dream Whip or Estee.
Spread on top and chill overnight.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Use 8 x 10-inch or 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook the pasta and drain.
Coat with the olive oil.
Sprinkle well with the Parmesan cheese, stirring.
Oil a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Layer the spaghetti, spinach, cottage cheese, sauce and Mozzarella.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream together shortening, vanilla, sugars and eggs.
Stir in rest of ingredients; mix thoroughly.
Shape dough into balls. Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten in crisscross pattern with fork dipped in flour.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: brownie swirl cheesecake
directions: Prepare brownie mix as directed.
Grease bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.
Pour batter evenly into pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Combine softened cream cheese, sugar and vanilla, mixing at medium speed with electric mixer until well blended. Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Pour over brownie layer.
Spoon melted chocolate over cream cheese mixture; cut through batter with knife for marble effect.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: hot chili
directions: Combine ground beef, onion and garlic in large skillet.
Cook until meat is lightly browned.
Add remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer one hour (or until thickened), skimming off grease.

title: dip for fruit
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Core and and slice apples, pears and peaches and use whole strawberries.

title: rhubarb ambrosia betty
directions: Mix
together
rhubarb, sugar, flour and salt.	Combine rind, orange, bread cubes, butter and coconut.
Put 1/2 of the bread mixture into
a greased 7 x 11-inch pan. Add rhubarb and top with rest
of
bread.
Bake
at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes. Serve warm with whipped topping.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and carrots together in salted water until tender; drain well.
Add soup, sour cream and pimento.
Melt butter; stir in stuffing mix.
Spread half of the stuffing mix in greased casserole.
Pour in squash mixture.
Cover with remaining stuffing mix.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: impossible pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients in blender container.
Blend until mixture is light yellow in color and all dry ingredients are mixed thoroughly.
Grease and flour a 10-inch pie pan.
Pour in blender mixture.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes or until a knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Coconut will rise to top and be golden brown.
There will be a thin layer of crust on the bottom.
Tastes like custard pie.

title: chicken hot dish
directions: Mix all ingredients together gently.
Put in casserole and bake one hour at 350°.

title: cream copped fruit mold
directions: Drain pineapple but preserve juice.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add 1 cup of the pineapple juice.
Refrigerate mixture until thickened.
Fold in crushed pineapple and marshmallows.
Spoon mixture into 9 x 11-inch dish or individual dishes.
Refrigerate until firm, but not quite set, so second layer will stick.

title: krispy lunch pickles
directions: Wash and slice cucumbers and chop onions and bell peppers. Let stand 3 hours in cold water and salt, then drain.
Mix vinegar, sugar and spice and boil.
Put drained cucumbers in and heat, but do not boil.
Put in jars and seal.

title: hawaiian fruit punch
directions: Note: Partial mixing may be done ahead of time for serving.

title: whiskey cake
directions: Mix all ingredients (except nuts) until smooth.
Add nuts. Pour into greased and floured tube or Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: fig jam
directions: To prepare chopped figs, pour boiling water over figs; let stand 10 minutes. Drain, stem and chop figs. Measure and add 3/4 cup water and sugar to figs. Slowly bring to boiling, stirring occasionally until sugar dissolves. Cook rapidly until thick. Stir frequently to prevent sticking. Add lemon juice and cook 1 minute longer. Pour, boiling hot, into sterilized Ball jars. Adjust caps. Yield: About 5 pints.

title: ground beef stew
directions: Brown ground beef in a large skillet; drain.
Add tomatoes and mixed vegetables with liquid.
Add potato, onion and garlic. Season to taste.
Simmer, uncovered, until potatoes are tender, about 15 minutes.
Serve over rice.
Makes 5 servings.

title: shoo-fly pie
directions: Mix together, then dissolve 2 teaspoons baking soda
in extra 1/2 cup hot water; add to mixture and beat.
Put into pie shells. Put crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° until top is dry and done.

title: best ever apple dumpling
directions: Make a mixture of 1 1/2 teaspoons cinnamon and 1/2 cup sugar. Place each apple on a 7-inch square of pastry.
Fill the cavity of each apple with the above mixture; dot with butter and wrap. Place in oblong baking dish.

title: pepperoni biscuits
directions: In a bowl, combine biscuit mix, milk, butter, garlic powder and italian seasoning.
Stir in pepperoni and cheese.
Drop by heaping tablespoonfuls 2 inches apart on an ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 400 degrees for 15 minutes or until golden brown. Serve warm.

title: apple crunch
directions: Arrange apples in shallow 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Sweeten to taste, using the brown sugar.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and dot with butter.
Combine flour, sugar, salt and baking powder.
Add beaten egg and mix with a fork until crumbly.
Pour over apples and shake so mixture will settle through and down.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until apples are tender and top is brown.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Chop cauliflower and broccoli up fine and pour dressing over them.
Let chill.

title: sweet potato delight
directions: Slice sweet potatoes in an oblong casserole dish.
Add pie filling, then cranberry sauce.
Dot the marmalade and preserves on top.
Bake at 350°
for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: cheesy beans
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Add flour.
Mix in milk, stirring until even consistency.
Add cheese.
When cheese is completely melted, add green beans; leave on low heat for 15 minutes, stirring. Enjoy.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Thaw broccoli and strain water out.
Mix butter and onion. Stir in flour and add water.
Cook until thickens and comes to a boil, stirring continuously.
Add Cheez Whiz and broccoli.
Add beaten eggs and mix.
Put into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole. Cover with crumbs and dot with butter.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
May be made day before serving, refrigerating unbaked overnight.
Bake 30 minutes prior to serving.

title: broccoli and cheese casserole
directions: Thaw broccoli in 1 cup boiling salted water.
Saute onion and celery in oleo.
Add soup and milk.
Simmer 3 minutes.
Add Cheez Whiz and mix well.
Add broccoli and rice.
Add salt and pepper. Put in buttered casserole dish and bake 40 minutes at 325°.

title: cracklin corn bread
directions: Beat eggs; add milk; beat again well.
To the egg and milk mixture add cornmeal mix, stir until well blended.
Add melted margarine, sugar and cracklins.

title: squash casserole
directions: Combine first 2 ingredients.
Cook, drain and mash together. Add remaining ingredients, reserving 1/2 cup cheese to sprinkle on top.
Pour into buttered casserole dish and bake at 375° until firm and cheese is slightly brown.

title: good rice pudding
directions: Pour into buttered casserole dish.
Set in pan of hot water in oven and bake (preheated oven) at 350° for 50 minutes (until knife comes out clean).

title: sweet 'n sour green beans
directions: In saucepan, combine onion, tomato sauce, bacon fat, vinegar and sugar.
Drain green beans and add to mixture; salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer for 25 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Add Jell-O and juice from pineapple into saucepan and heat. Stir in cranberry sauce and nuts.
Mix well and pour into mold. Chill.

title: pizza
directions: Measure mix into a bowl.
Stir mustard into milk and blend into mix.
Knead 1 minutes on board dusted with biscuit mix.
Roll to fit 12 inch pizza pan.
Prick surface with a fork.
Bake in hot oven, 425°, for 5-7 minutes or until set.
Remove from oven. Reduce heat to 375°.

title: seven layer taco salad
directions: On large plate, spread refried beans; for next layer, add precooked taco meat.
Third layer is sour cream, 4th layer is chopped lettuce, 5th layer is cheese, 6th layer is chopped tomatoes and 7th layer is sliced black olives.
Use Tostitos chips to scoop up taco salad.

title: play dough
directions: Mix all ingredients in saucepan.
Add a few drops of food coloring.
Cook over medium heat about 5 minutes or until it pulls away from sides of pan and forms a ball.
Knead a few minutes when cool enough to handle.
Store in an airtight container.

title: chicken breast with orange basil pesto
directions: Place basil, orange rind and garlic in blender or food processor.
Add orange juice, mustard, oil, salt and pepper. Process until paste is formed.
Marinate chicken in mixture overnight.
Spread mixture over chicken and grill or broil until done.
Also good with boneless pork chops.
(Low-fat.)

title: broccoli rice
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine margarine, onion and water and bring to a boil.
Add broccoli; cook 3 minutes.
Add rice.
Remove from heat and let stand until liquid is absorbed.
Stir in Cheez Whiz and soup.
Turn into a casserole and bake at 325° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: coconut custard pie
directions: Mix and pour in an unbaked pie shell; bake at 350° for about 50 minutes or less.

title: new two-flavor jello gelatin rainbow cake
directions: Place cake layers, top sides up, in 2 clean layer pans.
Prick each cake with utility fork at 1/2-inch intervals.
Dissolve each flavor of gelatin separately in 1 cup boiling water and carefully spoon each over one cake pan in warm water for 10 seconds.
Turn out onto serving plate.
Top with 1 cup Cool Whip.
Unmold second cake layer.
Place carefully on first layer.
Frost top and sides with remaining Cool Whip.
Chill.
Garnish as desired.

title: fancy egg scramble
directions: In saucepan, melt 2 tablespoons butter.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Add milk; cook and stir until bubbly.
Stir in cheese until melted and set aside.
In large skillet, cook ham and onions in 3 tablespoons butter until onion is tender, but not brown.
Add eggs and scramble just until set.
Fold into cheese mixture; turn into 7 1/2 x 12 x 2-inch baking dish.
Combine 4 teaspoons butter (melted), crumbs and paprika.
Sprinkle on top of eggs.
Chill until 30 minutes before serving.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes or until bubbly.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: jello fluff
directions: Mix dry jello, cottage cheese, Cool Whip and drained pineapple in a bowl.
Mix well.
Add nuts.
Chill before serving.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes into 1/8ths.
Put all into heavy pan with lid on. Cook over medium heat until potatoes are tender.
Remove the lid and cook a little longer to thicken the syrup.

title: forgotten cookies (meringue drops)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat egg whites and salt until very stiff.
Beat in sugar.
Add food coloring, if desired.
Fold in chocolate bits.
Drop by teaspoons on greased cookie sheets.
Size can be varied without problem.
For serving to children or nursing home patients, it is nice to make small cookies (about 1/2 teaspoon).

title: buttery pasta with shrimp
directions: Have ready cooked spaghetti.
In heavy saucepan, melt butter and add remaining ingredients (except tomatoes and cheese).
Stir to blend.
Cook over medium heat, 5 to 7 minutes.
Add spaghetti; stir to blend.
Continue cooking over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until spaghetti is heated through, 3 to 5 minutes. Remove from heat and add tomatoes.
Cover; let stand 1 minute. Before serving, sprinkle cheese over top.
Carrots and celery may be added if desired.

title: dessert cake
directions: Whip ingredients 150 strokes by hand.
Add nuts and crushed pineapple last.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: monkey sweet rolls
directions: Cut each biscuit into 4 pieces.
Roll each piece into mixture of 1/2 teaspoon of cinnamon and 1/3 cup sugar.

title: coconut-crusted perch
directions: For sweet-sour sauce, combine the first five ingredients in a small saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer, uncovered for 5 minutes or until slightly thickened.
Remove from the heat and keep warm.
In a shallow dish, combine the cracker crumbs and coconut.
In another shallow dish, whisk the eggs, milk and salt. Dip each fillet in egg mixture, then coat with crumb mixture.
In a large skillet, cook fish in 3 tablespoons oil in batches over medium-high heat for 1 to 2 minutes on each side or until fish flakes easily with a fork, adding oil as needed.
Serve with sweet-sour sauce.
Yield:
10 to 12 servings.

title: cheeseburger loaf
directions: Blend all ingredients, except cheese, until thoroughly mixed. Line loaf pan with heavy waxed paper.
Place 1/2 cup cheese in bottom of pan; spread evenly.
Cover with half the meat, then remaining cheese, then remaining meat.

title: holiday card holder
directions: Cut a green triangle and a gold star out of poster board.
Glue on star, then glue on plastic paper clips or clothespins.
Let dry. Hang by punching a hole through the poster board where the tree and star meet.
Loop a ribbon through the hole and tie a knot.
Hang on a hook or attach to refrigerator with heavy tape.
Clip the cards or pictures to the holders.

title: ewoldt family meat loaf
directions: In 9 x 13 cake pan, add all ingredients. Mix with hands. Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes. Drain grease from sides. Cut in serving size squares.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Layer cabbage, pepper, onions and pimentos; set aside.
Mix oil, sugar, vinegar, salt and celery seed.
Boil for 2 minutes. Pour hot dressing over vegetables.
Cover tightly and refrigerate at least 4 hours before serving.
Keeps for at least a week.

title: dill sauce
directions: Melt the butter.
Stir in the flour and cook slowly for 1 minute.
Add chicken broth gradually.
Stir in the dill weed, vinegar, and sugar and simmer for 10 minutes.
Stir in the sour cream and remove from the heat.
Use over beef or chicken.

title: twilla's hobo dinner
directions: Take a piece of aluminum foil and put hamburger patty in center of foil; arrange "veggies" on top of patties and cover with Catalina dressing.
Seal foil.
Continue until all patties are done.
Place on grill (medium heat) and cook for approximately 45 minutes, turning often.
It's a meal all wrapped in one!!!!

title: crabmeat casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except the bread crumbs, butter and cheese.
Place in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with mixture of the remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° until bubbly and brown, about 50 to 60 minutes.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: steamed fish with parsley butter
directions: Thaw fish if frozen.
Top each fish steak with a lemon slice. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Pour boiling water into wok to reach 1/2 inches below steamer rack.
Place fish on steamer rack. Cover wok and steam for 10 to 12 minutes or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork.
Remove to platter.

title: hush puppies
directions: Finely chop onion.
Combine cornmeal mix and onion in bowl. Add 1 egg (beaten) and milk stirring to combine.
Add garlic to taste.
Let set for 2 or 3 minutes to thicken.
Drop by teaspoon into hot fat (375°) frying only a few at a time.
Fry until golden brown.
Drain on absorbent paper.

title: refrigerator bread and butter pickles
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients and let set overnight. Drain.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over the pickles. Refrigerate for 6 hours before serving.

title: fruit salad
directions: Put sugar, flour, egg, butter, milk and reserved pineapple juice in boiler. Cook, stirring constantly until thickened. Cool. Combine apple, pineapple
and
nuts.
Pour
sauce
over. Mix and serve. This keeps well and is better the second day.

title: nachos
directions: Cover cookie sheet with Doritos.
In large saucepan mix chili and taco sauce; cook until well heated.
Pour over Doritos. Sprinkle cheese on top.
Broil in oven until cheese starts to bubble.

title: ginger crinkles
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Stir together first 5 ingredients. Combine the remaining ingredients and beat well.
Add dry ingredients to beaten mixture, beating well.
Form 1-inch balls. Roll in granulated sugar, if desired.
Place 2 inches apart on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake about 10 minutes.
Makes 48.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cook over low/medium heat until just comes to boil.
Brush as desired on meat while grilling.

title: shirley sauce
directions: Peel tomatoes and cut fine.
Chop onion, green pepper and celery.
Combine vegetables in pan and add other ingredients. Boil 1 hour.
Bottle in hot canning jars while
hot.

title: corn relish
directions: Mix all ingredients with corn and cook 30 to 40 minutes.
For less sweet, add 2 cups sugar; for sweeter, use 3 cups sugar.
Seal in sterilized jars.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix together wafers and 1 stick (or a little more) margarine and press in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch dish or pan.
Cut bananas lengthwise and put on top of wafers.
Beat for 15 minutes the 1 stick margarine, egg and powdered sugar.
Spread over bananas. Drain pineapple and put over sugar mixture.
Top with Cool Whip or Dream Whip.
Sprinkle nuts on top and maraschino cherries.

title: working women chicken pie
directions: Mix broth, vegetables and soup; pour over chicken in a baking pan.
Mix well; pour over chicken and stir.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: one step lasagna
directions: Combine water with sauce.
Cover bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish with 1 1/2 cups sauce.
Arrange layer of uncooked noodles on top of sauce.
Spread half Ricotta and half of Mozzarella cheese over noodles.
Sprinkle with 2 tablespoons Parmesan cheese.
Add another layer of sauce.
Repeat with a layer of noodles remaining Ricotta and Mozzarella and 2 tablespoons Parmesan.
Top with a layer of noodles.
Pour remaining sauce over, spread evenly to cover edges of noodles.
Sprinkle with 1/4 cup of Parmesan.
Cover tightly with heavy-duty foil.
Bake in a preheated oven for 1 hour until knife passes easily through pasta.
Let it stand covered on rack for 10 minutes.

title: dessert zucchini fritters(makes 2 servings)
directions: In a blender container, combine all ingredients, except raisins and zucchini.
Blend until smooth.
Pour mixture into a bowl.
Drain zucchini on paper towels.
Stir zucchini and raisins into egg mixture.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Break spaghetti noodles in half, then cook according to package directions.
Drain.
Dice all vegetables and add to the cooked spaghetti.
Pour the bottle of Kraft Italian dressing over this mixture.
Add Salad Supreme to taste.

title: tomato-beef casserole
directions: Lightly brown onion in shortening.
Add remaining ingredients, except cheese.
Put in 1-quart greased casserole dish.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes, until hot and bubbly.

title: oriental veggies
directions: In skillet, heat oil and cook sliced green beans, cauliflower, carrots and onions.

title: caviar pie
directions: Spread egg salad on plate.
Combine sour cream, onions and lemon juice.
Spread over salad and top with caviar.

title: cherry bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Beat in egg; mix and sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with the syrup from the chopped cherries and nuts. Place dough into 9 x 5-inch bread pan.
Let stand 2 minutes before baking in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake for 30 minutes at 400°.

title: barbecue mini meat loaves
directions: If you use turkey, add one beaten egg.

title: meat balls
directions: Roll in balls and brown.

title: savory swiss steak
directions: Brown steak on both sides.
Add water, tomato paste and contents of the beef stew seasoning package.
Simmer while covered for 2 hours.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: honey balls
directions: Cream the butter.
Add honey and cream.
Add vanilla and salt. Add flour and nuts; blend.
Shape into balls.
Use 1 level teaspoon.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 250° oven about 30 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar while still warm.
Makes 10 dozen.

title: pasta and cheese in a pot
directions: Cook meats and drain.
Add onions, garlic, sauce, tomatoes and mushrooms; simmer 20 minutes.
Cook shells and drain.
Pour half of shells into a deep casserole; cover with half of the sauce.
Layer sliced zucchini.
Spread with half of sour cream and cheeses.
Then add other half of shells, sauce, etc.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove lid to let brown if needed for last 5 minutes. Serves 8.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Combine potatoes, 1/2 cup butter, onion, soup and sour cream and stir well.
Put into greased 2 1/2-quart casserole.

title: cheese bars
directions: Cream butter with cheese.
Blend in flour and cayenne pepper. Fold in cereal. Press into a buttered baking pan (8 or 9-inch baking pan).
Bake at 375°
for 20 minutes, or until top is crisp. Allow to cool thoroughly.
Cut into bars and serve warm or cold. Stores well in refrigerator for several days.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Grease and flour three 8-inch cake pans.
Combine flour, sugar, salt, baking soda, cinnamon and nutmeg in a mixing bowl.
Add eggs and oil.
Mix until moistened.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Spoon into baking pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool for 10 minutes.
Remove cake from pans.
When thoroughly cool, frost with Cream Cheese Icing.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pack in oiled loaf pan.
Bake at 350°
for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Let stand 8 to 10 minutes before slicing.

title: chicken and broccoli
directions: Lay broccoli on bottom of casserole.
Mix cream of chicken soup, mayo, curry and lemon juice.
Spread on top.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Sprinkle croutons last 5 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serve with rice and tossed salad.

title: taco salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Chill.
Top with mild taco sauce or picante sauce or salsa.
May also top with guacamole and/or sour cream.
Serves 8.

title: shrimp asparagus casserole
directions: Cook asparagus until almost done.
Melt margarine.
Stir in flour and then cream.
Add Parmesan cheese and blend well.
Stir in shrimp, mix well.
Put asparagus in 9 x 9-inch casserole dish. Pour sauce over all.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: watermelon pickles
directions: Dissolve salt in cold water; pour over watermelon rind.
Stir in additional water if necessary to cover rind.
Let stand in cool place 8 hours.
Drain rind; cover with cold water.
Heat to boiling.

Cook uncovered just until tender, 10 to 15 minutes. Drain; tie cloves, cinnamon and ginger root in cheesecloth bag. Heat cheesecloth bag, sugar and vinegar to boil in large saucepan, stirring occasionally.
Boil uncovered 5 minutes; reduce heat. Add rind.
Simmer uncovered 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Remove cheesecloth bag.
Immediately pack mixture in hot jars, leaving 1/4-inch headspace.
Wipe rims of jars.
Seal and process in boiling water bath 10 minutes.
Makes
7 to 8 pints pickles.

title: shoney's chocolate sauce
directions: Mix sugar, flour and cocoa well.
Add milk, shortening and butter.
Start on low heat
in saucepan.
Cook until thickens. Remove from heat.
Add vanilla.
Good as hot fudge over ice cream.

title: 24 hour cocktails
directions: Combine whiskey, water and sugar.
Squeeze lemons and add juice and rinds to mixture.
Store in refrigerator for 24 hours. Remove and squeeze rinds and discard.
Serve in punch cups or old fashioned glasses.

title: cabbage rolls for 100
directions: Cut the stiff ridge core from cabbage.
Cook leaves until they are just starting to soften; drain.
Combine raw hamburger, sausage, rice, onion, eggs, salt, pepper and garlic salt.
Place a portion of meat mixture at stem end of each leaf and roll up, folding the sides over meat.
Chop remaining cabbage up and place in bottom of roaster.
Arrange rolls in roaster.
Layer more chopped cabbage if desired.
Pour tomato sauce over all.
Cook at 250° about 2 hours then turn back to 150° and simmer all night.
You can put sauerkraut in bottom of roaster and between layers.

title: bread and dip
directions: Scoop out middle of round rye bread.
Cut into pieces.
Cut up another loaf of bread also.
Fill scooped out loaf with dip.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour Bundt pan or use Baker's Joy (sprays oil and flour at the same time).
In a large bowl, cream margarine, shortening, sugar and eggs until well blended.
Sift flour and add alternately with 7-Up, beginning and ending with flour.
Add flavorings.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake at 325° for at least 1 hour or until done.
Let cool in pan for 20 minutes. Turn out onto rack and cool completely.

title: homemade french dressing
directions: Mix and store. Will keep several weeks.

title: meat loaf, barbecue style
directions: Mix together beef, crumbs, onion, beaten egg, salt, pepper and 1/2 can tomato sauce.
Form into loaf.
Put in shallow 7 x 10-inch pan.
Combine all remaining ingredients.
Pour over loaf.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Baste occasionally. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: 7-layer salad
directions: Chop lettuce and place in bowl.
In layers, place ingredients in order given.
Cover tightly and refrigerate 24 hours before serving.
Right before serving, mix up the salad.

title: milwaukee pork chops
directions: Fry chops until brown. Combine remaining ingredients and pour over chops. Reduce heat; cover and cook slowly until tender, at least an hour. The longer they simmer, the better they taste.

title: chocolate applesauce cake
directions: Cream the shortening, sugar and eggs together on low speed. Sift in another bowl the flour, cinnamon, salt, soda and cocoa. Add dry ingredients alternately with applesauce to creamed mixture.
Pour in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with nuts and chocolate chips mixed together with 2 tablespoons sugar over top of batter.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: carrot salad(serves 8 to 10)
directions: Parboil carrots and drain.
Mix soup, vinegar, salad oil, mustard, sugar and Worcestershire.
Pour over cooled carrots and add rest of vegetables.
Let stand in refrigerator, covered, several hours or overnight.
Keeps well for 1 to 2 weeks.
You may also add green beans, lima or chick peas.

title: frozen cucumbers
directions: Let cucumbers and onion slices stand 2 hours in salt.
Drain and rinse well.
Add vinegar and sugar.
Let stand 1/2 hour or until juice covers cucumbers.
Freeze in whatever size containers you wish to use.
Thaw and serve.
Will keep several days in refrigerator after thawing.
I use a 2-quart Pyrex roasting pan to make relish and freeze in different size containers.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Chop broccoli and onion.
Mix with mayonnaise and let set several hours or overnight in refrigerator.
Add the other ingredients and serve with baked shrimp.
(Recipe contained herein.)

title: cheese snacks
directions: Heat oven to 450° (hot).
Blend thoroughly with fork the Bisquick, cheese, mayonnaise and milk.
Shape into 1/2-inch balls. Roll in mixture of parsley and onion.
Bake on greased baking sheet for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes about 30.

title: mock pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into deep, unbaked pie shell. Bake at 375° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: buttermilk pie(makes 2 pies)
directions: Mix flour and sugar together.
Add remaining ingredients and pour into 2 pie shells.
Cook at 350° until custard is firm.
This pie needs no topping.
You can add Angel Flake coconut and nuts if you like.

title: angel food cake with mocha icing
directions: Slowly stir all ingredients and then chill for about 1 hour. Then whip using mixer until fairly firm texture.
Chill for 3 hours.
Whip again if needed.
Slice cake crosswise in three equal layers.
Frost between layers, top and sides.
This will probably be more than needed if using a store-bought cake since they tend to be smaller than those you bake yourself.

title: cheese vegetable soup
directions: Cook carrots, celery and onion in margarine in 4-quart Dutch oven until celery and onions are transparent, about 10 minutes. Stir in baking mix, paprika, pepper and cayenne.
Remove from heat.
Gradually stir in chicken broth.
Heat to boiling over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Boil 1 minute.
Reduce heat; stir in half and half and shredded cheese.
Heat until cheese is melted.

title: wacky cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Make one big hole (for oil) and two little ones.
Pour water over all and mix.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: heart healthy pumpkin muffins
directions: Combine dry ingredients, except nuts and raisins.
In another bowl, mix oil, egg and egg whites, water and pumpkin.
Add to dry ingredients.
Mix thoroughly. Stir in raisins and nuts.

title: ham 'n broccoli
directions: Thaw and break apart broccoli.
Combine all ingredients.
Mix as box directs, omitting the butter.
Pour into microwave dish. Cook as box directs.

title: broiled crab meltaways
directions: Slice muffins in half (for canapes, cut each half into quarters).
Mix well all remaining ingredients.
Spread on English muffins.
You must freeze for at least 30 minutes! (They can be frozen for weeks.)

title: barbecued sirloin roast
directions: Sprinkle both sides of roast with monosodium glutamate.
Place in a shallow baking dish.
Thoroughly combine vinegar, catsup, cooking oil, soy sauce, Worcestershire sauce, mustard, salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Pour mixture over roast and marinate for 2 to 3 hours, turning once or twice.
Place roast on grill or broiler pan for about 45 minutes to an hour, turning and basting every 10 to 15 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: irish cream puffs
directions: Heat margarine and water to a rolling boil.
Add flour.
Stir over low heat for 1 minute until mixture forms a ball.
Remove from heat.
Add eggs.
Beat with mixer until smooth.
Spoon mixture onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes until browned.
Stir together Cool Whip and instant pudding mix.
Slice top off warm puff.
Spoon in filling and replace top.
Cool.
Keep refrigerated.
Makes 18 puffs.

title: zucchini skillet medley
directions: Heat oil in skillet.
Add celery, onions and garlic.
Saute until tender.
Add zucchini, tomatoes, green peppers and carrots. Saute 10 minutes.

title: creamy pesto chicken and bow ties
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions.
Drain.
Meanwhile, heat butter in skillet.
Add chicken and cook until browned, stirring often.
Add soup, pesto sauce and milk.
Bring to a boil. Cook over low heat for 5 minutes or until done.
Stir in drained pasta and heat through.
Serves 4.
